v8
V8 is Googleâ€™s open source high-performance JavaScript and WebAssembly engine, written in C++. It is used in Chrome and in Node.js, among others. It implements ECMAScript and WebAssembly, and runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux systems that use x64, IA-32, or ARM processors. V8 can be embedded into any C++ application.

56class JSCallReducerAssembler : public JSGraphAssembler {
57 static constexpr bool kMarkLoopExits = true;
58
59 public:
60 JSCallReducerAssembler(JSCallReducer* reducer, Node* node,
61 Node* effect = nullptr, Node* control = nullptr)
62 : JSGraphAssembler(
63 reducer->broker(), reducer->JSGraphForGraphAssembler(),
64 reducer->ZoneForGraphAssembler(), BranchSemantics::kJS,
65 [reducer](Node* n) { reducer->RevisitForGraphAssembler(n); },
66 kMarkLoopExits),
67 dependencies_(reducer->dependencies()),
68 node_(node) {
69 InitializeEffectControl(
70 effect ? effect : NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node),
71 control ? control : NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node));
72
73 // Finish initializing the outermost catch scope.
74 bool has_handler =
75 NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &outermost_handler_);
76 outermost_catch_scope_.set_has_handler(has_handler);
77 }

182 class TryCatchBuilder0 {
183 public:
184 using TryFunction = VoidGenerator0;
185 using CatchFunction = std::function<void(TNode<Object>)>;
186
187 TryCatchBuilder0(JSCallReducerAssembler* gasm, const TryFunction& try_body)
188 : gasm_(gasm), try_body_(try_body) {}
189
190 void Catch(const CatchFunction& catch_body) {
191 TNode<Object> handler_exception;
192 Effect handler_effect{nullptr};
193 Control handler_control{nullptr};
194
195 auto continuation = gasm_->MakeLabel();
196
197 // Try.
198 {
199 CatchScope catch_scope = CatchScope::Inner(gasm_->temp_zone(), gasm_);
200 try_body_();
201 gasm_->Goto(&continuation);
202
203 catch_scope.MergeExceptionalPaths(&handler_exception, &handler_effect,
204 &handler_control);
205 }
206
207 // Catch.
208 {
209 gasm_->InitializeEffectControl(handler_effect, handler_control);
210 catch_body(handler_exception);
211 gasm_->Goto(&continuation);
212 }
213
214 gasm_->Bind(&continuation);
215 }
216
217 private:
218 JSCallReducerAssembler* const gasm_;
219 const VoidGenerator0 try_body_;
220 };
221
222 TryCatchBuilder0 Try(const VoidGenerator0& try_body) {
223 return {this, try_body};
224 }

226 using ConditionFunction1 = std::function<TNode<Boolean>(TNode<Number>)>;
227 using StepFunction1 = std::function<TNode<Number>(TNode<Number>)>;
228 class ForBuilder0 {
229 using For0BodyFunction = std::function<void(TNode<Number>)>;
230
231 public:
232 ForBuilder0(JSGraphAssembler* gasm, TNode<Number> initial_value,
233 const ConditionFunction1& cond, const StepFunction1& step)
234 : gasm_(gasm),
235 initial_value_(initial_value),
236 cond_(cond),
237 step_(step) {}
238
239 void Do(const For0BodyFunction& body) {
240 auto loop_exit = gasm_->MakeLabel();
241
242 {
243 GraphAssembler::LoopScope<kPhiRepresentation> loop_scope(gasm_);
244
245 auto loop_header = loop_scope.loop_header_label();
246 auto loop_body = gasm_->MakeLabel();
247
248 gasm_->Goto(loop_header, initial_value_);
249
250 gasm_->Bind(loop_header);
251 TNode<Number> i = loop_header->PhiAt<Number>(0);
252
253 gasm_->BranchWithHint(cond_(i), &loop_body, &loop_exit,
254 BranchHint::kTrue);
255
256 gasm_->Bind(&loop_body);
257 body(i);
258 gasm_->Goto(loop_header, step_(i));
259 }
260
261 gasm_->Bind(&loop_exit);
262 }
263
264 private:
265 static constexpr MachineRepresentation kPhiRepresentation =
266 MachineRepresentation::kTagged;
267
268 JSGraphAssembler* const gasm_;
269 const TNode<Number> initial_value_;
270 const ConditionFunction1 cond_;
271 const StepFunction1 step_;
272 };
273
274 ForBuilder0 ForZeroUntil(TNode<Number> excluded_limit) {
275 TNode<Number> initial_value = ZeroConstant();
276 auto cond = [=, this](TNode<Number> i) {
277 return NumberLessThan(i, excluded_limit);
278 };
279 auto step = [=, this](TNode<Number> i) {
280 return NumberAdd(i, OneConstant());
281 };
282 return {this, initial_value, cond, step};
283 }
284
285 ForBuilder0 Forever(TNode<Number> initial_value, const StepFunction1& step) {
286 return {this, initial_value,
287 [=, this](TNode<Number>) { return TrueConstant(); }, step};
288 }

290 using For1BodyFunction = std::function<void(TNode<Number>, TNode<Object>*)>;
291 class ForBuilder1 {
292 public:
293 ForBuilder1(JSGraphAssembler* gasm, TNode<Number> initial_value,
294 const ConditionFunction1& cond, const StepFunction1& step,
295 TNode<Object> initial_arg0)
296 : gasm_(gasm),
297 initial_value_(initial_value),
298 cond_(cond),
299 step_(step),
300 initial_arg0_(initial_arg0) {}
301
302 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT ForBuilder1& Do(const For1BodyFunction& body) {
303 body_ = body;
304 return *this;
305 }
306
307 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT TNode<Object> Value() {
308 DCHECK(body_);
309 TNode<Object> arg0 = initial_arg0_;
310
311 auto loop_exit = gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel(kPhiRepresentation);
312
313 {
314 GraphAssembler::LoopScope<kPhiRepresentation, kPhiRepresentation>
315 loop_scope(gasm_);
316
317 auto loop_header = loop_scope.loop_header_label();
318 auto loop_body = gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel(kPhiRepresentation);
319
320 gasm_->Goto(loop_header, initial_value_, initial_arg0_);
321
322 gasm_->Bind(loop_header);
323 TNode<Number> i = loop_header->PhiAt<Number>(0);
324 arg0 = loop_header->PhiAt<Object>(1);
325
326 gasm_->BranchWithHint(cond_(i), &loop_body, &loop_exit,
327 BranchHint::kTrue, arg0);
328
329 gasm_->Bind(&loop_body);
330 body_(i, &arg0);
331 gasm_->Goto(loop_header, step_(i), arg0);
332 }
333
334 gasm_->Bind(&loop_exit);
335 return TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(loop_exit.PhiAt<Object>(0));
336 }
337
338 void ValueIsUnused() { USE(Value()); }
339
340 private:
341 static constexpr MachineRepresentation kPhiRepresentation =
342 MachineRepresentation::kTagged;
343
344 JSGraphAssembler* const gasm_;
345 const TNode<Number> initial_value_;
346 const ConditionFunction1 cond_;
347 const StepFunction1 step_;
348 For1BodyFunction body_;
349 const TNode<Object> initial_arg0_;
350 };
351
352 ForBuilder1 For1(TNode<Number> initial_value, const ConditionFunction1& cond,
353 const StepFunction1& step, TNode<Object> initial_arg0) {
354 return {this, initial_value, cond, step, initial_arg0};
355 }
356
357 ForBuilder1 For1ZeroUntil(TNode<Number> excluded_limit,
358 TNode<Object> initial_arg0) {
359 TNode<Number> initial_value = ZeroConstant();
360 auto cond = [=, this](TNode<Number> i) {
361 return NumberLessThan(i, excluded_limit);
362 };
363 auto step = [=, this](TNode<Number> i) {
364 return NumberAdd(i, OneConstant());
365 };
366 return {this, initial_value, cond, step, initial_arg0};
367 }

369 void ThrowIfNotCallable(TNode<Object> maybe_callable,
370 FrameState frame_state) {
371 IfNot(ObjectIsCallable(maybe_callable))
372 .Then(_ {
373 JSCallRuntime1(Runtime::kThrowCalledNonCallable, maybe_callable,
374 ContextInput(), frame_state);
375 Unreachable(); // The runtime call throws unconditionally.
376 })
377 .ExpectTrue();
378 }

422 private:

477 // Returns {index,value}. Assumes that the map has not changed, but possibly
478 // the length and backing store.
479 std::pair<TNode<Number>, TNode<Object>> SafeLoadElement(ElementsKind kind,
480 TNode<JSArray> o,
481 TNode<Number> index) {
482 // Make sure that the access is still in bounds, since the callback could
483 // have changed the array's size.
484 TNode<Number> length = LoadJSArrayLength(o, kind);
485 index = CheckBounds(index, length);
486
487 // Reload the elements pointer before calling the callback, since the
488 // previous callback might have resized the array causing the elements
489 // buffer to be re-allocated.
490 TNode<HeapObject> elements =
491 LoadField<HeapObject>(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements(), o);
492 TNode<Object> value = LoadElement<Object>(
493 AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(kind), elements, index);
494 return std::make_pair(index, value);
495 }
496
497 template <typename... Vars>
498 TNode<Object> MaybeSkipHole(
499 TNode<Object> o, ElementsKind kind,
500 GraphAssemblerLabel<sizeof...(Vars)>* continue_label,
501 TNode<Vars>... vars) {
502 if (!IsHoleyElementsKind(kind)) return o;
503
504 auto if_not_hole = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentationOf<Vars>::value...);
505 BranchWithHint(HoleCheck(kind, o), continue_label, &if_not_hole,
506 BranchHint::kFalse, vars...);
507
508 // The contract is that we don't leak "the hole" into "user JavaScript",
509 // so we must rename the {element} here to explicitly exclude "the hole"
510 // from the type of {element}.
511 Bind(&if_not_hole);
512 return TypeGuardNonInternal(o);
513 }
514
515 TNode<Smi> LoadJSArrayLength(TNode<JSArray> array, ElementsKind kind) {
516 return LoadField<Smi>(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(kind), array);
517 }
518 void StoreJSArrayLength(TNode<JSArray> array, TNode<Number> value,
519 ElementsKind kind) {
520 StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(kind), array, value);
521 }
522 void StoreFixedArrayBaseElement(TNode<FixedArrayBase> o, TNode<Number> index,
523 TNode<Object> v, ElementsKind kind) {
524 StoreElement(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(kind), o, index, v);
525 }
526
527 TNode<FixedArrayBase> LoadElements(TNode<JSObject> o) {
528 return LoadField<FixedArrayBase>(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements(), o);
529 }
530 TNode<Smi> LoadFixedArrayBaseLength(TNode<FixedArrayBase> o) {
531 return LoadField<Smi>(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayLength(), o);
532 }
533
534 TNode<Boolean> HoleCheck(ElementsKind kind, TNode<Object> v) {
535 return IsDoubleElementsKind(kind)
536 ? NumberIsFloat64Hole(TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(v))
537 : IsTheHole(v);
538 }
539};

583 TNode<JSFunction> CreateClosureFromBuiltinSharedFunctionInfo(
584 SharedFunctionInfoRef shared, TNode<Context> context) {
585 DCHECK(shared.HasBuiltinId());
586 Handle<FeedbackCell> feedback_cell =
587 isolate()->factory()->many_closures_cell();
588 Callable const callable =
589 Builtins::CallableFor(isolate(), shared.builtin_id());
590 CodeRef code = MakeRef(broker(), *callable.code());
591 return AddNode<JSFunction>(graph()->NewNode(
592 javascript()->CreateClosure(shared, code), HeapConstant(feedback_cell),
593 context, effect(), control()));
594 }
595
596 void CallPromiseExecutor(TNode<Object> executor, TNode<JSFunction> resolve,
597 TNode<JSFunction> reject, FrameState frame_state) {
598 JSConstructNode n(node_ptr());
599 const ConstructParameters& p = n.Parameters();
600 FeedbackSource no_feedback_source{};
601 Node* no_feedback = UndefinedConstant();
602 MayThrow(_ {
603 return AddNode<Object>(graph()->NewNode(
604 javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(2), p.frequency(),
605 no_feedback_source,
606 ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined),
607 executor, UndefinedConstant(), resolve, reject, no_feedback,
608 n.context(), frame_state, effect(), control()));
609 });
610 }
611
612 void CallPromiseReject(TNode<JSFunction> reject, TNode<Object> exception,
613 FrameState frame_state) {
614 JSConstructNode n(node_ptr());
615 const ConstructParameters& p = n.Parameters();
616 FeedbackSource no_feedback_source{};
617 Node* no_feedback = UndefinedConstant();
618 MayThrow(_ {
619 return AddNode<Object>(graph()->NewNode(
620 javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(1), p.frequency(),
621 no_feedback_source,
622 ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined),
623 reject, UndefinedConstant(), exception, no_feedback, n.context(),
624 frame_state, effect(), control()));
625 });
626 }
627};

629class FastApiCallReducerAssembler : public JSCallReducerAssembler {
630 public:
631 FastApiCallReducerAssembler(
632 JSCallReducer* reducer, Node* node,
633 const FunctionTemplateInfoRef function_template_info,
634 FastApiCallFunction c_function, Node* receiver, Node* holder,
635 const SharedFunctionInfoRef shared, Node* target, const int arity,
636 Node* effect)
637 : JSCallReducerAssembler(reducer, node),
638 c_function_(c_function),
639 function_template_info_(function_template_info),
640 receiver_(receiver),
641 holder_(holder),
642 shared_(shared),
643 target_(target),
644 arity_(arity) {
645 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSCall, node->opcode());
646 InitializeEffectControl(effect, NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node));
647 }
648
649 TNode<Object> ReduceFastApiCall() {
650 JSCallNode n(node_ptr());
651
652 // C arguments include the receiver at index 0. Thus C index 1 corresponds
653 // to the JS argument 0, etc.
654 // All functions in c_candidate_functions_ have the same number of
655 // arguments, so extract c_argument_count from the first function.
656 const int c_argument_count =
657 static_cast<int>(c_function_.signature->ArgumentCount());
658 CHECK_GE(c_argument_count, kReceiver);
659
660 const int slow_arg_count =
661 // Arguments for CallApiCallbackOptimizedXXX builtin including
662 // context, see CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor.
663 kSlowBuiltinParams +
664 // JS arguments.
665 kReceiver + arity_;
666
667 const int value_input_count =
668 FastApiCallNode::ArityForArgc(c_argument_count, slow_arg_count);
669
670 base::SmallVector<Node*, kInlineSize> inputs(value_input_count +
671 kEffectAndControl);
672 int cursor = 0;
673 inputs[cursor++] = n.receiver();
674
675 // TODO(turbofan): Consider refactoring CFunctionInfo to distinguish
676 // between receiver and arguments, simplifying this (and related) spots.
677 int js_args_count = c_argument_count - kReceiver;
678 for (int i = 0; i < js_args_count; ++i) {
679 if (i < n.ArgumentCount()) {
680 inputs[cursor++] = n.Argument(i);
681 } else {
682 inputs[cursor++] = UndefinedConstant();
683 }
684 }
685
686 // Here we add the arguments for the slow call, which will be
687 // reconstructed at a later phase. Those are effectively the same
688 // arguments as for the fast call, but we want to have them as
689 // separate inputs, so that SimplifiedLowering can provide the best
690 // possible UseInfos for each of them. The inputs to FastApiCall
691 // look like:
692 // [receiver, ... C arguments, callback data,
693 // slow call code, external constant for function, argc,
694 // FunctionTemplateInfo, holder, receiver, ... JS arguments,
695 // context, new frame state].
696 bool no_profiling =
697 broker()->dependencies()->DependOnNoProfilingProtector();
698 Callable call_api_callback = Builtins::CallableFor(
699 isolate(), no_profiling ? Builtin::kCallApiCallbackOptimizedNoProfiling
700 : Builtin::kCallApiCallbackOptimized);
701 CallInterfaceDescriptor cid = call_api_callback.descriptor();
702 DCHECK_EQ(cid.GetParameterCount() + (cid.HasContextParameter() ? 1 : 0),
703 kSlowBuiltinParams);
704
705 CallDescriptor* call_descriptor =
706 Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(graph()->zone(), cid, arity_ + kReceiver,
707 CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState);
708 ApiFunction api_function(function_template_info_.callback(broker()));
709 ExternalReference function_reference = ExternalReference::Create(
710 isolate(), &api_function, ExternalReference::DIRECT_API_CALL,
711 function_template_info_.c_functions(broker()).data(),
712 function_template_info_.c_signatures(broker()).data(),
713 static_cast<unsigned>(
714 function_template_info_.c_functions(broker()).size()));
715
716 Node* continuation_frame_state = CreateInlinedApiFunctionFrameState(
717 jsgraph(), shared_, target_, ContextInput(), receiver_,
718 FrameStateInput());
719
720 // Callback data value for fast Api calls. Unlike slow Api calls, the fast
721 // variant passes callback data directly.
722 inputs[cursor++] =
723 Constant(function_template_info_.callback_data(broker()).value());
724
725 inputs[cursor++] = HeapConstant(call_api_callback.code());
726 inputs[cursor++] = ExternalConstant(function_reference);
727 inputs[cursor++] = NumberConstant(arity_);
728 inputs[cursor++] = HeapConstant(function_template_info_.object());
729 inputs[cursor++] = holder_;
730 inputs[cursor++] = receiver_;
731 for (int i = 0; i < arity_; ++i) {
732 inputs[cursor++] = Argument(i);
733 }
734 inputs[cursor++] = ContextInput();
735 inputs[cursor++] = continuation_frame_state;
736
737 inputs[cursor++] = effect();
738 inputs[cursor++] = control();
739
740 DCHECK_EQ(cursor, value_input_count + kEffectAndControl);
741
742 return FastApiCall(call_descriptor, inputs.begin(), inputs.size());
743 }
744
745 private:
746 static constexpr int kEffectAndControl = 2;
747
748 // Api function address, argc, FunctionTemplateInfo, holder, context.
749 // See CallApiCallbackOptimizedDescriptor.
750 static constexpr int kSlowBuiltinParams = 5;
751 static constexpr int kReceiver = 1;
752
753 // Enough for creating FastApiCall node with two JS arguments.
754 static constexpr int kInlineSize = 16;
755
756 TNode<Object> FastApiCall(CallDescriptor* descriptor, Node** inputs,
757 size_t inputs_size) {
758 return AddNode<Object>(graph()->NewNode(
759 simplified()->FastApiCall(c_function_, feedback(), descriptor),
760 static_cast<int>(inputs_size), inputs));
761 }
762
763 FastApiCallFunction c_function_;
764 const FunctionTemplateInfoRef function_template_info_;
765 Node* const receiver_;
766 Node* const holder_;
767 const SharedFunctionInfoRef shared_;
768 Node* const target_;
769 const int arity_;
770};
771

819TNode<Object> JSCallReducerAssembler::Call4(
820 const Callable& callable, TNode<Context> context, TNode<Object> arg0,
821 TNode<Object> arg1, TNode<Object> arg2, TNode<Object> arg3) {
822 // TODO(jgruber): Make this more generic. Currently it's fitted to its single
823 // callsite.

825 graph()->zone(), callable.descriptor(),
826 callable.descriptor().GetStackParameterCount(), CallDescriptor::kNoFlags,
827 Operator::kEliminatable);
828
829 return TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(Call(desc, HeapConstant(callable.code()),
830 arg0, arg1, arg2, arg3, context));
831}

835 TNode<Object> arg1, TNode<Object> arg2, FrameState frame_state) {
836 JSCallNode n(node_ptr());

839 return AddNode<Object>(graph()->NewNode(
840 javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(3), p.frequency(),
841 p.feedback(), ConvertReceiverMode::kAny,
842 p.speculation_mode(),
843 CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated),
844 function, this_arg, arg0, arg1, arg2, n.feedback_vector(),
845 ContextInput(), frame_state, effect(), control()));
846 });
847}

867 return MayThrow(_ {
868 Node* copy = graph()->CloneNode(node_ptr());
869 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(copy, effect());
870 NodeProperties::ReplaceControlInput(copy, control());
871 return AddNode<Object>(copy);
872 });

881
882TNode<JSArray> JSCallReducerAssembler::AllocateEmptyJSArray(
883 ElementsKind kind, NativeContextRef native_context) {
884 // TODO(jgruber): Port AllocationBuilder to JSGraphAssembler.
885 MapRef map = native_context.GetInitialJSArrayMap(broker(), kind);
886
887 AllocationBuilder ab(jsgraph(), broker(), effect(), control());
888 ab.Allocate(map.instance_size(), AllocationType::kYoung, Type::Array());
889 ab.Store(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), map);
890 Node* empty_fixed_array = jsgraph()->EmptyFixedArrayConstant();
891 ab.Store(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectPropertiesOrHashKnownPointer(),
892 empty_fixed_array);
893 ab.Store(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements(), empty_fixed_array);
894 ab.Store(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(kind), jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
895 for (int i = 0; i < map.GetInObjectProperties(); ++i) {
896 ab.Store(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectInObjectProperty(map, i),
897 jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
898 }
899 Node* result = ab.Finish();
900 InitializeEffectControl(result, control());
901 return TNode<JSArray>::UncheckedCast(result);
902}
903
904TNode<Number> JSCallReducerAssembler::LoadMapElementsKind(TNode<Map> map) {
905 TNode<Number> bit_field2 =
906 LoadField<Number>(AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField2(), map);
907 return NumberShiftRightLogical(
908 NumberBitwiseAnd(bit_field2,
909 NumberConstant(Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kMask)),
910 NumberConstant(Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kShift));
911}

913TNode<Object> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceMathUnary(const Operator* op) {
914 TNode<Object> input = Argument(0);
915 TNode<Number> input_as_number = SpeculativeToNumber(input);
916 return TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(graph()->NewNode(op, input_as_number));
917}
918
919TNode<Object> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceMathBinary(const Operator* op) {
920 TNode<Object> left = Argument(0);
921 TNode<Object> right = ArgumentOrNaN(1);
922 TNode<Number> left_number = SpeculativeToNumber(left);
923 TNode<Number> right_number = SpeculativeToNumber(right);
924 return TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(
925 graph()->NewNode(op, left_number, right_number));
926}

928TNode<String> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceStringPrototypeSubstring() {
929 TNode<Object> receiver = ReceiverInput();
930 TNode<Object> start = Argument(0);
931 TNode<Object> end = ArgumentOrUndefined(1);
932
933 TNode<String> receiver_string = CheckString(receiver);
934 TNode<Number> start_smi = CheckSmi(start);
935
936 TNode<Number> length = StringLength(receiver_string);
937
938 TNode<Number> end_smi = SelectIf<Number>(IsUndefined(end))
939 .Then(_ { return length; })
940 .Else(_ { return CheckSmi(end); })
941 .ExpectFalse()
942 .Value();
943
944 TNode<Number> zero = TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(ZeroConstant());
945 TNode<Number> finalStart = NumberMin(NumberMax(start_smi, zero), length);
946 TNode<Number> finalEnd = NumberMin(NumberMax(end_smi, zero), length);
947 TNode<Number> from = NumberMin(finalStart, finalEnd);
948 TNode<Number> to = NumberMax(finalStart, finalEnd);
949
950 return StringSubstring(receiver_string, from, to);
951}
952
953TNode<Boolean> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceStringPrototypeStartsWith(
954 StringRef search_element_string) {
955 DCHECK(search_element_string.IsContentAccessible());
956 TNode<Object> receiver = ReceiverInput();
957 TNode<Object> start = ArgumentOrZero(1);
958
959 TNode<String> receiver_string = CheckString(receiver);
960 TNode<Smi> start_smi = CheckSmi(start);
961 TNode<Number> length = StringLength(receiver_string);
962
963 TNode<Number> zero = ZeroConstant();
964 TNode<Number> clamped_start = NumberMin(NumberMax(start_smi, zero), length);
965
966 int search_string_length = search_element_string.length();
967 DCHECK(search_string_length <= JSCallReducer::kMaxInlineMatchSequence);
968
969 auto out = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
970
971 auto search_string_too_long =
972 NumberLessThan(NumberSubtract(length, clamped_start),
973 NumberConstant(search_string_length));
974
975 GotoIf(search_string_too_long, &out, BranchHint::kFalse, FalseConstant());
976
977 static_assert(String::kMaxLength <= kSmiMaxValue);
978
979 for (int i = 0; i < search_string_length; i++) {
980 TNode<Number> k = NumberConstant(i);
981 TNode<Number> receiver_string_position = TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(
982 TypeGuard(Type::UnsignedSmall(), NumberAdd(k, clamped_start)));
983 Node* receiver_string_char =
984 StringCharCodeAt(receiver_string, receiver_string_position);
985 Node* search_string_char = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
986 search_element_string.GetChar(broker(), i).value());
987 auto is_equal = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(),
988 search_string_char, receiver_string_char);
989 GotoIfNot(is_equal, &out, FalseConstant());
990 }
991
992 Goto(&out, TrueConstant());
993
994 Bind(&out);
995 return out.PhiAt<Boolean>(0);
996}
997
998TNode<Boolean> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceStringPrototypeStartsWith() {
999 TNode<Object> receiver = ReceiverInput();
1000 TNode<Object> search_element = ArgumentOrUndefined(0);
1001 TNode<Object> start = ArgumentOrZero(1);
1002
1003 TNode<String> receiver_string = CheckString(receiver);
1004 TNode<String> search_string = CheckString(search_element);
1005 TNode<Smi> start_smi = CheckSmi(start);
1006 TNode<Number> length = StringLength(receiver_string);
1007
1008 TNode<Number> zero = ZeroConstant();
1009 TNode<Number> clamped_start = NumberMin(NumberMax(start_smi, zero), length);
1010
1011 TNode<Number> search_string_length = StringLength(search_string);
1012
1013 auto out = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1014
1015 auto search_string_too_long = NumberLessThan(
1016 NumberSubtract(length, clamped_start), search_string_length);
1017
1018 GotoIf(search_string_too_long, &out, BranchHint::kFalse, FalseConstant());
1019
1020 static_assert(String::kMaxLength <= kSmiMaxValue);
1021
1022 ForZeroUntil(search_string_length).Do([&](TNode<Number> k) {
1023 TNode<Number> receiver_string_position = TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(
1024 TypeGuard(Type::UnsignedSmall(), NumberAdd(k, clamped_start)));
1025 Node* receiver_string_char =
1026 StringCharCodeAt(receiver_string, receiver_string_position);
1027 if (!v8_flags.turbo_loop_variable) {
1028 // Without loop variable analysis, Turbofan's typer is unable to derive a
1029 // sufficiently precise type here. This is not a soundness problem, but
1030 // triggers graph verification errors. So we only insert the TypeGuard if
1031 // necessary.
1032 k = TypeGuard(Type::Unsigned32(), k);
1033 }
1034 Node* search_string_char = StringCharCodeAt(search_string, k);
1035 auto is_equal = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(),
1036 receiver_string_char, search_string_char);
1037 GotoIfNot(is_equal, &out, FalseConstant());
1038 });
1039
1040 Goto(&out, TrueConstant());
1041
1042 Bind(&out);
1043 return out.PhiAt<Boolean>(0);
1044}
1045
1046TNode<Boolean> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceStringPrototypeEndsWith(
1047 StringRef search_element_string) {
1048 DCHECK(search_element_string.IsContentAccessible());
1049 TNode<Object> receiver = ReceiverInput();
1050 TNode<Object> end_position = ArgumentOrUndefined(1);
1051 TNode<Number> zero = ZeroConstant();
1052
1053 TNode<String> receiver_string = CheckString(receiver);
1054 TNode<Number> length = StringLength(receiver_string);
1055 int search_string_length = search_element_string.length();
1056 DCHECK_LE(search_string_length, JSCallReducer::kMaxInlineMatchSequence);
1057
1058 TNode<Number> clamped_end =
1059 SelectIf<Number>(IsUndefined(end_position))
1060 .Then(_ { return length; })
1061 .Else(_ {
1062 return NumberMin(NumberMax(CheckSmi(end_position), zero), length);
1063 })
1064 .ExpectTrue()
1065 .Value();
1066
1067 TNode<Number> start =
1068 NumberSubtract(clamped_end, NumberConstant(search_string_length));
1069
1070 auto out = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1071
1072 TNode<Boolean> search_string_too_long = NumberLessThan(start, zero);
1073 GotoIf(search_string_too_long, &out, BranchHint::kFalse, FalseConstant());
1074
1075 for (int i = 0; i < search_string_length; i++) {
1076 TNode<Number> k = NumberConstant(i);
1077 TNode<Number> receiver_string_position = TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(
1078 TypeGuard(Type::UnsignedSmall(), NumberAdd(k, start)));
1079 Node* receiver_string_char =
1080 StringCharCodeAt(receiver_string, receiver_string_position);
1081 Node* search_string_char = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
1082 search_element_string.GetChar(broker(), i).value());
1083 auto is_equal = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(),
1084 receiver_string_char, search_string_char);
1085 GotoIfNot(is_equal, &out, FalseConstant());
1086 }
1087
1088 Goto(&out, TrueConstant());
1089
1090 Bind(&out);
1091 return out.PhiAt<Boolean>(0);
1092}
1093
1094TNode<Boolean> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceStringPrototypeEndsWith() {
1095 TNode<Object> receiver = ReceiverInput();
1096 TNode<Object> search_string = ArgumentOrUndefined(0);
1097 TNode<Object> end_position = ArgumentOrUndefined(1);
1098 TNode<Number> zero = ZeroConstant();
1099
1100 TNode<String> receiver_string = CheckString(receiver);
1101 TNode<Number> length = StringLength(receiver_string);
1102 TNode<String> search_element_string = CheckString(search_string);
1103 TNode<Number> search_string_length = StringLength(search_element_string);
1104
1105 TNode<Number> clamped_end =
1106 SelectIf<Number>(IsUndefined(end_position))
1107 .Then(_ { return length; })
1108 .Else(_ {
1109 return NumberMin(NumberMax(CheckSmi(end_position), zero), length);
1110 })
1111 .ExpectTrue()
1112 .Value();
1113
1114 TNode<Number> start = NumberSubtract(clamped_end, search_string_length);
1115
1116 auto out = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1117
1118 TNode<Boolean> search_string_too_long = NumberLessThan(start, zero);
1119 GotoIf(search_string_too_long, &out, BranchHint::kFalse, FalseConstant());
1120
1121 ForZeroUntil(search_string_length).Do([&](TNode<Number> k) {
1122 TNode<Number> receiver_string_position = TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(
1123 TypeGuard(Type::UnsignedSmall(), NumberAdd(k, start)));
1124 Node* receiver_string_char =
1125 StringCharCodeAt(receiver_string, receiver_string_position);
1126 if (!v8_flags.turbo_loop_variable) {
1127 // Without loop variable analysis, Turbofan's typer is unable to derive a
1128 // sufficiently precise type here. This is not a soundness problem, but
1129 // triggers graph verification errors. So we only insert the TypeGuard if
1130 // necessary.
1131 k = TypeGuard(Type::Unsigned32(), k);
1132 }
1133 Node* search_string_char = StringCharCodeAt(search_element_string, k);
1134 auto is_equal = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(),
1135 receiver_string_char, search_string_char);
1136 GotoIfNot(is_equal, &out, FalseConstant());
1137 });
1138
1139 Goto(&out, TrueConstant());
1140
1141 Bind(&out);
1142 return out.PhiAt<Boolean>(0);
1143}
1144
1145TNode<String> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceStringPrototypeCharAt(
1146 StringRef s, uint32_t index) {
1147 DCHECK(s.IsContentAccessible());
1148 if (s.IsOneByteRepresentation()) {
1149 OptionalObjectRef elem = s.GetCharAsStringOrUndefined(broker(), index);
1150 TNode<String> elem_string =
1151 elem.has_value()
1152 ? TNode<String>::UncheckedCast(
1153 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(elem.value(), broker()))
1154 : EmptyStringConstant();
1155 return elem_string;
1156 } else {
1157 const uint32_t length = static_cast<uint32_t>(s.length());
1158 if (index >= length) return EmptyStringConstant();
1159 Handle<SeqTwoByteString> flat = broker()->CanonicalPersistentHandle(
1160 broker()
1161 ->local_isolate_or_isolate()
1162 ->factory()
1163 ->NewRawTwoByteString(1, AllocationType::kOld)
1164 .ToHandleChecked());
1165 flat->SeqTwoByteStringSet(0, s.GetChar(broker(), index).value());
1166 TNode<String> two_byte_elem =
1167 TNode<String>::UncheckedCast(jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(flat));
1168 return two_byte_elem;
1169 }
1170}
1171
1172TNode<String> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceStringPrototypeCharAt() {
1173 TNode<Object> receiver = ReceiverInput();
1174 TNode<Object> index = ArgumentOrZero(0);
1175
1176 TNode<String> receiver_string = CheckString(receiver);
1177 TNode<Number> index_smi = CheckSmi(index);
1178 TNode<Number> length = StringLength(receiver_string);
1179
1180 TNode<Number> bounded_index = CheckBounds(index_smi, length);
1181
1182 Node* result = StringCharCodeAt(receiver_string, bounded_index);
1183 TNode<String> result_string =
1184 StringFromSingleCharCode(TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(result));
1185 return result_string;
1186}
1187
1188TNode<String> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceStringPrototypeSlice() {
1189 TNode<Object> receiver = ReceiverInput();
1190 TNode<Object> start = Argument(0);
1191 TNode<Object> end = ArgumentOrUndefined(1);
1192
1193 TNode<String> receiver_string = CheckString(receiver);
1194 TNode<Number> start_smi = CheckSmi(start);
1195
1196 TNode<Number> length = StringLength(receiver_string);
1197
1198 TNode<Number> end_smi = SelectIf<Number>(IsUndefined(end))
1199 .Then(_ { return length; })
1200 .Else(_ { return CheckSmi(end); })
1201 .ExpectFalse()
1202 .Value();
1203
1204 TNode<Number> zero = TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(ZeroConstant());
1205 TNode<Number> from_untyped =
1206 SelectIf<Number>(NumberLessThan(start_smi, zero))
1207 .Then(_ { return NumberMax(NumberAdd(length, start_smi), zero); })
1208 .Else(_ { return NumberMin(start_smi, length); })
1209 .ExpectFalse()
1210 .Value();
1211 // {from} is always in non-negative Smi range, but our typer cannot figure
1212 // that out yet.
1213 TNode<Smi> from = TypeGuardUnsignedSmall(from_untyped);
1214
1215 TNode<Number> to_untyped =
1216 SelectIf<Number>(NumberLessThan(end_smi, zero))
1217 .Then(_ { return NumberMax(NumberAdd(length, end_smi), zero); })
1218 .Else(_ { return NumberMin(end_smi, length); })
1219 .ExpectFalse()
1220 .Value();
1221 // {to} is always in non-negative Smi range, but our typer cannot figure that
1222 // out yet.
1223 TNode<Smi> to = TypeGuardUnsignedSmall(to_untyped);
1224
1225 return SelectIf<String>(NumberLessThan(from, to))
1226 .Then(_ { return StringSubstring(receiver_string, from, to); })
1227 .Else(_ { return EmptyStringConstant(); })
1228 .ExpectTrue()
1229 .Value();
1230}
1231
1232TNode<Object> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceJSCallMathMinMaxWithArrayLike(
1233 Builtin builtin) {
1234 JSCallWithArrayLikeNode n(node_ptr());
1235 TNode<Object> arguments_list = n.Argument(0);
1236
1237 auto call_builtin = MakeLabel();
1238 auto done = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1239
1240 // Check if {arguments_list} is a JSArray.
1241 GotoIf(ObjectIsSmi(arguments_list), &call_builtin);
1242 TNode<Map> arguments_list_map =
1243 LoadField<Map>(AccessBuilder::ForMap(),
1244 TNode<HeapObject>::UncheckedCast(arguments_list));
1245 TNode<Number> arguments_list_instance_type = LoadField<Number>(
1246 AccessBuilder::ForMapInstanceType(), arguments_list_map);
1247 auto check_instance_type =
1248 NumberEqual(arguments_list_instance_type, NumberConstant(JS_ARRAY_TYPE));
1249 GotoIfNot(check_instance_type, &call_builtin);
1250
1251 // Check if {arguments_list} has PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS.
1252 TNode<Number> arguments_list_elements_kind =
1253 LoadMapElementsKind(arguments_list_map);
1254
1255 auto check_element_kind = NumberEqual(arguments_list_elements_kind,
1256 NumberConstant(PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS));
1257 GotoIfNot(check_element_kind, &call_builtin);
1258
1259 // If {arguments_list} is a JSArray with PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS, calculate the
1260 // result with inlined loop.
1261 TNode<JSArray> array_arguments_list =
1262 TNode<JSArray>::UncheckedCast(arguments_list);
1263 Goto(&done, builtin == Builtin::kMathMax
1264 ? DoubleArrayMax(array_arguments_list)
1265 : DoubleArrayMin(array_arguments_list));
1266
1267 // Otherwise, call BuiltinMathMin/Max as usual.
1268 Bind(&call_builtin);
1269 TNode<Object> call = CopyNode();
1270 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
1271
1272 // Set SpeculationMode to kDisallowSpeculation to avoid infinite
1273 // recursion.
1274 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
1275 call, javascript()->CallWithArrayLike(
1276 p.frequency(), p.feedback(),
1277 SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation, p.feedback_relation()));
1278 Goto(&done, call);
1279
1280 Bind(&done);
1281 return done.PhiAt<Object>(0);
1282}
1283
1284TNode<Object> IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReduceArrayPrototypeAt(
1285 ZoneVector<MapRef> maps, bool needs_fallback_builtin_call) {
1286 TNode<JSArray> receiver = ReceiverInputAs<JSArray>();
1287 TNode<Object> index = ArgumentOrZero(0);
1288
1289 TNode<Number> index_num = CheckSmi(index);
1290 TNode<FixedArrayBase> elements = LoadElements(receiver);
1291
1292 TNode<Map> receiver_map =
1293 TNode<Map>::UncheckedCast(LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), receiver));
1294
1295 auto out = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1296
1297 for (MapRef map : maps) {
1298 DCHECK(map.supports_fast_array_iteration(broker()));
1299 auto correct_map_label = MakeLabel(), wrong_map_label = MakeLabel();
1300 TNode<Boolean> is_map_equal = ReferenceEqual(receiver_map, Constant(map));
1301 Branch(is_map_equal, &correct_map_label, &wrong_map_label);
1302 Bind(&correct_map_label);
1303
1304 TNode<Number> length = LoadJSArrayLength(receiver, map.elements_kind());
1305
1306 // If index is less than 0, then subtract from length.
1307 TNode<Boolean> cond = NumberLessThan(index_num, ZeroConstant());
1308 TNode<Number> real_index_num =
1309 SelectIf<Number>(cond)
1310 .Then(_ { return NumberAdd(length, index_num); })
1311 .Else(_ { return index_num; })
1312 .ExpectTrue() // Most common usage should be .at(-1)
1313 .Value();
1314
1315 // Bound checking.
1316 GotoIf(NumberLessThan(real_index_num, ZeroConstant()), &out,
1317 UndefinedConstant());
1318 GotoIfNot(NumberLessThan(real_index_num, length), &out,
1319 UndefinedConstant());
1320 if (v8_flags.turbo_typer_hardening) {
1321 real_index_num = CheckBounds(real_index_num, length,
1322 CheckBoundsFlag::kAbortOnOutOfBounds);
1323 }
1324
1325 // Retrieving element at index.
1326 TNode<Object> element = LoadElement<Object>(
1327 AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(map.elements_kind()), elements,
1328 real_index_num);
1329 if (IsHoleyElementsKind(map.elements_kind())) {
1330 // This case is needed in particular for HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS: raw
1331 // doubles are stored in the FixedDoubleArray, and need to be converted to
1332 // HeapNumber or to Smi so that this function can return an Object. The
1333 // automatic converstion performed by
1334 // RepresentationChanger::GetTaggedRepresentationFor does not handle
1335 // holes, so we convert manually a potential hole here.
1336 element = ConvertHoleToUndefined(element, map.elements_kind());
1337 }
1338 Goto(&out, element);
1339
1340 Bind(&wrong_map_label);
1341 }
1342
1343 if (needs_fallback_builtin_call) {
1344 JSCallNode n(node_ptr());
1345 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
1346
1347 // We set SpeculationMode to kDisallowSpeculation to avoid infinite
1348 // recursion on the node we're creating (since, after all, it's calling
1349 // Array.Prototype.at).
1350 const Operator* op = javascript()->Call(
1351 JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(1), p.frequency(), p.feedback(),
1352 ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined,
1353 SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation, CallFeedbackRelation::kTarget);
1354 Node* fallback_builtin = node_ptr()->InputAt(0);
1355
1356 TNode<Object> res = AddNode<Object>(graph()->NewNode(
1357 op, fallback_builtin, receiver, index, n.feedback_vector(),
1358 ContextInput(), n.frame_state(), effect(), control()));
1359 Goto(&out, res);
1360 } else {
1361 Goto(&out, UndefinedConstant());
1362 }
1363
1364 Bind(&out);
1365 return out.PhiAt<Object>(0);
1366}
1367
1368TNode<Number> IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReduceArrayPrototypePush(
1369 MapInference* inference) {
1370 int const num_push_arguments = ArgumentCount();
1371 ZoneRefSet<Map> const& receiver_maps = inference->GetMaps();
1372
1373 base::SmallVector<MachineRepresentation, 4> argument_reps;
1374 base::SmallVector<Node*, 4> argument_nodes;
1375
1376 for (int i = 0; i < num_push_arguments; ++i) {
1377 argument_reps.push_back(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1378 argument_nodes.push_back(Argument(i));
1379 }
1380
1381 TNode<JSArray> receiver = ReceiverInputAs<JSArray>();
1382 TNode<Map> receiver_map = LoadMap(receiver);
1383
1384 auto double_label = MakeLabel(argument_reps);
1385 auto smi_label = MakeLabel(argument_reps);
1386 auto object_label = MakeLabel(argument_reps);
1387
1388 for (size_t i = 0; i < receiver_maps.size(); i++) {
1389 MapRef map = receiver_maps[i];
1390 ElementsKind kind = map.elements_kind();
1391
1392 if (i < receiver_maps.size() - 1) {
1393 TNode<Boolean> is_map_equal = ReferenceEqual(receiver_map, Constant(map));
1394 if (IsDoubleElementsKind(kind)) {
1395 GotoIf(is_map_equal, &double_label, argument_nodes);
1396 } else if (IsSmiElementsKind(kind)) {
1397 GotoIf(is_map_equal, &smi_label, argument_nodes);
1398 } else {
1399 GotoIf(is_map_equal, &object_label, argument_nodes);
1400 }
1401 } else {
1402 if (IsDoubleElementsKind(kind)) {
1403 Goto(&double_label, argument_nodes);
1404 } else if (IsSmiElementsKind(kind)) {
1405 Goto(&smi_label, argument_nodes);
1406 } else {
1407 Goto(&object_label, argument_nodes);
1408 }
1409 }
1410 }
1411
1412 auto return_label = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1413
1414 auto build_array_push = [&](ElementsKind kind,
1415 base::SmallVector<Node*, 1>& push_arguments) {
1416 // Only support PACKED_ELEMENTS and PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS, as "markers" of
1417 // what the elements array is (a FixedArray or FixedDoubleArray).
1418 DCHECK(kind == PACKED_ELEMENTS || kind == PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS);
1419
1420 // Load the "length" property of the {receiver}.
1421 TNode<Smi> length = LoadJSArrayLength(receiver, kind);
1422 TNode<Number> return_value = length;
1423
1424 // Check if we have any {values} to push.
1425 if (num_push_arguments > 0) {
1426 // Compute the resulting "length" of the {receiver}.
1427 TNode<Number> new_length = return_value =
1428 NumberAdd(length, NumberConstant(num_push_arguments));
1429
1430 // Load the elements backing store of the {receiver}.
1431 TNode<FixedArrayBase> elements = LoadElements(receiver);
1432 TNode<Smi> elements_length = LoadFixedArrayBaseLength(elements);
1433
1434 elements = MaybeGrowFastElements(
1435 kind, feedback(), receiver, elements,
1436 NumberAdd(length, NumberConstant(num_push_arguments - 1)),
1437 elements_length);
1438
1439 // Update the JSArray::length field. Since this is observable,
1440 // there must be no other check after this.
1441 StoreJSArrayLength(receiver, new_length, kind);
1442
1443 // Append the {values} to the {elements}.
1444 for (int i = 0; i < num_push_arguments; ++i) {
1445 StoreFixedArrayBaseElement(
1446 elements, NumberAdd(length, NumberConstant(i)),
1447 TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(push_arguments[i]), kind);
1448 }
1449 }
1450
1451 Goto(&return_label, return_value);
1452 };
1453
1454 if (double_label.IsUsed()) {
1455 Bind(&double_label);
1456 base::SmallVector<Node*, 1> push_arguments(num_push_arguments);
1457 for (int i = 0; i < num_push_arguments; ++i) {
1458 Node* value =
1459 CheckNumber(TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(double_label.PhiAt(i)));
1460 // Make sure we do not store signaling NaNs into double arrays.
1461 value = AddNode<Number>(
1462 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberSilenceNaN(), value));
1463 push_arguments[i] = value;
1464 }
1465 build_array_push(PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS, push_arguments);
1466 }
1467
1468 if (smi_label.IsUsed()) {
1469 Bind(&smi_label);
1470 base::SmallVector<Node*, 4> push_arguments(num_push_arguments);
1471 for (int i = 0; i < num_push_arguments; ++i) {
1472 Node* value = CheckSmi(TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(smi_label.PhiAt(i)));
1473 push_arguments[i] = value;
1474 }
1475 Goto(&object_label, push_arguments);
1476 }
1477
1478 if (object_label.IsUsed()) {
1479 Bind(&object_label);
1480 base::SmallVector<Node*, 1> push_arguments(num_push_arguments);
1481 for (int i = 0; i < num_push_arguments; ++i) {
1482 push_arguments[i] = object_label.PhiAt(i);
1483 }
1484 build_array_push(PACKED_ELEMENTS, push_arguments);
1485 }
1486
1487 Bind(&return_label);
1488 return TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(return_label.PhiAt(0));
1489}

1493struct ForEachFrameStateParams {
1494 JSGraph* jsgraph;
1495 SharedFunctionInfoRef shared;
1496 TNode<Context> context;
1497 TNode<Object> target;
1498 FrameState outer_frame_state;
1499 TNode<Object> receiver;
1500 TNode<Object> callback;
1501 TNode<Object> this_arg;
1502 TNode<Object> original_length;
1503};
1504
1505FrameState ForEachLoopLazyFrameState(const ForEachFrameStateParams& params,
1506 TNode<Object> k) {
1507 Builtin builtin = Builtin::kArrayForEachLoopLazyDeoptContinuation;
1508 Node* checkpoint_params[] = {params.receiver, params.callback,
1509 params.this_arg, k, params.original_length};
1510 return CreateJavaScriptBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
1511 params.jsgraph, params.shared, builtin, params.target, params.context,
1512 checkpoint_params, arraysize(checkpoint_params), params.outer_frame_state,
1513 ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY);
1514}
1515
1516FrameState ForEachLoopEagerFrameState(const ForEachFrameStateParams& params,
1517 TNode<Object> k) {
1518 Builtin builtin = Builtin::kArrayForEachLoopEagerDeoptContinuation;
1519 Node* checkpoint_params[] = {params.receiver, params.callback,
1520 params.this_arg, k, params.original_length};
1521 return CreateJavaScriptBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
1522 params.jsgraph, params.shared, builtin, params.target, params.context,
1523 checkpoint_params, arraysize(checkpoint_params), params.outer_frame_state,
1524 ContinuationFrameStateMode::EAGER);
1525}

1528
1529TNode<Object>
1530IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReduceArrayPrototypeForEach(
1531 MapInference* inference, const bool has_stability_dependency,
1532 ElementsKind kind, SharedFunctionInfoRef shared) {
1533 FrameState outer_frame_state = FrameStateInput();
1534 TNode<Context> context = ContextInput();
1535 TNode<Object> target = TargetInput();
1536 TNode<JSArray> receiver = ReceiverInputAs<JSArray>();
1537 TNode<Object> fncallback = ArgumentOrUndefined(0);
1538 TNode<Object> this_arg = ArgumentOrUndefined(1);
1539
1540 TNode<Number> original_length = LoadJSArrayLength(receiver, kind);
1541
1542 ForEachFrameStateParams frame_state_params{
1543 jsgraph(), shared, context, target, outer_frame_state,
1544 receiver, fncallback, this_arg, original_length};
1545
1546 ThrowIfNotCallable(fncallback, ForEachLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params,
1547 ZeroConstant()));
1548
1549 ForZeroUntil(original_length).Do([&](TNode<Number> k) {
1550 Checkpoint(ForEachLoopEagerFrameState(frame_state_params, k));
1551
1552 // Deopt if the map has changed during the iteration.
1553 MaybeInsertMapChecks(inference, has_stability_dependency);
1554
1555 TNode<Object> element;
1556 std::tie(k, element) = SafeLoadElement(kind, receiver, k);
1557
1558 auto continue_label = MakeLabel();
1559 element = MaybeSkipHole(element, kind, &continue_label);
1560
1561 TNode<Number> next_k = NumberAdd(k, OneConstant());
1562 JSCall3(fncallback, this_arg, element, k, receiver,
1563 ForEachLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, next_k));
1564
1565 Goto(&continue_label);
1566 Bind(&continue_label);
1567 });
1568
1569 return UndefinedConstant();
1570}

1604 : Builtin::kArrayReduceRightPreLoopEagerDeoptContinuation;

1607 params.jsgraph, params.shared, builtin, params.target, params.context,

1618 : Builtin::kArrayReduceRightLoopLazyDeoptContinuation;

1643
1644TNode<Object> IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReduceArrayPrototypeReduce(
1645 MapInference* inference, const bool has_stability_dependency,
1646 ElementsKind kind, ArrayReduceDirection direction,
1647 SharedFunctionInfoRef shared) {
1648 FrameState outer_frame_state = FrameStateInput();
1649 TNode<Context> context = ContextInput();
1650 TNode<Object> target = TargetInput();
1651 TNode<JSArray> receiver = ReceiverInputAs<JSArray>();
1652 TNode<Object> fncallback = ArgumentOrUndefined(0);
1653
1654 ReduceFrameStateParams frame_state_params{
1655 jsgraph(), shared, direction, context, target, outer_frame_state};
1656
1657 TNode<Number> original_length = LoadJSArrayLength(receiver, kind);
1658
1659 // Set up variable behavior depending on the reduction kind (left/right).
1660 TNode<Number> k;
1661 StepFunction1 step;
1662 ConditionFunction1 cond;
1663 TNode<Number> zero = ZeroConstant();
1664 TNode<Number> one = OneConstant();
1665 if (direction == ArrayReduceDirection::kLeft) {
1666 k = zero;
1667 step = [&](TNode<Number> i) { return NumberAdd(i, one); };
1668 cond = [&](TNode<Number> i) { return NumberLessThan(i, original_length); };
1669 } else {
1670 k = NumberSubtract(original_length, one);
1671 step = [&](TNode<Number> i) { return NumberSubtract(i, one); };
1672 cond = [&](TNode<Number> i) { return NumberLessThanOrEqual(zero, i); };
1673 }
1674
1675 ThrowIfNotCallable(
1676 fncallback, ReducePreLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, receiver,
1677 fncallback, k, original_length));
1678
1679 // Set initial accumulator value.
1680 TNode<Object> accumulator;
1681 if (ArgumentCount() > 1) {
1682 accumulator = Argument(1); // Initial value specified by the user.
1683 } else {
1684 // The initial value was not specified by the user. In this case, the first
1685 // (or last in the case of reduceRight) non-holey value of the array is
1686 // used. Loop until we find it. If not found, trigger a deopt.
1687 // TODO(jgruber): The deopt does not seem necessary. Instead we could simply
1688 // throw the TypeError here from optimized code.
1689 auto found_initial_element = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged,
1690 MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1691 Forever(k, step).Do([&](TNode<Number> k) {
1692 Checkpoint(ReducePreLoopEagerFrameState(frame_state_params, receiver,
1693 fncallback, original_length));
1694 CheckIf(cond(k), DeoptimizeReason::kNoInitialElement);
1695
1696 TNode<Object> element;
1697 std::tie(k, element) = SafeLoadElement(kind, receiver, k);
1698
1699 auto continue_label = MakeLabel();
1700 GotoIf(HoleCheck(kind, element), &continue_label);
1701 Goto(&found_initial_element, k, TypeGuardNonInternal(element));
1702
1703 Bind(&continue_label);
1704 });
1705 Unreachable(); // The loop is exited either by deopt or a jump to below.
1706
1707 // TODO(jgruber): This manual fiddling with blocks could be avoided by
1708 // implementing a `break` mechanic for loop builders.
1709 Bind(&found_initial_element);
1710 k = step(found_initial_element.PhiAt<Number>(0));
1711 accumulator = found_initial_element.PhiAt<Object>(1);
1712 }
1713
1714 TNode<Object> result =
1715 For1(k, cond, step, accumulator)
1716 .Do([&](TNode<Number> k, TNode<Object>* accumulator) {
1717 Checkpoint(ReduceLoopEagerFrameState(frame_state_params, receiver,
1718 fncallback, k, original_length,
1719 *accumulator));
1720
1721 // Deopt if the map has changed during the iteration.
1722 MaybeInsertMapChecks(inference, has_stability_dependency);
1723
1724 TNode<Object> element;
1725 std::tie(k, element) = SafeLoadElement(kind, receiver, k);
1726
1727 auto continue_label = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1728 element =
1729 MaybeSkipHole(element, kind, &continue_label, *accumulator);
1730
1731 TNode<Number> next_k = step(k);
1732 TNode<Object> next_accumulator = JSCall4(
1733 fncallback, UndefinedConstant(), *accumulator, element, k,
1734 receiver,
1735 ReduceLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, receiver,
1736 fncallback, next_k, original_length));
1737 Goto(&continue_label, next_accumulator);
1738
1739 Bind(&continue_label);
1740 *accumulator = continue_label.PhiAt<Object>(0);
1741 })
1742 .Value();
1743
1744 return result;
1745}
1746

1798
1799TNode<JSArray> IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReduceArrayPrototypeMap(
1800 MapInference* inference, const bool has_stability_dependency,
1801 ElementsKind kind, SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
1802 NativeContextRef native_context) {
1803 FrameState outer_frame_state = FrameStateInput();
1804 TNode<Context> context = ContextInput();
1805 TNode<Object> target = TargetInput();
1806 TNode<JSArray> receiver = ReceiverInputAs<JSArray>();
1807 TNode<Object> fncallback = ArgumentOrUndefined(0);
1808 TNode<Object> this_arg = ArgumentOrUndefined(1);
1809
1810 TNode<Number> original_length = LoadJSArrayLength(receiver, kind);
1811
1812 // If the array length >= kMaxFastArrayLength, then CreateArray
1813 // will create a dictionary. We should deopt in this case, and make sure
1814 // not to attempt inlining again.
1815 original_length = CheckBounds(original_length,
1816 NumberConstant(JSArray::kMaxFastArrayLength));
1817
1818 // Even though {JSCreateArray} is not marked as {kNoThrow}, we can elide the
1819 // exceptional projections because it cannot throw with the given
1820 // parameters.
1821 TNode<Object> array_ctor =
1822 Constant(native_context.GetInitialJSArrayMap(broker(), kind)
1823 .GetConstructor(broker()));
1824
1825 MapFrameStateParams frame_state_params{
1826 jsgraph(), shared, context, target, outer_frame_state,
1827 receiver, fncallback, this_arg, {} /* TBD */, original_length};
1828
1829 TNode<JSArray> a =
1830 CreateArrayNoThrow(array_ctor, original_length,
1831 MapPreLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params));
1832 frame_state_params.a = a;
1833
1834 ThrowIfNotCallable(fncallback,
1835 MapLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, ZeroConstant()));
1836
1837 ForZeroUntil(original_length).Do([&](TNode<Number> k) {
1838 Checkpoint(MapLoopEagerFrameState(frame_state_params, k));
1839 MaybeInsertMapChecks(inference, has_stability_dependency);
1840
1841 TNode<Object> element;
1842 std::tie(k, element) = SafeLoadElement(kind, receiver, k);
1843
1844 auto continue_label = MakeLabel();
1845 element = MaybeSkipHole(element, kind, &continue_label);
1846
1847 TNode<Object> v = JSCall3(fncallback, this_arg, element, k, receiver,
1848 MapLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, k));
1849
1850 // The array {a} should be HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS because we'd only come into
1851 // this loop if the input array length is non-zero, and "new Array({x > 0})"
1852 // always produces a HOLEY array.
1853 MapRef holey_double_map =
1854 native_context.GetInitialJSArrayMap(broker(), HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS);
1855 MapRef holey_map =
1856 native_context.GetInitialJSArrayMap(broker(), HOLEY_ELEMENTS);
1857 TransitionAndStoreElement(holey_double_map, holey_map, a, k, v);
1858
1859 Goto(&continue_label);
1860 Bind(&continue_label);
1861 });
1862
1863 return a;
1864}

1939
1940TNode<JSArray>
1941IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReduceArrayPrototypeFilter(
1942 MapInference* inference, const bool has_stability_dependency,
1943 ElementsKind kind, SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
1944 NativeContextRef native_context) {
1945 FrameState outer_frame_state = FrameStateInput();
1946 TNode<Context> context = ContextInput();
1947 TNode<Object> target = TargetInput();
1948 TNode<JSArray> receiver = ReceiverInputAs<JSArray>();
1949 TNode<Object> fncallback = ArgumentOrUndefined(0);
1950 TNode<Object> this_arg = ArgumentOrUndefined(1);
1951
1952 // The output array is packed (filter doesn't visit holes).
1953 const ElementsKind packed_kind = GetPackedElementsKind(kind);
1954 TNode<JSArray> a = AllocateEmptyJSArray(packed_kind, native_context);
1955
1956 TNode<Number> original_length = LoadJSArrayLength(receiver, kind);
1957
1958 FilterFrameStateParams frame_state_params{
1959 jsgraph(), shared, context, target, outer_frame_state,
1960 receiver, fncallback, this_arg, a, original_length};
1961
1962 // This frame state doesn't ever call the deopt continuation, it's only
1963 // necessary to specify a continuation in order to handle the exceptional
1964 // case. We don't have all the values available to completely fill out
1965 // the checkpoint parameters yet, but that's okay because it'll never be
1966 // called.
1967 TNode<Number> zero = ZeroConstant();
1968 ThrowIfNotCallable(fncallback, FilterLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params,
1969 zero, zero, zero));
1970
1971 TNode<Number> initial_a_length = zero;
1972 For1ZeroUntil(original_length, initial_a_length)
1973 .Do([&](TNode<Number> k, TNode<Object>* a_length_object) {
1974 TNode<Number> a_length = TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(*a_length_object);
1975 Checkpoint(FilterLoopEagerFrameState(frame_state_params, k, a_length));
1976 MaybeInsertMapChecks(inference, has_stability_dependency);
1977
1978 TNode<Object> element;
1979 std::tie(k, element) = SafeLoadElement(kind, receiver, k);
1980
1981 auto continue_label = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned);
1982 element = MaybeSkipHole(element, kind, &continue_label, a_length);
1983
1984 TNode<Object> v = JSCall3(
1985 fncallback, this_arg, element, k, receiver,
1986 FilterLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, k, a_length, element));
1987
1988 // We need an eager frame state for right after the callback function
1989 // returned, just in case an attempt to grow the output array fails.
1990 Checkpoint(FilterLoopEagerPostCallbackFrameState(frame_state_params, k,
1991 a_length, element, v));
1992
1993 GotoIfNot(ToBoolean(v), &continue_label, a_length);
1994
1995 // Since the callback returned a trueish value, store the element in a.
1996 {
1997 TNode<Number> a_length1 = TypeGuardFixedArrayLength(a_length);
1998 TNode<FixedArrayBase> elements = LoadElements(a);
1999 elements = MaybeGrowFastElements(kind, FeedbackSource{}, a, elements,
2000 a_length1,
2001 LoadFixedArrayBaseLength(elements));
2002
2003 TNode<Number> new_a_length = NumberInc(a_length1);
2004 StoreJSArrayLength(a, new_a_length, kind);
2005 StoreFixedArrayBaseElement(elements, a_length1, element, kind);
2006
2007 Goto(&continue_label, new_a_length);
2008 }
2009
2010 Bind(&continue_label);
2011 *a_length_object =
2012 TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(continue_label.PhiAt(0));
2013 })
2014 .ValueIsUnused();
2015
2016 return a;
2017}

2076
2077TNode<Object> IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReduceArrayPrototypeFind(
2078 MapInference* inference, const bool has_stability_dependency,
2079 ElementsKind kind, SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
2080 NativeContextRef native_context, ArrayFindVariant variant) {
2081 FrameState outer_frame_state = FrameStateInput();
2082 TNode<Context> context = ContextInput();
2083 TNode<Object> target = TargetInput();
2084 TNode<JSArray> receiver = ReceiverInputAs<JSArray>();
2085 TNode<Object> fncallback = ArgumentOrUndefined(0);
2086 TNode<Object> this_arg = ArgumentOrUndefined(1);
2087
2088 TNode<Number> original_length = LoadJSArrayLength(receiver, kind);
2089
2090 FindFrameStateParams frame_state_params{
2091 jsgraph(), shared, context, target, outer_frame_state,
2092 receiver, fncallback, this_arg, original_length};
2093
2094 ThrowIfNotCallable(
2095 fncallback,
2096 FindLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, ZeroConstant(), variant));
2097
2098 const bool is_find_variant = (variant == ArrayFindVariant::kFind);
2099 auto out = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
2100
2101 ForZeroUntil(original_length).Do([&](TNode<Number> k) {
2102 Checkpoint(FindLoopEagerFrameState(frame_state_params, k, variant));
2103 MaybeInsertMapChecks(inference, has_stability_dependency);
2104
2105 TNode<Object> element;
2106 std::tie(k, element) = SafeLoadElement(kind, receiver, k);
2107
2108 if (IsHoleyElementsKind(kind)) {
2109 element = ConvertHoleToUndefined(element, kind);
2110 }
2111
2112 TNode<Object> if_found_value = is_find_variant ? element : k;
2113 TNode<Number> next_k = NumberInc(k);
2114
2115 // The callback result states whether the desired element was found.
2116 TNode<Object> v =
2117 JSCall3(fncallback, this_arg, element, k, receiver,
2118 FindLoopAfterCallbackLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, next_k,
2119 if_found_value, variant));
2120
2121 GotoIf(ToBoolean(v), &out, if_found_value);
2122 });
2123
2124 // If the loop completed, the element was not found.
2125 TNode<Object> if_not_found_value =
2126 is_find_variant ? TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(UndefinedConstant())
2127 : TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(MinusOneConstant());
2128 Goto(&out, if_not_found_value);
2129
2130 Bind(&out);
2131 return out.PhiAt<Object>(0);
2132}

2177
2178TNode<Boolean>
2179IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReduceArrayPrototypeEverySome(
2180 MapInference* inference, const bool has_stability_dependency,
2181 ElementsKind kind, SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
2182 NativeContextRef native_context, ArrayEverySomeVariant variant) {
2183 FrameState outer_frame_state = FrameStateInput();
2184 TNode<Context> context = ContextInput();
2185 TNode<Object> target = TargetInput();
2186 TNode<JSArray> receiver = ReceiverInputAs<JSArray>();
2187 TNode<Object> fncallback = ArgumentOrUndefined(0);
2188 TNode<Object> this_arg = ArgumentOrUndefined(1);
2189
2190 TNode<Number> original_length = LoadJSArrayLength(receiver, kind);
2191
2192 EverySomeFrameStateParams frame_state_params{
2193 jsgraph(), shared, context, target, outer_frame_state,
2194 receiver, fncallback, this_arg, original_length};
2195
2196 ThrowIfNotCallable(
2197 fncallback,
2198 EverySomeLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, ZeroConstant(), variant));
2199
2200 auto out = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
2201
2202 ForZeroUntil(original_length).Do([&](TNode<Number> k) {
2203 Checkpoint(EverySomeLoopEagerFrameState(frame_state_params, k, variant));
2204 MaybeInsertMapChecks(inference, has_stability_dependency);
2205
2206 TNode<Object> element;
2207 std::tie(k, element) = SafeLoadElement(kind, receiver, k);
2208
2209 auto continue_label = MakeLabel();
2210 element = MaybeSkipHole(element, kind, &continue_label);
2211
2212 TNode<Object> v =
2213 JSCall3(fncallback, this_arg, element, k, receiver,
2214 EverySomeLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, k, variant));
2215
2216 if (variant == ArrayEverySomeVariant::kEvery) {
2217 GotoIfNot(ToBoolean(v), &out, FalseConstant());
2218 } else {
2219 DCHECK_EQ(variant, ArrayEverySomeVariant::kSome);
2220 GotoIf(ToBoolean(v), &out, TrueConstant());
2221 }
2222 Goto(&continue_label);
2223 Bind(&continue_label);
2224 });
2225
2226 Goto(&out, (variant == ArrayEverySomeVariant::kEvery) ? TrueConstant()
2227 : FalseConstant());
2228
2229 Bind(&out);
2230 return out.PhiAt<Boolean>(0);
2231}

2233namespace {
2234
2235Callable GetCallableForArrayIndexOfIncludes(ArrayIndexOfIncludesVariant variant,
2236 ElementsKind elements_kind,
2237 Isolate* isolate) {
2238 if (variant == ArrayIndexOfIncludesVariant::kIndexOf) {
2239 switch (elements_kind) {
2240 case PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS:
2241 case HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS:
2242 return Builtins::CallableFor(isolate, Builtin::kArrayIndexOfSmi);
2243 case PACKED_ELEMENTS:
2244 case HOLEY_ELEMENTS:
2245 return Builtins::CallableFor(isolate,
2246 Builtin::kArrayIndexOfSmiOrObject);
2247 case PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS:
2248 return Builtins::CallableFor(isolate,
2249 Builtin::kArrayIndexOfPackedDoubles);
2250 default:
2251 DCHECK_EQ(HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS, elements_kind);
2252 return Builtins::CallableFor(isolate,
2253 Builtin::kArrayIndexOfHoleyDoubles);
2254 }
2255 } else {
2256 DCHECK_EQ(variant, ArrayIndexOfIncludesVariant::kIncludes);
2257 switch (elements_kind) {
2258 case PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS:
2259 case HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS:
2260 return Builtins::CallableFor(isolate, Builtin::kArrayIncludesSmi);
2261 case PACKED_ELEMENTS:
2262 case HOLEY_ELEMENTS:
2263 return Builtins::CallableFor(isolate,
2264 Builtin::kArrayIncludesSmiOrObject);
2265 case PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS:
2266 return Builtins::CallableFor(isolate,
2267 Builtin::kArrayIncludesPackedDoubles);
2268 default:
2269 DCHECK_EQ(HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS, elements_kind);
2270 return Builtins::CallableFor(isolate,
2271 Builtin::kArrayIncludesHoleyDoubles);
2272 }
2273 }
2274 UNREACHABLE();
2275}
2276
2277} // namespace
2278TNode<Object>
2279IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReduceArrayPrototypeIndexOfIncludes(
2280 ElementsKind kind, ArrayIndexOfIncludesVariant variant) {
2281 TNode<Context> context = ContextInput();
2282 TNode<JSArray> receiver = ReceiverInputAs<JSArray>();
2283 TNode<Object> search_element = ArgumentOrUndefined(0);
2284 TNode<Object> from_index = ArgumentOrZero(1);
2285
2286 // TODO(jgruber): This currently only reduces to a stub call. Create a full
2287 // reduction (similar to other higher-order array builtins) instead of
2288 // lowering to a builtin call. E.g. Array.p.every and Array.p.some have almost
2289 // identical functionality.
2290
2291 TNode<Number> length = LoadJSArrayLength(receiver, kind);
2292 TNode<FixedArrayBase> elements = LoadElements(receiver);
2293
2294 const bool have_from_index = ArgumentCount() > 1;
2295 if (have_from_index) {
2296 TNode<Smi> from_index_smi = CheckSmi(from_index);
2297
2298 // If the index is negative, it means the offset from the end and
2299 // therefore needs to be added to the length. If the result is still
2300 // negative, it needs to be clamped to 0.
2301 TNode<Boolean> cond = NumberLessThan(from_index_smi, ZeroConstant());
2302 from_index = SelectIf<Number>(cond)
2303 .Then(_ {
2304 return NumberMax(NumberAdd(length, from_index_smi),
2305 ZeroConstant());
2306 })
2307 .Else(_ { return from_index_smi; })
2308 .ExpectFalse()
2309 .Value();
2310 }
2311
2312 return Call4(GetCallableForArrayIndexOfIncludes(variant, kind, isolate()),
2313 context, elements, search_element, length, from_index);
2314}

2317struct PromiseCtorFrameStateParams {
2318 JSGraph* jsgraph;
2319 SharedFunctionInfoRef shared;
2320 Node* node_ptr;
2321 TNode<Context> context;
2322 TNode<Object> target;
2323 FrameState outer_frame_state;
2324};
2325
2326// Remnant of old-style JSCallReducer code. Could be ported to graph assembler,
2327// but probably not worth the effort.
2328FrameState CreateConstructInvokeStubFrameState(
2329 Node* node, Node* outer_frame_state, SharedFunctionInfoRef shared,
2330 Node* context, CommonOperatorBuilder* common, Graph* graph) {
2331 const FrameStateFunctionInfo* state_info =
2332 common->CreateFrameStateFunctionInfo(FrameStateType::kConstructInvokeStub,
2333 1, 0, 0, shared.object(), {});
2334
2335 const Operator* op = common->FrameState(
2336 BytecodeOffset::None(), OutputFrameStateCombine::Ignore(), state_info);
2337 const Operator* op0 = common->StateValues(0, SparseInputMask::Dense());
2338 Node* node0 = graph->NewNode(op0);
2339
2340 static constexpr int kTargetInputIndex = 0;
2341 static constexpr int kReceiverInputIndex = 1;
2342 std::vector<Node*> params;
2343 params.push_back(node->InputAt(kReceiverInputIndex));
2344 const Operator* op_param = common->StateValues(
2345 static_cast<int>(params.size()), SparseInputMask::Dense());
2346 Node* params_node = graph->NewNode(op_param, static_cast<int>(params.size()),
2347 &params.front());
2348 DCHECK(context);
2349 return FrameState(graph->NewNode(op, params_node, node0, node0, context,
2350 node->InputAt(kTargetInputIndex),
2351 outer_frame_state));
2352}
2353
2354FrameState PromiseConstructorFrameState(
2355 const PromiseCtorFrameStateParams& params, CommonOperatorBuilder* common,
2356 Graph* graph) {
2357 DCHECK_EQ(1,
2358 params.shared.internal_formal_parameter_count_without_receiver());
2359 return CreateConstructInvokeStubFrameState(
2360 params.node_ptr, params.outer_frame_state, params.shared, params.context,
2361 common, graph);
2362}
2363
2364FrameState PromiseConstructorLazyFrameState(
2365 const PromiseCtorFrameStateParams& params,
2366 FrameState constructor_frame_state) {
2367 // The deopt continuation of this frame state is never called; the frame state
2368 // is only necessary to obtain the right stack trace.
2369 JSGraph* jsgraph = params.jsgraph;
2370 Node* checkpoint_params[] = {
2371 jsgraph->UndefinedConstant(), /* receiver */
2372 jsgraph->UndefinedConstant(), /* promise */
2373 jsgraph->UndefinedConstant(), /* reject function */
2374 jsgraph->TheHoleConstant() /* exception */
2375 };
2376 return CreateJavaScriptBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
2377 jsgraph, params.shared, Builtin::kPromiseConstructorLazyDeoptContinuation,
2378 params.target, params.context, checkpoint_params,
2379 arraysize(checkpoint_params), constructor_frame_state,
2380 ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY);
2381}

2383FrameState PromiseConstructorLazyWithCatchFrameState(
2384 const PromiseCtorFrameStateParams& params,
2385 FrameState constructor_frame_state, TNode<JSPromise> promise,
2386 TNode<JSFunction> reject) {
2387 // This continuation just returns the created promise and takes care of
2388 // exceptions thrown by the executor.
2389 Node* checkpoint_params[] = {
2390 params.jsgraph->UndefinedConstant(), /* receiver */
2391 promise, reject};
2392 return CreateJavaScriptBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
2393 params.jsgraph, params.shared,
2394 Builtin::kPromiseConstructorLazyDeoptContinuation, params.target,
2395 params.context, checkpoint_params, arraysize(checkpoint_params),
2396 constructor_frame_state, ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY_WITH_CATCH);
2397}

2400
2401TNode<Object> PromiseBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReducePromiseConstructor(
2402 NativeContextRef native_context) {
2403 DCHECK_GE(ConstructArity(), 1);
2404
2405 JSConstructNode n(node_ptr());
2406 FrameState outer_frame_state = FrameStateInput();
2407 TNode<Context> context = ContextInput();
2408 TNode<Object> target = TargetInput();
2409 TNode<Object> executor = n.Argument(0);
2410 DCHECK_EQ(target, NewTargetInput());
2411
2412 SharedFunctionInfoRef promise_shared =
2413 native_context.promise_function(broker()).shared(broker());
2414
2415 PromiseCtorFrameStateParams frame_state_params{jsgraph(), promise_shared,
2416 node_ptr(), context,
2417 target, outer_frame_state};
2418
2419 // Insert a construct stub frame into the chain of frame states. This will
2420 // reconstruct the proper frame when deoptimizing within the constructor.
2421 // For the frame state, we only provide the executor parameter, even if more
2422 // arguments were passed. This is not observable from JS.
2423 FrameState constructor_frame_state =
2424 PromiseConstructorFrameState(frame_state_params, common(), graph());
2425
2426 ThrowIfNotCallable(executor,
2427 PromiseConstructorLazyFrameState(frame_state_params,
2428 constructor_frame_state));
2429
2430 TNode<JSPromise> promise = CreatePromise(context);
2431
2432 // 8. CreatePromiseResolvingFunctions
2433 // Allocate a promise context for the closures below.
2434 TNode<Context> promise_context = CreateFunctionContext(
2435 native_context, context, PromiseBuiltins::kPromiseContextLength);
2436 StoreContextSlot(promise_context, PromiseBuiltins::kPromiseSlot, promise);
2437 StoreContextSlot(promise_context, PromiseBuiltins::kAlreadyResolvedSlot,
2438 FalseConstant());
2439 StoreContextSlot(promise_context, PromiseBuiltins::kDebugEventSlot,
2440 TrueConstant());
2441
2442 // Allocate closures for the resolve and reject cases.
2443 SharedFunctionInfoRef resolve_sfi =
2444 MakeRef(broker(), broker()
2445 ->isolate()
2446 ->factory()
2447 ->promise_capability_default_resolve_shared_fun());
2448 TNode<JSFunction> resolve =
2449 CreateClosureFromBuiltinSharedFunctionInfo(resolve_sfi, promise_context);
2450
2451 SharedFunctionInfoRef reject_sfi =
2452 MakeRef(broker(), broker()
2453 ->isolate()
2454 ->factory()
2455 ->promise_capability_default_reject_shared_fun());
2456 TNode<JSFunction> reject =
2457 CreateClosureFromBuiltinSharedFunctionInfo(reject_sfi, promise_context);
2458
2459 FrameState lazy_with_catch_frame_state =
2460 PromiseConstructorLazyWithCatchFrameState(
2461 frame_state_params, constructor_frame_state, promise, reject);
2462
2463 // 9. Call executor with both resolving functions.
2464 // 10a. Call reject if the call to executor threw.
2465 Try(_ {
2466 CallPromiseExecutor(executor, resolve, reject, lazy_with_catch_frame_state);
2467 }).Catch([&](TNode<Object> exception) {
2468 // Clear pending message since the exception is not going to be rethrown.
2469 ClearPendingMessage();
2470 CallPromiseReject(reject, exception, lazy_with_catch_frame_state);
2471 });
2472
2473 return promise;
2474}
2475
2476#undef _
2477
2478std::pair<Node*, Node*> JSCallReducer::ReleaseEffectAndControlFromAssembler(
2479 JSCallReducerAssembler* gasm) {
2480 auto catch_scope = gasm->catch_scope();
2481 DCHECK(catch_scope->is_outermost());
2482
2483 if (catch_scope->has_handler() &&
2484 catch_scope->has_exceptional_control_flow()) {
2485 TNode<Object> handler_exception;
2486 Effect handler_effect{nullptr};
2487 Control handler_control{nullptr};
2488 gasm->catch_scope()->MergeExceptionalPaths(
2489 &handler_exception, &handler_effect, &handler_control);
2490
2491 ReplaceWithValue(gasm->outermost_handler(), handler_exception,
2492 handler_effect, handler_control);
2493 }
2494
2495 return {gasm->effect(), gasm->control()};
2496}
2497
2498Reduction JSCallReducer::ReplaceWithSubgraph(JSCallReducerAssembler* gasm,
2499 Node* subgraph) {
2500 // TODO(jgruber): Consider a less fiddly way of integrating the new subgraph
2501 // into the outer graph. For instance, the subgraph could be created in
2502 // complete isolation, and then plugged into the outer graph in one go.
2503 // Instead of manually tracking IfException nodes, we could iterate the
2504 // subgraph.
2505
2506 // Replace the Call node with the newly-produced subgraph.
2507 ReplaceWithValue(gasm->node_ptr(), subgraph, gasm->effect(), gasm->control());
2508
2509 // Wire exception edges contained in the newly-produced subgraph into the
2510 // outer graph.
2511 auto catch_scope = gasm->catch_scope();
2512 DCHECK(catch_scope->is_outermost());
2513
2514 if (catch_scope->has_handler() &&
2515 catch_scope->has_exceptional_control_flow()) {
2516 TNode<Object> handler_exception;
2517 Effect handler_effect{nullptr};
2518 Control handler_control{nullptr};
2519 gasm->catch_scope()->MergeExceptionalPaths(
2520 &handler_exception, &handler_effect, &handler_control);
2521
2522 ReplaceWithValue(gasm->outermost_handler(), handler_exception,
2523 handler_effect, handler_control);
2524 }
2525
2526 return Replace(subgraph);
2527}

2529Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceMathUnary(Node* node, const Operator* op) {
2530 JSCallNode n(node);
2531 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2532 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
2533 return NoChange();
2534 }
2535 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
2536 Node* value = jsgraph()->NaNConstant();
2537 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
2538 return Replace(value);
2539 }
2540
2541 JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node);
2542 Node* subgraph = a.ReduceMathUnary(op);
2543 return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
2544}

2546Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceMathBinary(Node* node, const Operator* op) {
2547 JSCallNode n(node);
2548 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2549 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
2550 return NoChange();
2551 }
2552 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
2553 Node* value = jsgraph()->NaNConstant();
2554 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
2555 return Replace(value);
2556 }
2557
2558 JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node);
2559 Node* subgraph = a.ReduceMathBinary(op);
2560 return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
2561}

2563// ES6 section 20.2.2.19 Math.imul ( x, y )
2564Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceMathImul(Node* node) {
2565 JSCallNode n(node);
2566 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2567 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
2568 return NoChange();
2569 }
2570 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
2571 Node* value = jsgraph()->ZeroConstant();
2572 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
2573 return Replace(value);
2574 }
2575 Node* left = n.Argument(0);
2576 Node* right = n.ArgumentOr(1, jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
2577 Effect effect = n.effect();
2578 Control control = n.control();
2579
2580 left = effect =
2581 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->SpeculativeToNumber(
2582 NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball, p.feedback()),
2583 left, effect, control);
2584 right = effect =
2585 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->SpeculativeToNumber(
2586 NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball, p.feedback()),
2587 right, effect, control);
2588 left = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberToUint32(), left);
2589 right = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberToUint32(), right);
2590 Node* value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberImul(), left, right);
2591 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect);
2592 return Replace(value);
2593}

2595// ES6 section 20.2.2.11 Math.clz32 ( x )
2596Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceMathClz32(Node* node) {
2597 JSCallNode n(node);
2598 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2599 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
2600 return NoChange();
2601 }
2602 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
2603 Node* value = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(32);
2604 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
2605 return Replace(value);
2606 }
2607 Node* input = n.Argument(0);
2608 Effect effect = n.effect();
2609 Control control = n.control();
2610
2611 input = effect =
2612 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->SpeculativeToNumber(
2613 NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball, p.feedback()),
2614 input, effect, control);
2615 input = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberToUint32(), input);
2616 Node* value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberClz32(), input);
2617 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect);
2618 return Replace(value);
2619}
