2621// ES6 section 20.2.2.24 Math.max ( value1, value2, ...values )
2622// ES6 section 20.2.2.25 Math.min ( value1, value2, ...values )
2623Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceMathMinMax(Node* node, const Operator* op,
2624 Node* empty_value) {
2625 JSCallNode n(node);
2626 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2627 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
2628 return NoChange();
2629 }
2630 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
2631 ReplaceWithValue(node, empty_value);
2632 return Replace(empty_value);
2633 }
2634 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
2635 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
2636
2637 Node* value = effect =
2638 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->SpeculativeToNumber(
2639 NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball, p.feedback()),
2640 n.Argument(0), effect, control);
2641 for (int i = 1; i < n.ArgumentCount(); i++) {
2642 Node* input = effect = graph()->NewNode(
2643 simplified()->SpeculativeToNumber(NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball,
2644 p.feedback()),
2645 n.Argument(i), effect, control);
2646 value = graph()->NewNode(op, value, input);
2647 }
2648
2649 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect);
2650 return Replace(value);
2651}
2652
2653Reduction JSCallReducer::Reduce(Node* node) {
2654 switch (node->opcode()) {
2655 case IrOpcode::kJSConstruct:
2656 return ReduceJSConstruct(node);
2657 case IrOpcode::kJSConstructWithArrayLike:
2658 return ReduceJSConstructWithArrayLike(node);
2659 case IrOpcode::kJSConstructWithSpread:
2660 return ReduceJSConstructWithSpread(node);
2661 case IrOpcode::kJSConstructForwardAllArgs:
2662 return ReduceJSConstructForwardAllArgs(node);
2663 case IrOpcode::kJSCall:
2664 return ReduceJSCall(node);
2665 case IrOpcode::kJSCallWithArrayLike:
2666 return ReduceJSCallWithArrayLike(node);
2667 case IrOpcode::kJSCallWithSpread:
2668 return ReduceJSCallWithSpread(node);
2669 default:
2670 break;
2671 }
2672 return NoChange();
2673}
2674
2675void JSCallReducer::Finalize() {
2676 // TODO(turbofan): This is not the best solution; ideally we would be able
2677 // to teach the GraphReducer about arbitrary dependencies between different
2678 // nodes, even if they don't show up in the use list of the other node.
2679 std::set<Node*> const waitlist = std::move(waitlist_);
2680 for (Node* node : waitlist) {
2681 if (!node->IsDead()) {
2682 // Remember the max node id before reduction.
2683 NodeId const max_id = static_cast<NodeId>(graph()->NodeCount() - 1);
2684 Reduction const reduction = Reduce(node);
2685 if (reduction.Changed()) {
2686 Node* replacement = reduction.replacement();
2687 if (replacement != node) {
2688 Replace(node, replacement, max_id);
2689 }
2690 }
2691 }
2692 }
2693}
2694
2695// ES6 section 22.1.1 The Array Constructor
2696Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayConstructor(Node* node) {
2697 JSCallNode n(node);
2698 Node* target = n.target();
2699 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2700
2701 // Turn the {node} into a {JSCreateArray} call.
2702 size_t const arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
2703 node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
2704 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, target, 0);
2705 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, target, 1);
2706 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node,
2707 javascript()->CreateArray(arity, std::nullopt));
2708 return Changed(node);
2709}
2710
2711// ES6 section 19.3.1.1 Boolean ( value )
2712Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceBooleanConstructor(Node* node) {
2713 // Replace the {node} with a proper {ToBoolean} operator.
2714 JSCallNode n(node);
2715 Node* value = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
2716 value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ToBoolean(), value);
2717 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
2718 return Replace(value);
2719}
2720
2721// ES section #sec-object-constructor
2722Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceObjectConstructor(Node* node) {
2723 JSCallNode n(node);
2724 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) return NoChange();
2725 Node* value = n.Argument(0);
2726 Effect effect = n.effect();
2727
2728 // We can fold away the Tagged<Object>(x) call if |x| is definitely not a
2729 // primitive.
2730 if (NodeProperties::CanBePrimitive(broker(), value, effect)) {
2731 if (!NodeProperties::CanBeNullOrUndefined(broker(), value, effect)) {
2732 // Turn the {node} into a {JSToObject} call if we know that
2733 // the {value} cannot be null or undefined.
2734 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInputs(node, value);
2735 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->ToObject());
2736 return Changed(node);
2737 }
2738 } else {
2739 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
2740 return Replace(value);
2741 }
2742 return NoChange();
2743}
2744
2745// ES6 section 19.2.3.1 Function.prototype.apply ( thisArg, argArray )
2746Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceFunctionPrototypeApply(Node* node) {
2747 JSCallNode n(node);
2748 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2749 CallFeedbackRelation new_feedback_relation =
2750 p.feedback_relation() == CallFeedbackRelation::kReceiver
2751 ? CallFeedbackRelation::kTarget
2752 : CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated;
2753 int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
2754
2755 if (arity < 2) {
2756 // Degenerate cases.
2757 ConvertReceiverMode convert_mode;
2758 if (arity == 0) {
2759 // Neither thisArg nor argArray was provided.
2760 convert_mode = ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined;
2761 node->ReplaceInput(n.TargetIndex(), n.receiver());
2762 node->ReplaceInput(n.ReceiverIndex(), jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
2763 } else {
2764 DCHECK_EQ(arity, 1);
2765 // The argArray was not provided, just remove the {target}.
2766 convert_mode = ConvertReceiverMode::kAny;
2767 node->RemoveInput(n.TargetIndex());
2768 --arity;
2769 }
2770 // Change {node} to a {JSCall} and try to reduce further.
2771 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
2772 node, javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(arity), p.frequency(),
2773 p.feedback(), convert_mode,
2774 p.speculation_mode(), new_feedback_relation));
2775 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCall(node));
2776 }
2777
2778 // Turn the JSCall into a JSCallWithArrayLike.
2779 // If {argArray} can be null or undefined, we have to generate branches since
2780 // JSCallWithArrayLike would throw for null or undefined.
2781
2782 Node* target = n.receiver();
2783 Node* this_argument = n.Argument(0);
2784 Node* arguments_list = n.Argument(1);
2785 Node* context = n.context();
2786 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
2787 Effect effect = n.effect();
2788 Control control = n.control();
2789
2790 // If {arguments_list} cannot be null or undefined, we don't need
2791 // to expand this {node} to control-flow.
2792 if (!NodeProperties::CanBeNullOrUndefined(broker(), arguments_list, effect)) {
2793 // Massage the value inputs appropriately.
2794 node->ReplaceInput(n.TargetIndex(), target);
2795 node->ReplaceInput(n.ReceiverIndex(), this_argument);
2796 node->ReplaceInput(n.ArgumentIndex(0), arguments_list);
2797 while (arity-- > 1) node->RemoveInput(n.ArgumentIndex(1));
2798
2799 // Morph the {node} to a {JSCallWithArrayLike}.
2800 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
2801 node, javascript()->CallWithArrayLike(p.frequency(), p.feedback(),
2802 p.speculation_mode(),
2803 new_feedback_relation));
2804 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCallWithArrayLike(node));
2805 }
2806
2807 // Check whether {arguments_list} is null.
2808 Node* check_null =
2809 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), arguments_list,
2810 jsgraph()->NullConstant());
2811 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse), check_null,
2812 control);
2813 Node* if_null = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), control);
2814 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), control);
2815
2816 // Check whether {arguments_list} is undefined.
2817 Node* check_undefined =
2818 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), arguments_list,
2819 jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
2820 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse),
2821 check_undefined, control);
2822 Node* if_undefined = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), control);
2823 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), control);
2824
2825 // Lower to {JSCallWithArrayLike} if {arguments_list} is neither null
2826 // nor undefined.
2827 Node* effect0 = effect;
2828 Node* control0 = control;
2829 Node* value0 = effect0 = control0 = graph()->NewNode(
2830 javascript()->CallWithArrayLike(p.frequency(), p.feedback(),
2831 p.speculation_mode(),
2832 new_feedback_relation),
2833 target, this_argument, arguments_list, n.feedback_vector(), context,
2834 frame_state, effect0, control0);
2835
2836 // Lower to {JSCall} if {arguments_list} is either null or undefined.
2837 Node* effect1 = effect;
2838 Node* control1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_null, if_undefined);
2839 Node* value1 = effect1 = control1 = graph()->NewNode(
2840 javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(0)), target, this_argument,
2841 n.feedback_vector(), context, frame_state, effect1, control1);
2842
2843 // Rewire potential exception edges.
2844 Node* if_exception = nullptr;
2845 if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &if_exception)) {
2846 // Create appropriate {IfException} and {IfSuccess} nodes.
2847 Node* if_exception0 =
2848 graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), control0, effect0);
2849 control0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), control0);
2850 Node* if_exception1 =
2851 graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), control1, effect1);
2852 control1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), control1);
2853
2854 // Join the exception edges.
2855 Node* merge =
2856 graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_exception0, if_exception1);
2857 Node* ephi = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), if_exception0,
2858 if_exception1, merge);
2859 Node* phi =
2860 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
2861 if_exception0, if_exception1, merge);
2862 ReplaceWithValue(if_exception, phi, ephi, merge);
2863 }
2864
2865 // Join control paths.
2866 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), control0, control1);
2867 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), effect0, effect1, control);
2868 Node* value =
2869 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2), value0,
2870 value1, control);
2871 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
2872 return Replace(value);
2873}
2874
2875// ES section #sec-function.prototype.bind
2876Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceFunctionPrototypeBind(Node* node) {
2877 JSCallNode n(node);
2878 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2879 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
2880 return NoChange();
2881 }
2882
2883 // Value inputs to the {node} are as follows:
2884 //
2885 // - target, which is Function.prototype.bind JSFunction
2886 // - receiver, which is the [[BoundTargetFunction]]
2887 // - bound_this (optional), which is the [[BoundThis]]
2888 // - and all the remaining value inputs are [[BoundArguments]]
2889 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
2890 Node* context = n.context();
2891 Effect effect = n.effect();
2892 Control control = n.control();
2893
2894 // Ensure that the {receiver} is known to be a JSBoundFunction or
2895 // a JSFunction with the same [[Prototype]], and all maps we've
2896 // seen for the {receiver} so far indicate that {receiver} is
2897 // definitely a constructor or not a constructor.
2898 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
2899 if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
2900 ZoneRefSet<Map> const& receiver_maps = inference.GetMaps();
2901
2902 MapRef first_receiver_map = receiver_maps[0];
2903 bool const is_constructor = first_receiver_map.is_constructor();
2904
2905 HeapObjectRef prototype = first_receiver_map.prototype(broker());
2906
2907 for (MapRef receiver_map : receiver_maps) {
2908 HeapObjectRef map_prototype = receiver_map.prototype(broker());
2909
2910 // Check for consistency among the {receiver_maps}.
2911 if (!map_prototype.equals(prototype) ||
2912 receiver_map.is_constructor() != is_constructor ||
2913 !InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSFunctionOrBoundFunctionOrWrappedFunction(
2914 receiver_map.instance_type())) {
2915 return inference.NoChange();
2916 }
2917
2918 // Disallow binding of slow-mode functions. We need to figure out
2919 // whether the length and name property are in the original state.
2920 if (receiver_map.is_dictionary_map()) return inference.NoChange();
2921
2922 // Check whether the length and name properties are still present
2923 // as AccessorInfo objects. In that case, their values can be
2924 // recomputed even if the actual value of the object changes.
2925 // This mirrors the checks done in builtins-function-gen.cc at
2926 // runtime otherwise.
2927 int minimum_nof_descriptors =
2928 std::max(
2929 {JSFunctionOrBoundFunctionOrWrappedFunction::kLengthDescriptorIndex,
2930 JSFunctionOrBoundFunctionOrWrappedFunction::
2931 kNameDescriptorIndex}) +
2932 1;
2933 if (receiver_map.NumberOfOwnDescriptors() < minimum_nof_descriptors) {
2934 return inference.NoChange();
2935 }
2936 const InternalIndex kLengthIndex(
2937 JSFunctionOrBoundFunctionOrWrappedFunction::kLengthDescriptorIndex);
2938 const InternalIndex kNameIndex(
2939 JSFunctionOrBoundFunctionOrWrappedFunction::kNameDescriptorIndex);
2940 StringRef length_string = broker()->length_string();
2941 StringRef name_string = broker()->name_string();
2942
2943 OptionalObjectRef length_value(
2944 receiver_map.GetStrongValue(broker(), kLengthIndex));
2945 OptionalObjectRef name_value(
2946 receiver_map.GetStrongValue(broker(), kNameIndex));
2947 if (!length_value || !name_value) {
2948 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(
2949 broker(), "name or length descriptors on map " << receiver_map);
2950 return inference.NoChange();
2951 }
2952 if (!receiver_map.GetPropertyKey(broker(), kLengthIndex)
2953 .equals(length_string) ||
2954 !length_value->IsAccessorInfo() ||
2955 !receiver_map.GetPropertyKey(broker(), kNameIndex)
2956 .equals(name_string) ||
2957 !name_value->IsAccessorInfo()) {
2958 return inference.NoChange();
2959 }
2960 }
2961
2962 // Choose the map for the resulting JSBoundFunction (but bail out in case of a
2963 // custom prototype).
2964 MapRef map =
2965 is_constructor
2966 ? native_context().bound_function_with_constructor_map(broker())
2967 : native_context().bound_function_without_constructor_map(broker());
2968 if (!map.prototype(broker()).equals(prototype)) return inference.NoChange();
2969
2970 inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
2971 control, p.feedback());
2972
2973 // Replace the {node} with a JSCreateBoundFunction.
2974 static constexpr int kBoundThis = 1;
2975 static constexpr int kReceiverContextEffectAndControl = 4;
2976 int const arity = n.ArgumentCount();
2977
2978 if (arity > 0) {
2979 MapRef fixed_array_map = broker()->fixed_array_map();
2980 AllocationBuilder ab(jsgraph(), broker(), effect, control);
2981 if (!ab.CanAllocateArray(arity, fixed_array_map)) {
2982 return NoChange();
2983 }
2984 }
2985
2986 int const arity_with_bound_this = std::max(arity, kBoundThis);
2987 int const input_count =
2988 arity_with_bound_this + kReceiverContextEffectAndControl;
2989 Node** inputs = graph()->zone()->AllocateArray<Node*>(input_count);
2990 int cursor = 0;
2991 inputs[cursor++] = receiver;
2992 inputs[cursor++] = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph()); // bound_this.
2993 for (int i = 1; i < arity; ++i) {
2994 inputs[cursor++] = n.Argument(i);
2995 }
2996 inputs[cursor++] = context;
2997 inputs[cursor++] = effect;
2998 inputs[cursor++] = control;
2999 DCHECK_EQ(cursor, input_count);
3000 Node* value = effect =
3001 graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateBoundFunction(
3002 arity_with_bound_this - kBoundThis, map),
3003 input_count, inputs);
3004 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
3005 return Replace(value);
3006}
3007
3008// ES6 section 19.2.3.3 Function.prototype.call (thisArg, ...args)
3009Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceFunctionPrototypeCall(Node* node) {
3010 JSCallNode n(node);
3011 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
3012 Node* target = n.target();
3013 Effect effect = n.effect();
3014 Control control = n.control();
3015
3016 // Change context of {node} to the Function.prototype.call context,
3017 // to ensure any exception is thrown in the correct context.
3018 Node* context;
3019 HeapObjectMatcher m(target);
3020 if (m.HasResolvedValue() && m.Ref(broker()).IsJSFunction()) {
3021 JSFunctionRef function = m.Ref(broker()).AsJSFunction();
3022 context = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(function.context(broker()), broker());
3023 } else {
3024 context = effect = graph()->NewNode(
3025 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSFunctionContext()), target,
3026 effect, control);
3027 }
3028 NodeProperties::ReplaceContextInput(node, context);
3029 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
3030
3031 // Remove the target from {node} and use the receiver as target instead, and
3032 // the thisArg becomes the new target. If thisArg was not provided, insert
3033 // undefined instead.
3034 int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
3035 ConvertReceiverMode convert_mode;
3036 if (arity == 0) {
3037 // The thisArg was not provided, use undefined as receiver.
3038 convert_mode = ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined;
3039 node->ReplaceInput(n.TargetIndex(), n.receiver());
3040 node->ReplaceInput(n.ReceiverIndex(), jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
3041 } else {
3042 // Just remove the target, which is the first value input.
3043 convert_mode = ConvertReceiverMode::kAny;
3044 node->RemoveInput(n.TargetIndex());
3045 --arity;
3046 }
3047 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
3048 node, javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(arity), p.frequency(),
3049 p.feedback(), convert_mode, p.speculation_mode(),
3050 CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated));
3051 // Try to further reduce the JSCall {node}.
3052 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCall(node));
3053}
3054
3055// ES6 section 19.2.3.6 Function.prototype [ @@hasInstance ] (V)
3056Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceFunctionPrototypeHasInstance(Node* node) {
3057 JSCallNode n(node);
3058 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
3059 Node* object = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
3060 Node* context = n.context();
3061 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
3062 Effect effect = n.effect();
3063 Control control = n.control();
3064
3065 // TODO(turbofan): If JSOrdinaryToInstance raises an exception, the
3066 // stack trace doesn't contain the @@hasInstance call; we have the
3067 // corresponding bug in the baseline case. Some massaging of the frame
3068 // state would be necessary here.
3069
3070 // Morph this {node} into a JSOrdinaryHasInstance node.
3071 node->ReplaceInput(0, receiver);
3072 node->ReplaceInput(1, object);
3073 node->ReplaceInput(2, context);
3074 node->ReplaceInput(3, frame_state);
3075 node->ReplaceInput(4, effect);
3076 node->ReplaceInput(5, control);
3077 node->TrimInputCount(6);
3078 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->OrdinaryHasInstance());
3079 return Changed(node);
3080}
3081
3082Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceObjectGetPrototype(Node* node, Node* object) {
3083 Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
3084
3085 // Try to determine the {object} map.
3086 MapInference inference(broker(), object, effect);
3087 if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
3088 ZoneRefSet<Map> const& object_maps = inference.GetMaps();
3089
3090 MapRef candidate_map = object_maps[0];
3091 HeapObjectRef candidate_prototype = candidate_map.prototype(broker());
3092
3093 // Check if we can constant-fold the {candidate_prototype}.
3094 for (size_t i = 0; i < object_maps.size(); ++i) {
3095 MapRef object_map = object_maps[i];
3096 HeapObjectRef map_prototype = object_map.prototype(broker());
3097 if (IsSpecialReceiverInstanceType(object_map.instance_type()) ||
3098 !map_prototype.equals(candidate_prototype)) {
3099 // We exclude special receivers, like JSProxy or API objects that
3100 // might require access checks here; we also don't want to deal
3101 // with hidden prototypes at this point.
3102 return inference.NoChange();
3103 }
3104 // The above check also excludes maps for primitive values, which is
3105 // important because we are not applying [[ToObject]] here as expected.
3106 DCHECK(!object_map.IsPrimitiveMap() && object_map.IsJSReceiverMap());
3107 }
3108 if (!inference.RelyOnMapsViaStability(dependencies())) {
3109 return inference.NoChange();
3110 }
3111 Node* value = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(candidate_prototype, broker());
3112 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
3113 return Replace(value);
3114}

3139// ES #sec-object.prototype.hasownproperty
3140Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceObjectPrototypeHasOwnProperty(Node* node) {
3141 JSCallNode call_node(node);
3142 Node* receiver = call_node.receiver();
3143 Node* name = call_node.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
3144 Effect effect = call_node.effect();
3145 Control control = call_node.control();
3146
3147 // We can optimize a call to Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty if it's being
3148 // used inside a fast-mode for..in, so for code like this:
3149 //
3150 // for (name in receiver) {
3151 // if (receiver.hasOwnProperty(name)) {
3152 // ...
3153 // }
3154 // }
3155 //
3156 // If the for..in is in fast-mode, we know that the {receiver} has {name}
3157 // as own property, otherwise the enumeration wouldn't include it. The graph
3158 // constructed by the BytecodeGraphBuilder in this case looks like this:
3159
3160 // receiver
3161 // ^ ^
3162 // | |
3163 // | +-+
3164 // | |
3165 // | JSToObject
3166 // | ^
3167 // | |
3168 // | JSForInNext
3169 // | ^
3170 // +----+ |
3171 // | |
3172 // JSCall[hasOwnProperty]
3173
3174 // We can constant-fold the {node} to True in this case, and insert
3175 // a (potentially redundant) map check to guard the fact that the
3176 // {receiver} map didn't change since the dominating JSForInNext. This
3177 // map check is only necessary when TurboFan cannot prove that there
3178 // is no observable side effect between the {JSForInNext} and the
3179 // {JSCall} to Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.
3180 //
3181 // Also note that it's safe to look through the {JSToObject}, since the
3182 // Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty does an implicit ToObject anyway, and
3183 // these operations are not observable.
3184 if (name->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSForInNext) {
3185 JSForInNextNode n(name);
3186 if (n.Parameters().mode() != ForInMode::kGeneric) {
3187 Node* object = n.receiver();
3188 Node* cache_type = n.cache_type();
3189 if (object->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToObject) {
3190 object = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(object, 0);
3191 }
3192 if (object == receiver) {
3193 // No need to repeat the map check if we can prove that there's no
3194 // observable side effect between {effect} and {name].
3195 if (!NodeProperties::NoObservableSideEffectBetween(effect, name)) {
3196 Node* receiver_map = effect =
3197 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap()),
3198 receiver, effect, control);
3199 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(),
3200 receiver_map, cache_type);
3201 effect = graph()->NewNode(
3202 simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap), check, effect,
3203 control);
3204 }
3205 Node* value = jsgraph()->TrueConstant();
3206 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
3207 return Replace(value);
3208 }
3209
3210 // We can also optimize for this case below:
3211
3212 // receiver(is a heap constant with fast map)
3213 // ^
3214 // | object(all keys are enumerable)
3215 // | ^
3216 // | |
3217 // | JSForInNext
3218 // | ^
3219 // +----+ |
3220 // | |
3221 // JSCall[hasOwnProperty]
3222
3223 // We can replace the {JSCall} with several internalized string
3224 // comparisons.
3225
3226 if (receiver->opcode() == IrOpcode::kHeapConstant) {
3227 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
3228 if (!inference.HaveMaps()) {
3229 return inference.NoChange();
3230 }
3231 const ZoneRefSet<Map>& receiver_maps = inference.GetMaps();
3232 if (receiver_maps.size() == 1) {
3233 const MapRef receiver_map = *receiver_maps.begin();
3234 InstanceType instance_type = receiver_map.instance_type();
3235 int const nof = receiver_map.NumberOfOwnDescriptors();
3236 // We set a heuristic value to limit the compare instructions number.
3237 if (nof > 4 || instance_type <= LAST_SPECIAL_RECEIVER_TYPE ||
3238 receiver_map.is_dictionary_map()) {
3239 return inference.NoChange();
3240 }
3241 // Replace builtin call with several internalized string comparisons.
3242 CallParameters const& p = call_node.Parameters();
3243 inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(),
3244 &effect, control, p.feedback());
3245#define __ gasm.
3246 JSGraphAssembler gasm(broker(), jsgraph(), jsgraph()->zone(),
3247 BranchSemantics::kJS);
3248 gasm.InitializeEffectControl(effect, control);
3249 auto done = __ MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
3250 const DescriptorArrayRef descriptor_array =
3251 receiver_map.instance_descriptors(broker());
3252 for (InternalIndex key_index : InternalIndex::Range(nof)) {
3253 NameRef receiver_key =
3254 descriptor_array.GetPropertyKey(broker(), key_index);
3255 Node* lhs = jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(receiver_key.object());
3256 __ GotoIf(__ ReferenceEqual(TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(lhs),
3257 TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(name)),
3258 &done, __ TrueConstant());
3259 }
3260 __ Goto(&done, __ FalseConstant());
3261 __ Bind(&done);
3262
3263 Node* value = done.PhiAt(0);
3264 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, gasm.effect(), gasm.control());
3265 return Replace(value);
3266#undef __
3267 }
3268 return inference.NoChange();
3269 }
3270 }
3271 }
3272
3273 return NoChange();
3274}
3275
3276// ES #sec-object.prototype.isprototypeof
3277Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceObjectPrototypeIsPrototypeOf(Node* node) {
3278 JSCallNode n(node);
3279 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
3280 Node* value = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
3281 Effect effect = n.effect();
3282
3283 // Ensure that the {receiver} is known to be a JSReceiver (so that
3284 // the ToObject step of Object.prototype.isPrototypeOf is a no-op).
3285 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
3286 if (!inference.HaveMaps() || !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAreJSReceiver()) {
3287 return NoChange();
3288 }
3289
3290 // We don't check whether {value} is a proper JSReceiver here explicitly,
3291 // and don't explicitly rule out Primitive {value}s, since all of them
3292 // have null as their prototype, so the prototype chain walk inside the
3293 // JSHasInPrototypeChain operator immediately aborts and yields false.
3294 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, value, n.TargetIndex());
3295 for (int i = node->op()->ValueInputCount(); i > 2; i--) {
3296 node->RemoveInput(2);
3297 }
3298 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->HasInPrototypeChain());
3299 return Changed(node);
3300}

3302// ES6 section 26.1.1 Reflect.apply ( target, thisArgument, argumentsList )
3303Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceReflectApply(Node* node) {
3304 JSCallNode n(node);
3305 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
3306 int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
3307 // Massage value inputs appropriately.
3308 static_assert(n.ReceiverIndex() > n.TargetIndex());
3309 node->RemoveInput(n.ReceiverIndex());
3310 node->RemoveInput(n.TargetIndex());
3311 while (arity < 3) {
3312 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), arity++, jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
3313 }
3314 while (arity-- > 3) {
3315 node->RemoveInput(arity);
3316 }
3317 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
3318 node, javascript()->CallWithArrayLike(p.frequency(), p.feedback(),
3319 p.speculation_mode(),
3320 CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated));
3321 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCallWithArrayLike(node));
3322}

3324// ES6 section 26.1.2 Reflect.construct ( target, argumentsList [, newTarget] )
3325Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceReflectConstruct(Node* node) {
3326 JSCallNode n(node);
3327 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
3328 int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
3329 // Massage value inputs appropriately.
3330 TNode<Object> arg_target = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
3331 TNode<Object> arg_argument_list = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph());
3332 TNode<Object> arg_new_target = n.ArgumentOr(2, arg_target);
3333
3334 static_assert(n.ReceiverIndex() > n.TargetIndex());
3335 node->RemoveInput(n.ReceiverIndex());
3336 node->RemoveInput(n.TargetIndex());
3337
3338 // TODO(jgruber): This pattern essentially ensures that we have the correct
3339 // number of inputs for a given argument count. Wrap it in a helper function.
3340 static_assert(JSConstructNode::FirstArgumentIndex() == 2);
3341 while (arity < 3) {
3342 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), arity++, jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
3343 }
3344 while (arity-- > 3) {
3345 node->RemoveInput(arity);
3346 }
3347
3348 static_assert(JSConstructNode::TargetIndex() == 0);
3349 static_assert(JSConstructNode::NewTargetIndex() == 1);
3350 static_assert(JSConstructNode::kFeedbackVectorIsLastInput);
3351 node->ReplaceInput(JSConstructNode::TargetIndex(), arg_target);
3352 node->ReplaceInput(JSConstructNode::NewTargetIndex(), arg_new_target);
3353 node->ReplaceInput(JSConstructNode::ArgumentIndex(0), arg_argument_list);
3354
3355 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
3356 node, javascript()->ConstructWithArrayLike(p.frequency(), p.feedback()));
3357 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSConstructWithArrayLike(node));
3358}

3388// ES section #sec-reflect.get
3389Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceReflectGet(Node* node) {
3390 JSCallNode n(node);
3391 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
3392 int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
3393 if (arity != 2) return NoChange();
3394 Node* target = n.Argument(0);
3395 Node* key = n.Argument(1);
3396 Node* context = n.context();
3397 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
3398 Effect effect = n.effect();
3399 Control control = n.control();
3400
3401 // Check whether {target} is a JSReceiver.
3402 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsReceiver(), target);
3403 Node* branch =
3404 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check, control);
3405
3406 // Throw an appropriate TypeError if the {target} is not a JSReceiver.
3407 Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
3408 Node* efalse = effect;
3409 {
3410 if_false = efalse = graph()->NewNode(
3411 javascript()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowTypeError, 2),
3412 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
3413 static_cast<int>(MessageTemplate::kCalledOnNonObject)),
3414 jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(factory()->ReflectGet_string()), context,
3415 frame_state, efalse, if_false);
3416 }
3417
3418 // Otherwise just use the existing GetPropertyStub.
3419 Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
3420 Node* etrue = effect;
3421 Node* vtrue;
3422 {
3423 Callable callable = Builtins::CallableFor(isolate(), Builtin::kGetProperty);
3424 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
3425 graph()->zone(), callable.descriptor(),
3426 callable.descriptor().GetStackParameterCount(),
3427 CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState, Operator::kNoProperties);
3428 Node* stub_code = jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(callable.code());
3429 vtrue = etrue = if_true =
3430 graph()->NewNode(common()->Call(call_descriptor), stub_code, target,
3431 key, context, frame_state, etrue, if_true);
3432 }
3433
3434 // Rewire potential exception edges.
3435 Node* on_exception = nullptr;
3436 if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &on_exception)) {
3437 // Create appropriate {IfException} and {IfSuccess} nodes.
3438 Node* extrue = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), etrue, if_true);
3439 if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), if_true);
3440 Node* exfalse = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), efalse, if_false);
3441 if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), if_false);
3442
3443 // Join the exception edges.
3444 Node* merge = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), extrue, exfalse);
3445 Node* ephi =
3446 graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), extrue, exfalse, merge);
3447 Node* phi =
3448 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
3449 extrue, exfalse, merge);
3450 ReplaceWithValue(on_exception, phi, ephi, merge);
3451 }
3452
3453 // Connect the throwing path to end.
3454 if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->Throw(), efalse, if_false);
3455 MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), if_false);
3456
3457 // Continue on the regular path.
3458 ReplaceWithValue(node, vtrue, etrue, if_true);
3459 return Changed(vtrue);
3460}

3462// ES section #sec-reflect.has
3463Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceReflectHas(Node* node) {
3464 JSCallNode n(node);
3465 Node* target = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
3466 Node* key = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph());
3467 Node* context = n.context();
3468 Effect effect = n.effect();
3469 Control control = n.control();
3470 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
3471
3472 // Check whether {target} is a JSReceiver.
3473 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsReceiver(), target);
3474 Node* branch =
3475 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check, control);
3476
3477 // Throw an appropriate TypeError if the {target} is not a JSReceiver.
3478 Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
3479 Node* efalse = effect;
3480 {
3481 if_false = efalse = graph()->NewNode(
3482 javascript()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowTypeError, 2),
3483 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
3484 static_cast<int>(MessageTemplate::kCalledOnNonObject)),
3485 jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(factory()->ReflectHas_string()), context,
3486 frame_state, efalse, if_false);
3487 }
3488
3489 // Otherwise just use the existing {JSHasProperty} logic.
3490 Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
3491 Node* etrue = effect;
3492 Node* vtrue;
3493 {
3494 // TODO(magardn): collect feedback so this can be optimized
3495 vtrue = etrue = if_true = graph()->NewNode(
3496 javascript()->HasProperty(FeedbackSource()), target, key,
3497 jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant(), context, frame_state, etrue, if_true);
3498 }
3499
3500 // Rewire potential exception edges.
3501 Node* on_exception = nullptr;
3502 if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &on_exception)) {
3503 // Create appropriate {IfException} and {IfSuccess} nodes.
3504 Node* extrue = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), etrue, if_true);
3505 if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), if_true);
3506 Node* exfalse = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), efalse, if_false);
3507 if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), if_false);
3508
3509 // Join the exception edges.
3510 Node* merge = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), extrue, exfalse);
3511 Node* ephi =
3512 graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), extrue, exfalse, merge);
3513 Node* phi =
3514 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
3515 extrue, exfalse, merge);
3516 ReplaceWithValue(on_exception, phi, ephi, merge);
3517 }
3518
3519 // Connect the throwing path to end.
3520 if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->Throw(), efalse, if_false);
3521 MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), if_false);
3522
3523 // Continue on the regular path.
3524 ReplaceWithValue(node, vtrue, etrue, if_true);
3525 return Changed(vtrue);
3526}

3528namespace {
3529
3530bool CanInlineArrayIteratingBuiltin(JSHeapBroker* broker,
3531 ZoneRefSet<Map> const& receiver_maps,
3532 ElementsKind* kind_return) {
3533 DCHECK_NE(0, receiver_maps.size());
3534 *kind_return = receiver_maps[0].elements_kind();
3535 for (MapRef map : receiver_maps) {
3536 if (!map.supports_fast_array_iteration(broker) ||
3537 !UnionElementsKindUptoSize(kind_return, map.elements_kind())) {
3538 return false;
3539 }
3540 }
3541 return true;
3542}
3543
3544bool CanInlineArrayResizingBuiltin(JSHeapBroker* broker,
3545 ZoneRefSet<Map> const& receiver_maps,
3546 std::vector<ElementsKind>* kinds,
3547 bool builtin_is_push = false) {
3548 DCHECK_NE(0, receiver_maps.size());
3549 for (MapRef map : receiver_maps) {
3550 if (!map.supports_fast_array_resize(broker)) return false;
3551 // TODO(turbofan): We should also handle fast holey double elements once
3552 // we got the hole NaN mess sorted out in TurboFan/V8.
3553 if (map.elements_kind() == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS && !builtin_is_push) {
3554 return false;
3555 }
3556 ElementsKind current_kind = map.elements_kind();
3557 auto kind_ptr = kinds->data();
3558 size_t i;
3559 for (i = 0; i < kinds->size(); i++, kind_ptr++) {
3560 if (UnionElementsKindUptoPackedness(kind_ptr, current_kind)) {
3561 break;
3562 }
3563 }
3564 if (i == kinds->size()) kinds->push_back(current_kind);
3565 }
3566 return true;
3567}
3568
3569// Wraps common setup code for iterating array builtins.
3570class IteratingArrayBuiltinHelper {
3571 public:
3572 IteratingArrayBuiltinHelper(Node* node, JSHeapBroker* broker,
3573 JSGraph* jsgraph,
3574 CompilationDependencies* dependencies)
3575 : receiver_(NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1)),
3576 effect_(NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)),
3577 control_(NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node)),
3578 inference_(broker, receiver_, effect_) {
3579 if (!v8_flags.turbo_inline_array_builtins) return;
3580
3581 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSCall, node->opcode());
3582 const CallParameters& p = CallParametersOf(node->op());
3583 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
3584 return;
3585 }
3586
3587 // Try to determine the {receiver} map.
3588 if (!inference_.HaveMaps()) return;
3589 ZoneRefSet<Map> const& receiver_maps = inference_.GetMaps();
3590
3591 if (!CanInlineArrayIteratingBuiltin(broker, receiver_maps,
3592 &elements_kind_)) {
3593 return;
3594 }
3595
3596 // TODO(jgruber): May only be needed for holey elements kinds.
3597 if (!dependencies->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) return;
3598
3599 has_stability_dependency_ = inference_.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(
3600 dependencies, jsgraph, &effect_, control_, p.feedback());
3601
3602 can_reduce_ = true;
3603 }
3604
3605 bool can_reduce() const { return can_reduce_; }
3606 bool has_stability_dependency() const { return has_stability_dependency_; }
3607 Effect effect() const { return effect_; }
3608 Control control() const { return control_; }
3609 MapInference* inference() { return &inference_; }
3610 ElementsKind elements_kind() const { return elements_kind_; }
3611
3612 private:
3613 bool can_reduce_ = false;
3614 bool has_stability_dependency_ = false;
3615 Node* receiver_;
3616 Effect effect_;
3617 Control control_;
3618 MapInference inference_;
3619 ElementsKind elements_kind_;
3620};
3621
3622} // namespace

3625 SharedFunctionInfoRef shared) {
3626 IteratingArrayBuiltinHelper h(node, broker(), jsgraph(), dependencies());
3627 if (!h.can_reduce()) return h.inference()->NoChange();
3628
3629 IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler a(this, node);
3630 a.InitializeEffectControl(h.effect(), h.control());
3631 TNode<Object> subgraph = a.ReduceArrayPrototypeForEach(
3632 h.inference(), h.has_stability_dependency(), h.elements_kind(), shared);
3633 return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
3634}

3784#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3785
3786namespace {
3787
3788bool CanInlineJSToWasmCall(const wasm::CanonicalSig* wasm_signature) {
3789 if (wasm_signature->return_count() > 1) {
3790 return false;
3791 }
3792
3793 for (auto type : wasm_signature->all()) {
3794#if defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_32_BIT)
3795 if (type == wasm::kCanonicalI64) return false;
3796#endif
3797 if (type != wasm::kCanonicalI32 && type != wasm::kCanonicalI64 &&
3798 type != wasm::kCanonicalF32 && type != wasm::kCanonicalF64 &&
3799 type != wasm::kCanonicalExternRef) {
3800 return false;
3801 }
3802 }
3803
3804 return true;
3805}
3806
3807} // namespace
3808
3809Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceCallWasmFunction(Node* node,
3810 SharedFunctionInfoRef shared) {
3811 DCHECK(flags() & kInlineJSToWasmCalls);
3812
3813 JSCallNode n(node);
3814 const CallParameters& p = n.Parameters();
3815
3816 // Avoid deoptimization loops
3817 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
3818 return NoChange();
3819 }
3820
3821 // Read the trusted object only once to ensure a consistent view on it.
3822 Tagged<Object> trusted_data = shared.object()->GetTrustedData();
3823 if (!IsWasmExportedFunctionData(trusted_data)) return NoChange();
3824 Tagged<WasmExportedFunctionData> function_data =
3825 Cast<WasmExportedFunctionData>(trusted_data);
3826
3827 if (function_data->is_promising()) return NoChange();
3828
3829 Tagged<WasmTrustedInstanceData> instance_data =
3830 function_data->instance_data();
3831 const wasm::CanonicalSig* wasm_signature = function_data->sig();
3832 if (!CanInlineJSToWasmCall(wasm_signature)) {
3833 return NoChange();
3834 }
3835
3836 wasm::NativeModule* native_module = instance_data->native_module();
3837 const wasm::WasmModule* wasm_module = native_module->module();
3838 int wasm_function_index = function_data->function_index();
3839
3840 if (wasm_module_for_inlining_ == nullptr) {
3841 wasm_module_for_inlining_ = wasm_module;
3842 }
3843
3844 // TODO(mliedtke): We should be able to remove module, signature, native
3845 // module and function index from the SharedFunctionInfoRef. However, for some
3846 // reason I may dereference the SharedFunctionInfoRef here but not in
3847 // JSInliningHeuristic later on.
3848 const Operator* op =
3849 javascript()->CallWasm(wasm_module, wasm_signature, wasm_function_index,
3850 shared, native_module, p.feedback());
3851
3852 // Remove additional inputs
3853 size_t actual_arity = n.ArgumentCount();
3854 DCHECK(JSCallNode::kFeedbackVectorIsLastInput);
3855 DCHECK_EQ(actual_arity + JSWasmCallNode::kExtraInputCount - 1,
3856 n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
3857 size_t expected_arity = wasm_signature->parameter_count();
3858
3859 while (actual_arity > expected_arity) {
3860 int removal_index =
3861 static_cast<int>(n.FirstArgumentIndex() + expected_arity);
3862 DCHECK_LT(removal_index, static_cast<int>(node->InputCount()));
3863 node->RemoveInput(removal_index);
3864 actual_arity--;
3865 }
3866
3867 // Add missing inputs
3868 while (actual_arity < expected_arity) {
3869 int insertion_index = n.ArgumentIndex(n.ArgumentCount());
3870 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), insertion_index,
3871 jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
3872 actual_arity++;
3873 }
3874
3875 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, op);
3876 return Changed(node);
3877}
3878#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3879
3880Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceCallApiFunction(Node* node,
3881 SharedFunctionInfoRef shared) {
3882 JSCallNode n(node);
3883 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
3884 int const argc = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
3885 Node* target = n.target();
3886 Node* global_proxy = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
3887 native_context().global_proxy_object(broker()), broker());
3888 Node* receiver = (p.convert_mode() == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined)
3889 ? global_proxy
3890 : n.receiver();
3891 Node* holder;
3892 Node* context = n.context();
3893 Effect effect = n.effect();
3894 Control control = n.control();
3895 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
3896
3897 if (!shared.function_template_info(broker()).has_value()) {
3898 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(
3899 broker(), "FunctionTemplateInfo for function with SFI " << shared);
3900 return NoChange();
3901 }
3902
3903 // See if we can optimize this API call to {shared}.
3904 FunctionTemplateInfoRef function_template_info(
3905 shared.function_template_info(broker()).value());
3906
3907 if (function_template_info.accept_any_receiver() &&
3908 function_template_info.is_signature_undefined(broker())) {
3909 // We might be able to
3910 // optimize the API call depending on the {function_template_info}.
3911 // If the API function accepts any kind of {receiver}, we only need to
3912 // ensure that the {receiver} is actually a JSReceiver at this point,
3913 // and also pass that as the {holder}. There are two independent bits
3914 // here:
3915 //
3916 // a. When the "accept any receiver" bit is set, it means we don't
3917 // need to perform access checks, even if the {receiver}'s map
3918 // has the "needs access check" bit set.
3919 // b. When the {function_template_info} has no signature, we don't
3920 // need to do the compatible receiver check, since all receivers
3921 // are considered compatible at that point, and the {receiver}
3922 // will be pass as the {holder}.
3923 //
3924 receiver = holder = effect = graph()->NewNode(
3925 simplified()->ConvertReceiver(p.convert_mode()), receiver,
3926 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(native_context(), broker()), global_proxy,
3927 effect, control);
3928 } else {
3929 // Try to infer the {receiver} maps from the graph.
3930 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
3931 if (inference.HaveMaps()) {
3932 ZoneRefSet<Map> const& receiver_maps = inference.GetMaps();
3933 MapRef first_receiver_map = receiver_maps[0];
3934
3935 // See if we can constant-fold the compatible receiver checks.
3936 HolderLookupResult api_holder =
3937 function_template_info.LookupHolderOfExpectedType(broker(),
3938 first_receiver_map);
3939 if (api_holder.lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderNotFound) {
3940 return inference.NoChange();
3941 }
3942
3943 // Check that all {receiver_maps} are actually JSReceiver maps and
3944 // that the {function_template_info} accepts them without access
3945 // checks (even if "access check needed" is set for {receiver}).
3946 //
3947 // Note that we don't need to know the concrete {receiver} maps here,
3948 // meaning it's fine if the {receiver_maps} are unreliable, and we also
3949 // don't need to install any stability dependencies, since the only
3950 // relevant information regarding the {receiver} is the Map::constructor
3951 // field on the root map (which is different from the JavaScript exposed
3952 // "constructor" property) and that field cannot change.
3953 //
3954 // So if we know that {receiver} had a certain constructor at some point
3955 // in the past (i.e. it had a certain map), then this constructor is going
3956 // to be the same later, since this information cannot change with map
3957 // transitions.
3958 //
3959 // The same is true for the instance type, e.g. we still know that the
3960 // instance type is JSObject even if that information is unreliable, and
3961 // the "access check needed" bit, which also cannot change later.
3962 CHECK(first_receiver_map.IsJSReceiverMap());
3963 CHECK(!first_receiver_map.is_access_check_needed() ||
3964 function_template_info.accept_any_receiver());
3965
3966 for (size_t i = 1; i < receiver_maps.size(); ++i) {
3967 MapRef receiver_map = receiver_maps[i];
3968 HolderLookupResult holder_i =
3969 function_template_info.LookupHolderOfExpectedType(broker(),
3970 receiver_map);
3971
3972 if (api_holder.lookup != holder_i.lookup) return inference.NoChange();
3973 DCHECK(holder_i.lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderFound ||
3974 holder_i.lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderIsReceiver);
3975 if (holder_i.lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderFound) {
3976 DCHECK(api_holder.holder.has_value() && holder_i.holder.has_value());
3977 if (!api_holder.holder->equals(*holder_i.holder)) {
3978 return inference.NoChange();
3979 }
3980 }
3981
3982 CHECK(receiver_map.IsJSReceiverMap());
3983 CHECK(!receiver_map.is_access_check_needed() ||
3984 function_template_info.accept_any_receiver());
3985 }
3986
3987 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation &&
3988 !inference.RelyOnMapsViaStability(dependencies())) {
3989 // We were not able to make the receiver maps reliable without map
3990 // checks but doing map checks would lead to deopt loops, so give up.
3991 return inference.NoChange();
3992 }
3993
3994 // TODO(neis): The maps were used in a way that does not actually require
3995 // map checks or stability dependencies.
3996 inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
3997 control, p.feedback());
3998
3999 // Determine the appropriate holder for the {lookup}.
4000 holder = api_holder.lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderFound
4001 ? jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(*api_holder.holder, broker())
4002 : receiver;
4003 } else {
4004 // We don't have enough information to eliminate the access check
4005 // and/or the compatible receiver check, so use the generic builtin
4006 // that does those checks dynamically. This is still significantly
4007 // faster than the generic call sequence.
4008 Builtin builtin_name;
4009 if (function_template_info.accept_any_receiver()) {
4010 DCHECK(!function_template_info.is_signature_undefined(broker()));
4011 builtin_name = Builtin::kCallFunctionTemplate_CheckCompatibleReceiver;
4012 } else if (function_template_info.is_signature_undefined(broker())) {
4013 builtin_name = Builtin::kCallFunctionTemplate_CheckAccess;
4014 } else {
4015 builtin_name =
4016 Builtin::kCallFunctionTemplate_CheckAccessAndCompatibleReceiver;
4017 }
4018
4019 // The CallFunctionTemplate builtin requires the {receiver} to be
4020 // an actual JSReceiver, so make sure we do the proper conversion
4021 // first if necessary.
4022 receiver = holder = effect = graph()->NewNode(
4023 simplified()->ConvertReceiver(p.convert_mode()), receiver,
4024 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(native_context(), broker()), global_proxy,
4025 effect, control);
4026
4027 Callable callable = Builtins::CallableFor(isolate(), builtin_name);
4028 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
4029 graph()->zone(), callable.descriptor(),
4030 argc + 1 /* implicit receiver */, CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState);
4031 node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
4032 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 0,
4033 jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(callable.code()));
4034 node->ReplaceInput(
4035 1, jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(function_template_info, broker()));
4036 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 2,
4037 jsgraph()->Int32Constant(JSParameterCount(argc)));
4038 node->ReplaceInput(3, receiver); // Update receiver input.
4039 node->ReplaceInput(6 + argc, effect); // Update effect input.
4040 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, common()->Call(call_descriptor));
4041 return Changed(node);
4042 }
4043 }
4044
4045 // TODO(turbofan): Consider introducing a JSCallApiCallback operator for
4046 // this and lower it during JSGenericLowering, and unify this with the
4047 // JSNativeContextSpecialization::InlineApiCall method a bit.
4048 compiler::OptionalObjectRef maybe_callback_data =
4049 function_template_info.callback_data(broker());
4050 // Check if the function has an associated C++ code to execute.
4051 if (!maybe_callback_data.has_value()) {
4052 // TODO(ishell): consider generating "return undefined" for empty function
4053 // instead of failing.
4054 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(broker(), "call code for function template info "
4055 << function_template_info);
4056 return NoChange();
4057 }
4058
4059 // Handles overloaded functions.
4060 FastApiCallFunction c_function = fast_api_call::GetFastApiCallTarget(
4061 broker(), function_template_info, argc);
4062
4063 if (c_function.address) {
4064 FastApiCallReducerAssembler a(this, node, function_template_info,
4065 c_function, receiver, holder, shared, target,
4066 argc, effect);
4067 Node* fast_call_subgraph = a.ReduceFastApiCall();
4068
4069 return Replace(fast_call_subgraph);
4070 }
4071
4072 // Slow call
4073
4074 bool no_profiling = broker()->dependencies()->DependOnNoProfilingProtector();
4075 Callable call_api_callback = Builtins::CallableFor(
4076 isolate(), no_profiling ? Builtin::kCallApiCallbackOptimizedNoProfiling
4077 : Builtin::kCallApiCallbackOptimized);
4078 CallInterfaceDescriptor cid = call_api_callback.descriptor();
4079 auto call_descriptor =
4080 Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(graph()->zone(), cid, argc + 1 /*
4081 implicit receiver */, CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState);
4082 ApiFunction api_function(function_template_info.callback(broker()));
4083 ExternalReference function_reference = ExternalReference::Create(
4084 &api_function, ExternalReference::DIRECT_API_CALL);
4085
4086 Node* continuation_frame_state = CreateInlinedApiFunctionFrameState(
4087 jsgraph(), shared, target, context, receiver, frame_state);
4088
4089 node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
4090 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 0,
4091 jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(call_api_callback.code()));
4092 node->ReplaceInput(1, jsgraph()->ExternalConstant(function_reference));
4093 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 2, jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(argc));
4094 node->InsertInput(
4095 graph()->zone(), 3,
4096 jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(function_template_info.object()));
4097 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 4, holder);
4098 node->ReplaceInput(5, receiver); // Update receiver input.
4099 // 6 + argc is context input.
4100 node->ReplaceInput(6 + argc + 1, continuation_frame_state);
4101 node->ReplaceInput(6 + argc + 2, effect);
4102 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, common()->Call(call_descriptor));
4103 return Changed(node);
4104}
4105
4106namespace {
4107
4108// Check whether elements aren't mutated; we play it extremely safe here by
4109// explicitly checking that {node} is only used by {LoadField} or
4110// {LoadElement}.
4111bool IsSafeArgumentsElements(Node* node) {
4112 for (Edge const edge : node->use_edges()) {
4113 if (!NodeProperties::IsValueEdge(edge)) continue;
4114 if (edge.from()->opcode() != IrOpcode::kLoadField &&
4115 edge.from()->opcode() != IrOpcode::kLoadElement) {
4116 return false;
4117 }
4118 }
4119 return true;
4120}

4122#ifdef DEBUG
4123bool IsCallOrConstructWithArrayLike(Node* node) {
4124 return node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCallWithArrayLike ||
4125 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSConstructWithArrayLike;
4126}
4127#endif
4128
4129bool IsCallOrConstructWithSpread(Node* node) {
4130 return node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCallWithSpread ||
4131 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSConstructWithSpread;
4132}
4133
4134bool IsCallWithArrayLikeOrSpread(Node* node) {
4135 return node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCallWithArrayLike ||
4136 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCallWithSpread;
4137}
