4140
4141Node* JSCallReducer::ConvertHoleToUndefined(Node* value, ElementsKind kind) {
4142 DCHECK(IsHoleyElementsKind(kind));
4143 if (kind == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS) {
4144 return graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ChangeFloat64HoleToTagged(), value);
4145 }
4146 return graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ConvertTaggedHoleToUndefined(), value);
4147}
4148
4149void JSCallReducer::CheckIfConstructor(Node* construct) {
4150 JSConstructNode n(construct);
4151 Node* new_target = n.new_target();
4152 Control control = n.control();
4153
4154 Node* check =
4155 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsConstructor(), new_target);
4156 Node* check_branch =
4157 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check, control);
4158 Node* check_fail = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), check_branch);
4159 Node* check_throw = check_fail = graph()->NewNode(
4160 javascript()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowTypeError, 2),
4161 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
4162 static_cast<int>(MessageTemplate::kNotConstructor)),
4163 new_target, n.context(), n.frame_state(), n.effect(), check_fail);
4164 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), check_branch);
4165 NodeProperties::ReplaceControlInput(construct, control);
4166
4167 // Rewire potential exception edges.
4168 Node* on_exception = nullptr;
4169 if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(construct, &on_exception)) {
4170 // Create appropriate {IfException} and {IfSuccess} nodes.
4171 Node* if_exception =
4172 graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), check_throw, check_fail);
4173 check_fail = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), check_fail);
4174
4175 // Join the exception edges.
4176 Node* merge =
4177 graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_exception, on_exception);
4178 Node* ephi = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), if_exception,
4179 on_exception, merge);
4180 Node* phi =
4181 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
4182 if_exception, on_exception, merge);
4183 ReplaceWithValue(on_exception, phi, ephi, merge);
4184 merge->ReplaceInput(1, on_exception);
4185 ephi->ReplaceInput(1, on_exception);
4186 phi->ReplaceInput(1, on_exception);
4187 }
4188
4189 // The above %ThrowTypeError runtime call is an unconditional throw,
4190 // making it impossible to return a successful completion in this case. We
4191 // simply connect the successful completion to the graph end.
4192 Node* throw_node =
4193 graph()->NewNode(common()->Throw(), check_throw, check_fail);
4194 MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), throw_node);
4195}
4196
4197namespace {
4198
4199bool ShouldUseCallICFeedback(Node* node) {
4200 HeapObjectMatcher m(node);
4201 if (m.HasResolvedValue() || m.IsCheckClosure() || m.IsJSCreateClosure()) {
4202 // Don't use CallIC feedback when we know the function
4203 // being called, i.e. either know the closure itself or
4204 // at least the SharedFunctionInfo.
4205 return false;
4206 } else if (m.IsPhi()) {
4207 // Protect against endless loops here.
4208 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
4209 if (control->opcode() == IrOpcode::kLoop ||
4210 control->opcode() == IrOpcode::kDead)
4211 return false;
4212 // Check if {node} is a Phi of nodes which shouldn't
4213 // use CallIC feedback (not looking through loops).
4214 int const value_input_count = m.node()->op()->ValueInputCount();
4215 for (int n = 0; n < value_input_count; ++n) {
4216 if (ShouldUseCallICFeedback(node->InputAt(n))) return true;
4217 }
4218 return false;
4219 }
4220 return true;
4221}
4222
4223} // namespace
4224
4225Node* JSCallReducer::CheckArrayLength(Node* array, ElementsKind elements_kind,
4226 uint32_t array_length,
4227 const FeedbackSource& feedback_source,
4228 Effect effect, Control control) {
4229 Node* length = effect = graph()->NewNode(
4230 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(elements_kind)),
4231 array, effect, control);
4232 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(), length,
4233 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(array_length));
4234 return graph()->NewNode(
4235 simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kArrayLengthChanged,
4236 feedback_source),
4237 check, effect, control);
4238}
4239
4240Reduction
4241JSCallReducer::ReduceCallOrConstructWithArrayLikeOrSpreadOfCreateArguments(
4242 Node* node, Node* arguments_list, int arraylike_or_spread_index,
4243 CallFrequency const& frequency, FeedbackSource const& feedback,
4244 SpeculationMode speculation_mode, CallFeedbackRelation feedback_relation) {
4245 DCHECK_EQ(arguments_list->opcode(), IrOpcode::kJSCreateArguments);
4246
4247 // Check if {node} is the only value user of {arguments_list} (except for
4248 // value uses in frame states). If not, we give up for now.
4249 for (Edge edge : arguments_list->use_edges()) {
4250 if (!NodeProperties::IsValueEdge(edge)) continue;
4251 Node* const user = edge.from();
4252 switch (user->opcode()) {
4253 case IrOpcode::kCheckMaps:
4254 case IrOpcode::kFrameState:
4255 case IrOpcode::kStateValues:
4256 case IrOpcode::kReferenceEqual:
4257 case IrOpcode::kReturn:
4258 // Ignore safe uses that definitely don't mess with the arguments.
4259 continue;
4260 case IrOpcode::kLoadField: {
4261 DCHECK_EQ(arguments_list, user->InputAt(0));
4262 FieldAccess const& access = FieldAccessOf(user->op());
4263 if (access.offset == JSArray::kLengthOffset) {
4264 // Ignore uses for arguments#length.
4265 static_assert(
4266 static_cast<int>(JSArray::kLengthOffset) ==
4267 static_cast<int>(JSStrictArgumentsObject::kLengthOffset));
4268 static_assert(
4269 static_cast<int>(JSArray::kLengthOffset) ==
4270 static_cast<int>(JSSloppyArgumentsObject::kLengthOffset));
4271 continue;
4272 } else if (access.offset == JSObject::kElementsOffset) {
4273 // Ignore safe uses for arguments#elements.
4274 if (IsSafeArgumentsElements(user)) continue;
4275 }
4276 break;
4277 }
4278 case IrOpcode::kJSCallWithArrayLike: {
4279 // Ignore uses as argumentsList input to calls with array like.
4280 JSCallWithArrayLikeNode n(user);
4281 if (edge.index() == n.ArgumentIndex(0)) continue;
4282 break;
4283 }
4284 case IrOpcode::kJSConstructWithArrayLike: {
4285 // Ignore uses as argumentsList input to calls with array like.
4286 JSConstructWithArrayLikeNode n(user);
4287 if (edge.index() == n.ArgumentIndex(0)) continue;
4288 break;
4289 }
4290 case IrOpcode::kJSCallWithSpread: {
4291 // Ignore uses as spread input to calls with spread.
4292 JSCallWithSpreadNode n(user);
4293 if (edge.index() == n.LastArgumentIndex()) continue;
4294 break;
4295 }
4296 case IrOpcode::kJSConstructWithSpread: {
4297 // Ignore uses as spread input to construct with spread.
4298 JSConstructWithSpreadNode n(user);
4299 if (edge.index() == n.LastArgumentIndex()) continue;
4300 break;
4301 }
4302 default:
4303 break;
4304 }
4305 // We cannot currently reduce the {node} to something better than what
4306 // it already is, but we might be able to do something about the {node}
4307 // later, so put it on the waitlist and try again during finalization.
4308 waitlist_.insert(node);
4309 return NoChange();
4310 }
4311
4312 // Get to the actual frame state from which to extract the arguments;
4313 // we can only optimize this in case the {node} was already inlined into
4314 // some other function (and same for the {arguments_list}).
4315 CreateArgumentsType const type = CreateArgumentsTypeOf(arguments_list->op());
4316 FrameState frame_state =
4317 FrameState{NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(arguments_list)};
4318
4319 int formal_parameter_count;
4320 {
4321 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared;
4322 if (!frame_state.frame_state_info().shared_info().ToHandle(&shared)) {
4323 return NoChange();
4324 }
4325 formal_parameter_count =
4326 MakeRef(broker(), shared)
4327 .internal_formal_parameter_count_without_receiver();
4328 }
4329
4330 if (type == CreateArgumentsType::kMappedArguments) {
4331 // Mapped arguments (sloppy mode) that are aliased can only be handled
4332 // here if there's no side-effect between the {node} and the {arg_array}.
4333 // TODO(turbofan): Further relax this constraint.
4334 if (formal_parameter_count != 0) {
4335 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
4336 if (!NodeProperties::NoObservableSideEffectBetween(effect,
4337 arguments_list)) {
4338 return NoChange();
4339 }
4340 }
4341 }
4342
4343 // For call/construct with spread, we need to also install a code
4344 // dependency on the array iterator lookup protector cell to ensure
4345 // that no one messed with the %ArrayIteratorPrototype%.next method.
4346 if (IsCallOrConstructWithSpread(node)) {
4347 if (!dependencies()->DependOnArrayIteratorProtector()) return NoChange();
4348 }
4349
4350 // Remove the {arguments_list} input from the {node}.
4351 node->RemoveInput(arraylike_or_spread_index);
4352
4353 // The index of the first relevant parameter. Only non-zero when looking at
4354 // rest parameters, in which case it is set to the index of the first rest
4355 // parameter.
4356 const int start_index = (type == CreateArgumentsType::kRestParameter)
4357 ? formal_parameter_count
4358 : 0;
4359
4360 // After removing the arraylike or spread object, the argument count is:
4361 int argc =
4362 arraylike_or_spread_index - JSCallOrConstructNode::FirstArgumentIndex();
4363 // Check if are spreading to inlined arguments or to the arguments of
4364 // the outermost function.
4365 if (frame_state.outer_frame_state()->opcode() != IrOpcode::kFrameState) {
4366 Operator const* op;
4367 if (IsCallWithArrayLikeOrSpread(node)) {
4368 static constexpr int kTargetAndReceiver = 2;
4369 op = javascript()->CallForwardVarargs(argc + kTargetAndReceiver,
4370 start_index);
4371 } else {
4372 static constexpr int kTargetAndNewTarget = 2;
4373 op = javascript()->ConstructForwardVarargs(argc + kTargetAndNewTarget,
4374 start_index);
4375 }
4376 node->RemoveInput(JSCallOrConstructNode::FeedbackVectorIndexForArgc(argc));
4377 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, op);
4378 return Changed(node);
4379 }
4380 // Get to the actual frame state from which to extract the arguments;
4381 // we can only optimize this in case the {node} was already inlined into
4382 // some other function (and same for the {arg_array}).
4383 FrameState outer_state{frame_state.outer_frame_state()};
4384 FrameStateInfo outer_info = outer_state.frame_state_info();
4385 if (outer_info.type() == FrameStateType::kInlinedExtraArguments) {
4386 // Need to take the parameters from the inlined extra arguments frame state.
4387 frame_state = outer_state;
4388 }
4389 // Add the actual parameters to the {node}, skipping the receiver.
4390 StateValuesAccess parameters_access(frame_state.parameters());
4391 for (auto it = parameters_access.begin_without_receiver_and_skip(start_index);
4392 !it.done(); ++it) {
4393 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(it.node());
4394 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(),
4395 JSCallOrConstructNode::ArgumentIndex(argc++), it.node());
4396 }
4397
4398 if (IsCallWithArrayLikeOrSpread(node)) {
4399 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
4400 node, javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(argc), frequency,
4401 feedback, ConvertReceiverMode::kAny,
4402 speculation_mode, feedback_relation));
4403 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCall(node));
4404 } else {
4405 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
4406 node, javascript()->Construct(JSConstructNode::ArityForArgc(argc),
4407 frequency, feedback));
4408
4409 // Check whether the given new target value is a constructor function. The
4410 // replacement {JSConstruct} operator only checks the passed target value
4411 // but relies on the new target value to be implicitly valid.
4412 CheckIfConstructor(node);
4413 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSConstruct(node));
4414 }
4415}
4416
4417Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceCallOrConstructWithArrayLikeOrSpread(
4418 Node* node, int argument_count, int arraylike_or_spread_index,
4419 CallFrequency const& frequency, FeedbackSource const& feedback_source,
4420 SpeculationMode speculation_mode, CallFeedbackRelation feedback_relation,
4421 Node* target, Effect effect, Control control) {
4422 DCHECK(IsCallOrConstructWithArrayLike(node) ||
4423 IsCallOrConstructWithSpread(node));
4424 DCHECK_IMPLIES(speculation_mode == SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation,
4425 feedback_source.IsValid());
4426
4427 Node* arguments_list =
4428 NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, arraylike_or_spread_index);
4429
4430 if (arguments_list->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCreateArguments) {
4431 return ReduceCallOrConstructWithArrayLikeOrSpreadOfCreateArguments(
4432 node, arguments_list, arraylike_or_spread_index, frequency,
4433 feedback_source, speculation_mode, feedback_relation);
4434 }
4435
4436 if (!v8_flags.turbo_optimize_apply) return NoChange();
4437
4438 // Optimization of construct nodes not supported yet.
4439 if (!IsCallWithArrayLikeOrSpread(node)) return NoChange();
4440
4441 // Avoid deoptimization loops.
4442 if (speculation_mode != SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation) return NoChange();
4443
4444 // Only optimize with array literals.
4445 if (arguments_list->opcode() != IrOpcode::kJSCreateLiteralArray &&
4446 arguments_list->opcode() != IrOpcode::kJSCreateEmptyLiteralArray) {
4447 return NoChange();
4448 }
4449
4450 // For call/construct with spread, we need to also install a code
4451 // dependency on the array iterator lookup protector cell to ensure
4452 // that no one messed with the %ArrayIteratorPrototype%.next method.
4453 if (IsCallOrConstructWithSpread(node)) {
4454 if (!dependencies()->DependOnArrayIteratorProtector()) return NoChange();
4455 }
4456
4457 if (arguments_list->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCreateEmptyLiteralArray) {
4458 if (generated_calls_with_array_like_or_spread_.count(node)) {
4459 return NoChange(); // Avoid infinite recursion.
4460 }
4461 JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node);
4462 Node* subgraph = a.ReduceJSCallWithArrayLikeOrSpreadOfEmpty(
4463 &generated_calls_with_array_like_or_spread_);
4464 return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
4465 }
4466
4467 DCHECK_EQ(arguments_list->opcode(), IrOpcode::kJSCreateLiteralArray);
4468 int new_argument_count;
4469
4470 // Find array length and elements' kind from the feedback's allocation
4471 // site's boilerplate JSArray.
4472 JSCreateLiteralOpNode args_node(arguments_list);
4473 CreateLiteralParameters const& args_params = args_node.Parameters();
4474 const FeedbackSource& array_feedback = args_params.feedback();
4475 const ProcessedFeedback& feedback =
4476 broker()->GetFeedbackForArrayOrObjectLiteral(array_feedback);
4477 if (feedback.IsInsufficient()) return NoChange();
4478
4479 AllocationSiteRef site = feedback.AsLiteral().value();
4480 if (!site.boilerplate(broker()).has_value()) return NoChange();
4481
4482 JSArrayRef boilerplate_array = site.boilerplate(broker())->AsJSArray();
4483 int const array_length =
4484 boilerplate_array.GetBoilerplateLength(broker()).AsSmi();
4485
4486 // We'll replace the arguments_list input with {array_length} element loads.
4487 new_argument_count = argument_count - 1 + array_length;
4488
4489 // Do not optimize calls with a large number of arguments.
4490 // Arbitrarily sets the limit to 32 arguments.
4491 const int kMaxArityForOptimizedFunctionApply = 32;
4492 if (new_argument_count > kMaxArityForOptimizedFunctionApply) {
4493 return NoChange();
4494 }
4495
4496 // Determine the array's map.
4497 MapRef array_map = boilerplate_array.map(broker());
4498 if (!array_map.supports_fast_array_iteration(broker())) {
4499 return NoChange();
4500 }
4501
4502 // Check and depend on NoElementsProtector.
4503 if (!dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
4504 return NoChange();
4505 }
4506
4507 // Remove the {arguments_list} node which will be replaced by a sequence of
4508 // LoadElement nodes.
4509 node->RemoveInput(arraylike_or_spread_index);
4510
4511 // Speculate on that array's map is still equal to the dynamic map of
4512 // arguments_list; generate a map check.
4513 effect = graph()->NewNode(
4514 simplified()->CheckMaps(CheckMapsFlag::kNone, ZoneRefSet<Map>(array_map),
4515 feedback_source),
4516 arguments_list, effect, control);
4517
4518 // Speculate on that array's length being equal to the dynamic length of
4519 // arguments_list; generate a deopt check.
4520 ElementsKind elements_kind = array_map.elements_kind();
4521 effect = CheckArrayLength(arguments_list, elements_kind, array_length,
4522 feedback_source, effect, control);
4523
4524 // Generate N element loads to replace the {arguments_list} node with a set
4525 // of arguments loaded from it.
4526 Node* elements = effect = graph()->NewNode(
4527 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements()),
4528 arguments_list, effect, control);
4529 for (int i = 0; i < array_length; i++) {
4530 // Load the i-th element from the array.
4531 Node* index = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(i);
4532 Node* load = effect = graph()->NewNode(
4533 simplified()->LoadElement(
4534 AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(elements_kind)),
4535 elements, index, effect, control);
4536
4537 // In "holey" arrays some arguments might be missing and we pass
4538 // 'undefined' instead.
4539 if (IsHoleyElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
4540 load = ConvertHoleToUndefined(load, elements_kind);
4541 }
4542
4543 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), arraylike_or_spread_index + i, load);
4544 }
4545
4546 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
4547 node,
4548 javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(new_argument_count),
4549 frequency, feedback_source, ConvertReceiverMode::kAny,
4550 speculation_mode, CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated));
4551 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
4552 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCall(node));
4553}
4554
4555bool JSCallReducer::IsBuiltinOrApiFunction(JSFunctionRef function) const {
4556 // TODO(neis): Add a way to check if function template info isn't serialized
4557 // and add a warning in such cases. Currently we can't tell if function
4558 // template info doesn't exist or wasn't serialized.
4559 return function.shared(broker()).HasBuiltinId() ||
4560 function.shared(broker()).function_template_info(broker()).has_value();
4561}
4562
4563Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceJSCall(Node* node) {
4564 if (broker()->StackHasOverflowed()) return NoChange();
4565
4566 JSCallNode n(node);
4567 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
4568 Node* target = n.target();
4569 Effect effect = n.effect();
4570 Control control = n.control();
4571 int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
4572
4573 // Try to specialize JSCall {node}s with constant {target}s.
4574 HeapObjectMatcher m(target);
4575 if (m.HasResolvedValue()) {
4576 ObjectRef target_ref = m.Ref(broker());
4577 if (target_ref.IsJSFunction()) {
4578 JSFunctionRef function = target_ref.AsJSFunction();
4579
4580 // Don't inline cross native context.
4581 if (!function.native_context(broker()).equals(native_context())) {
4582 return NoChange();
4583 }
4584
4585 return ReduceJSCall(node, function.shared(broker()));
4586 } else if (target_ref.IsJSBoundFunction()) {
4587 JSBoundFunctionRef function = target_ref.AsJSBoundFunction();
4588 ObjectRef bound_this = function.bound_this(broker());
4589 ConvertReceiverMode const convert_mode =
4590 bound_this.IsNullOrUndefined()
4591 ? ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined
4592 : ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined;
4593
4594 // TODO(jgruber): Inline this block below once TryGet is guaranteed to
4595 // succeed.
4596 FixedArrayRef bound_arguments = function.bound_arguments(broker());
4597 const uint32_t bound_arguments_length = bound_arguments.length();
4598 if (arity + bound_arguments_length > Code::kMaxArguments) {
4599 return NoChange();
4600 }
4601 static constexpr int kInlineSize = 16; // Arbitrary.
4602 base::SmallVector<Node*, kInlineSize> args;
4603 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < bound_arguments_length; ++i) {
4604 OptionalObjectRef maybe_arg = bound_arguments.TryGet(broker(), i);
4605 if (!maybe_arg.has_value()) {
4606 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(broker(), "bound argument");
4607 return NoChange();
4608 }
4609 args.emplace_back(
4610 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(maybe_arg.value(), broker()));
4611 }
4612
4613 // Patch {node} to use [[BoundTargetFunction]] and [[BoundThis]].
4614 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(
4615 node,
4616 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(function.bound_target_function(broker()),
4617 broker()),
4618 JSCallNode::TargetIndex());
4619 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(
4620 node, jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(bound_this, broker()),
4621 JSCallNode::ReceiverIndex());
4622
4623 // Insert the [[BoundArguments]] for {node}.
4624 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < bound_arguments_length; ++i) {
4625 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), i + 2, args[i]);
4626 arity++;
4627 }
4628
4629 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
4630 node,
4631 javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(arity), p.frequency(),
4632 p.feedback(), convert_mode, p.speculation_mode(),
4633 CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated));
4634
4635 // Try to further reduce the JSCall {node}.
4636 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCall(node));
4637 }
4638
4639 // Don't mess with other {node}s that have a constant {target}.
4640 // TODO(bmeurer): Also support proxies here.
4641 return NoChange();
4642 }
4643
4644 // If {target} is the result of a JSCreateClosure operation, we can
4645 // just immediately try to inline based on the SharedFunctionInfo,
4646 // since TurboFan generally doesn't inline cross-context, and hence
4647 // the {target} must have the same native context as the call site.
4648 // Same if the {target} is the result of a CheckClosure operation.
4649 if (target->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCreateClosure) {
4650 CreateClosureParameters const& params =
4651 JSCreateClosureNode{target}.Parameters();
4652 return ReduceJSCall(node, params.shared_info());
4653 } else if (target->opcode() == IrOpcode::kCheckClosure) {
4654 FeedbackCellRef cell = MakeRef(broker(), FeedbackCellOf(target->op()));
4655 OptionalSharedFunctionInfoRef shared = cell.shared_function_info(broker());
4656 if (!shared.has_value()) {
4657 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(broker(), "Unable to reduce JSCall. FeedbackCell "
4658 << cell << " has no FeedbackVector");
4659 return NoChange();
4660 }
4661 return ReduceJSCall(node, *shared);
4662 }
4663
4664 // If {target} is the result of a JSCreateBoundFunction operation,
4665 // we can just fold the construction and call the bound target
4666 // function directly instead.
4667 if (target->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCreateBoundFunction) {
4668 Node* bound_target_function = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(target, 0);
4669 Node* bound_this = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(target, 1);
4670 uint32_t const bound_arguments_length =
4671 static_cast<int>(CreateBoundFunctionParametersOf(target->op()).arity());
4672
4673 // Patch the {node} to use [[BoundTargetFunction]] and [[BoundThis]].
4674 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, bound_target_function,
4675 n.TargetIndex());
4676 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, bound_this, n.ReceiverIndex());
4677
4678 // Insert the [[BoundArguments]] for {node}.
4679 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < bound_arguments_length; ++i) {
4680 Node* value = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(target, 2 + i);
4681 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), n.ArgumentIndex(i), value);
4682 arity++;
4683 }
4684
4685 // Update the JSCall operator on {node}.
4686 ConvertReceiverMode const convert_mode =
4687 NodeProperties::CanBeNullOrUndefined(broker(), bound_this, effect)
4688 ? ConvertReceiverMode::kAny
4689 : ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined;
4690 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
4691 node,
4692 javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(arity), p.frequency(),
4693 p.feedback(), convert_mode, p.speculation_mode(),
4694 CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated));
4695
4696 // Try to further reduce the JSCall {node}.
4697 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCall(node));
4698 }
4699
4700 if (!ShouldUseCallICFeedback(target) ||
4701 p.feedback_relation() == CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated ||
4702 !p.feedback().IsValid()) {
4703 return NoChange();
4704 }
4705
4706 ProcessedFeedback const& feedback =
4707 broker()->GetFeedbackForCall(p.feedback());
4708 if (feedback.IsInsufficient()) {
4709 return ReduceForInsufficientFeedback(
4710 node, DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForCall);
4711 }
4712
4713 OptionalHeapObjectRef feedback_target;
4714 if (p.feedback_relation() == CallFeedbackRelation::kTarget) {
4715 feedback_target = feedback.AsCall().target();
4716 } else {
4717 DCHECK_EQ(p.feedback_relation(), CallFeedbackRelation::kReceiver);
4718 feedback_target = native_context().function_prototype_apply(broker());
4719 }
4720
4721 if (feedback_target.has_value() &&
4722 feedback_target->map(broker()).is_callable()) {
4723 Node* target_function =
4724 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(*feedback_target, broker());
4725
4726 // Check that the {target} is still the {target_function}.
4727 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), target,
4728 target_function);
4729 effect = graph()->NewNode(
4730 simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongCallTarget), check,
4731 effect, control);
4732
4733 // Specialize the JSCall node to the {target_function}.
4734 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, target_function, n.TargetIndex());
4735 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
4736
4737 // Try to further reduce the JSCall {node}.
4738 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCall(node));
4739 } else if (feedback_target.has_value() && feedback_target->IsFeedbackCell()) {
4740 FeedbackCellRef feedback_cell = feedback_target.value().AsFeedbackCell();
4741 // TODO(neis): This check seems unnecessary.
4742 if (feedback_cell.feedback_vector(broker()).has_value()) {
4743 // Check that {target} is a closure with given {feedback_cell},
4744 // which uniquely identifies a given function inside a native context.
4745 Node* target_closure = effect =
4746 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckClosure(feedback_cell.object()),
4747 target, effect, control);
4748
4749 // Specialize the JSCall node to the {target_closure}.
4750 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, target_closure, n.TargetIndex());
4751 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
4752
4753 // Try to further reduce the JSCall {node}.
4754 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCall(node));
4755 }
4756 }
4757 return NoChange();
4758}
4759
4760Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceJSCall(Node* node,
4761 SharedFunctionInfoRef shared) {
4762 JSCallNode n(node);
4763 Node* target = n.target();
4764
4765 // Do not reduce calls to functions with break points.
4766 // If this state changes during background compilation, the compilation
4767 // job will be aborted from the main thread (see
4768 // Debug::PrepareFunctionForDebugExecution()).
4769 if (shared.HasBreakInfo(broker())) return NoChange();
4770
4771 // Class constructors are callable, but [[Call]] will raise an exception.
4772 // See ES6 section 9.2.1 [[Call]] ( thisArgument, argumentsList ).
4773 if (IsClassConstructor(shared.kind())) {
4774 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInputs(node, target);
4775 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
4776 node, javascript()->CallRuntime(
4777 Runtime::kThrowConstructorNonCallableError, 1));

4779 }

5151 return ReduceCallApiFunction(node, shared);
5152 }

5156 // Peek at the trusted object; ReduceCallWasmFunction will do that again
5157 // and crash if this is not a WasmExportedFunctionData any more then.
5158 IsWasmExportedFunctionData(shared.object()->GetTrustedData())) {
5159 return ReduceCallWasmFunction(node, shared);
5160 }
5161#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5162
5163 return NoChange();
5164}
5165
5166TNode<Object> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceJSCallWithArrayLikeOrSpreadOfEmpty(
5167 std::unordered_set<Node*>* generated_calls_with_array_like_or_spread) {
5168 DCHECK_EQ(generated_calls_with_array_like_or_spread->count(node_ptr()), 0);
5169 JSCallWithArrayLikeOrSpreadNode n(node_ptr());
5170 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
5171 TNode<Object> arguments_list = n.LastArgument();
5172 DCHECK_EQ(static_cast<Node*>(arguments_list)->opcode(),
5173 IrOpcode::kJSCreateEmptyLiteralArray);
5174
5175 // Check that arguments_list's prototype is still an array prototype.
5176 TNode<Map> map = LoadMap(TNode<HeapObject>::UncheckedCast(arguments_list));
5177 TNode<HeapObject> proto = TNode<HeapObject>::UncheckedCast(
5178 LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapPrototype(), map));
5179 TNode<HeapObject> initial_array_prototype =
5180 HeapConstant(broker()
5181 ->target_native_context()
5182 .initial_array_prototype(broker())
5183 .object());
5184 TNode<Boolean> check = ReferenceEqual(proto, initial_array_prototype);
5185 CheckIf(check, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap, p.feedback());
5186
5187 // Turn the JSCallWithArrayLike or JSCallWithSpread roughly into:
5188 //
5189 // "arguments_list array is still empty?"
5190 // |
5191 // |
5192 // Branch
5193 // / \
5194 // / \
5195 // IfTrue IfFalse
5196 // | |
5197 // | |
5198 // JSCall JSCallWithArrayLike/JSCallWithSpread
5199 // \ /
5200 // \ /
5201 // Merge
5202
5203 TNode<Number> length = TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(
5204 LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(NO_ELEMENTS), arguments_list));
5205 return SelectIf<Object>(NumberEqual(length, ZeroConstant()))
5206 .Then([&]() {
5207 TNode<Object> call = CopyNode();
5208 static_cast<Node*>(call)->RemoveInput(n.LastArgumentIndex());
5209 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
5210 call, javascript()->Call(p.arity() - 1, p.frequency(), p.feedback(),
5211 p.convert_mode(), p.speculation_mode(),
5212 p.feedback_relation()));
5213 return call;
5214 })
5215 .Else([&]() {
5216 TNode<Object> call = CopyNode();
5217 generated_calls_with_array_like_or_spread->insert(call);
5218 return call;
5219 })
5220 .ExpectFalse()
5221 .Value();
5222}
5223
5224namespace {
5225
5226// Check if the target is a class constructor.
5227// We need to check all cases where the target will be typed as Function
5228// to prevent later optimizations from using the CallFunction trampoline,
5229// skipping the instance type check.
5230bool TargetIsClassConstructor(Node* node, JSHeapBroker* broker) {
5231 Node* target = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
5232 OptionalSharedFunctionInfoRef shared;
5233 HeapObjectMatcher m(target);
5234 if (m.HasResolvedValue()) {
5235 ObjectRef target_ref = m.Ref(broker);
5236 if (target_ref.IsJSFunction()) {
5237 JSFunctionRef function = target_ref.AsJSFunction();
5238 shared = function.shared(broker);
5239 }
5240 } else if (target->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCreateClosure) {
5241 CreateClosureParameters const& ccp =
5242 JSCreateClosureNode{target}.Parameters();
5243 shared = ccp.shared_info();
5244 } else if (target->opcode() == IrOpcode::kCheckClosure) {
5245 FeedbackCellRef cell = MakeRef(broker, FeedbackCellOf(target->op()));
5246 shared = cell.shared_function_info(broker);
5247 }
5248
5249 if (shared.has_value() && IsClassConstructor(shared->kind())) return true;
5250
5251 return false;
5252}
5253
5254} // namespace
5255
5256Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceJSCallWithArrayLike(Node* node) {
5257 JSCallWithArrayLikeNode n(node);
5258 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
5259 DCHECK_EQ(p.arity_without_implicit_args(), 1); // The arraylike object.
5260 // Class constructors are callable, but [[Call]] will raise an exception.
5261 // See ES6 section 9.2.1 [[Call]] ( thisArgument, argumentsList ).
5262 if (TargetIsClassConstructor(node, broker())) {
5263 return NoChange();
5264 }
5265
5266 std::optional<Reduction> maybe_result =
5267 TryReduceJSCallMathMinMaxWithArrayLike(node);
5268 if (maybe_result.has_value()) {
5269 return maybe_result.value();
5270 }
5271
5272 return ReduceCallOrConstructWithArrayLikeOrSpread(
5273 node, n.ArgumentCount(), n.LastArgumentIndex(), p.frequency(),
5274 p.feedback(), p.speculation_mode(), p.feedback_relation(), n.target(),
5275 n.effect(), n.control());
5276}
5277
5278Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceJSCallWithSpread(Node* node) {
5279 JSCallWithSpreadNode n(node);
5280 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
5281 DCHECK_GE(p.arity_without_implicit_args(), 1); // At least the spread.
5282 // Class constructors are callable, but [[Call]] will raise an exception.
5283 // See ES6 section 9.2.1 [[Call]] ( thisArgument, argumentsList ).
5284 if (TargetIsClassConstructor(node, broker())) {
5285 return NoChange();
5286 }
5287 return ReduceCallOrConstructWithArrayLikeOrSpread(
5288 node, n.ArgumentCount(), n.LastArgumentIndex(), p.frequency(),
5289 p.feedback(), p.speculation_mode(), p.feedback_relation(), n.target(),
5290 n.effect(), n.control());
5291}
5292
5293Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceJSConstruct(Node* node) {
5294 if (broker()->StackHasOverflowed()) return NoChange();
5295
5296 JSConstructNode n(node);
5297 ConstructParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
5298 int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
5299 Node* target = n.target();
5300 Node* new_target = n.new_target();
5301 Effect effect = n.effect();
5302 Control control = n.control();
5303
5304 if (p.feedback().IsValid()) {
5305 ProcessedFeedback const& feedback =
5306 broker()->GetFeedbackForCall(p.feedback());
5307 if (feedback.IsInsufficient()) {
5308 return ReduceForInsufficientFeedback(
5309 node, DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForConstruct);
5310 }
5311
5312 OptionalHeapObjectRef feedback_target = feedback.AsCall().target();
5313 if (feedback_target.has_value() && feedback_target->IsAllocationSite()) {
5314 // The feedback is an AllocationSite, which means we have called the
5315 // Array function and collected transition (and pretenuring) feedback
5316 // for the resulting arrays. This has to be kept in sync with the
5317 // implementation in Ignition.
5318
5319 Node* array_function = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
5320 native_context().array_function(broker()), broker());
5321
5322 // Check that the {target} is still the {array_function}.
5323 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), target,
5324 array_function);
5325 effect = graph()->NewNode(
5326 simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongCallTarget), check,
5327 effect, control);
5328
5329 // Turn the {node} into a {JSCreateArray} call.
5330 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
5331 static_assert(JSConstructNode::NewTargetIndex() == 1);
5332 node->ReplaceInput(n.NewTargetIndex(), array_function);
5333 node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
5334 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
5335 node, javascript()->CreateArray(arity,
5336 feedback_target->AsAllocationSite()));
5337 return Changed(node);
5338 } else if (feedback_target.has_value() &&
5339 !HeapObjectMatcher(new_target).HasResolvedValue() &&
5340 feedback_target->map(broker()).is_constructor()) {
5341 Node* new_target_feedback =
5342 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(*feedback_target, broker());
5343
5344 // Check that the {new_target} is still the {new_target_feedback}.
5345 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), new_target,
5346 new_target_feedback);
5347 effect = graph()->NewNode(
5348 simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongCallTarget), check,
5349 effect, control);
5350
5351 // Specialize the JSConstruct node to the {new_target_feedback}.
5352 node->ReplaceInput(n.NewTargetIndex(), new_target_feedback);
5353 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
5354 if (target == new_target) {
5355 node->ReplaceInput(n.TargetIndex(), new_target_feedback);
5356 }
5357
5358 // Try to further reduce the JSConstruct {node}.
5359 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSConstruct(node));
5360 }
5361 }
5362
5363 // Try to specialize JSConstruct {node}s with constant {target}s.
5364 HeapObjectMatcher m(target);
5365 if (m.HasResolvedValue()) {
5366 HeapObjectRef target_ref = m.Ref(broker());
5367
5368 // Raise a TypeError if the {target} is not a constructor.
5369 if (!target_ref.map(broker()).is_constructor()) {
5370 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInputs(node, target);
5371 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node,
5372 javascript()->CallRuntime(
5373 Runtime::kThrowConstructedNonConstructable));
5374 return Changed(node);
5375 }
5376
5377 if (target_ref.IsJSFunction()) {
5378 JSFunctionRef function = target_ref.AsJSFunction();
5379
5380 // Do not reduce constructors with break points.
5381 // If this state changes during background compilation, the compilation
5382 // job will be aborted from the main thread (see
5383 // Debug::PrepareFunctionForDebugExecution()).
5384 SharedFunctionInfoRef sfi = function.shared(broker());
5385 if (sfi.HasBreakInfo(broker())) return NoChange();
5386
5387 // Don't inline cross native context.
5388 if (!function.native_context(broker()).equals(native_context())) {
5389 return NoChange();
5390 }
5391
5392 // Check for known builtin functions.
5393 Builtin builtin =
5394 sfi.HasBuiltinId() ? sfi.builtin_id() : Builtin::kNoBuiltinId;
5395 switch (builtin) {
5396 case Builtin::kArrayConstructor: {
5397 // TODO(bmeurer): Deal with Array subclasses here.
5398 // Turn the {node} into a {JSCreateArray} call.
5399 static_assert(JSConstructNode::NewTargetIndex() == 1);
5400 node->ReplaceInput(n.NewTargetIndex(), new_target);
5401 node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
5402 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
5403 node, javascript()->CreateArray(arity, std::nullopt));
5404 return Changed(node);
5405 }
5406 case Builtin::kObjectConstructor: {
5407 // If no value is passed, we can immediately lower to a simple
5408 // JSCreate and don't need to do any massaging of the {node}.
5409 if (arity == 0) {
5410 node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
5411 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->Create());
5412 return Changed(node);
5413 }
5414
5415 // If {target} is not the same as {new_target} (i.e. the Object
5416 // constructor), {value} will be ignored and therefore we can lower
5417 // to {JSCreate}. See https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-object-value.
5418 HeapObjectMatcher mnew_target(new_target);
5419 if (mnew_target.HasResolvedValue() &&
5420 !mnew_target.Ref(broker()).equals(function)) {
5421 // Drop the value inputs.
5422 node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
5423 for (int i = n.ArgumentCount() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
5424 node->RemoveInput(n.ArgumentIndex(i));
5425 }
5426 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->Create());
5427 return Changed(node);
5428 }
5429 break;
5430 }
5431 case Builtin::kPromiseConstructor:
5432 return ReducePromiseConstructor(node);
5433 case Builtin::kStringConstructor:
5434 return ReduceStringConstructor(node, function);
5435 case Builtin::kTypedArrayConstructor:
5436 return ReduceTypedArrayConstructor(node, function.shared(broker()));
5437 default:
5438 break;
5439 }
5440 } else if (target_ref.IsJSBoundFunction()) {
5441 JSBoundFunctionRef function = target_ref.AsJSBoundFunction();
5442 JSReceiverRef bound_target_function =
5443 function.bound_target_function(broker());
5444 FixedArrayRef bound_arguments = function.bound_arguments(broker());
5445 const uint32_t bound_arguments_length = bound_arguments.length();
5446
5447 // TODO(jgruber): Inline this block below once TryGet is guaranteed to
5448 // succeed.
5449 static constexpr int kInlineSize = 16; // Arbitrary.
5450 base::SmallVector<Node*, kInlineSize> args;
5451 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < bound_arguments_length; ++i) {
5452 OptionalObjectRef maybe_arg = bound_arguments.TryGet(broker(), i);
5453 if (!maybe_arg.has_value()) {
5454 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(broker(), "bound argument");
5455 return NoChange();
5456 }
5457 args.emplace_back(
5458 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(maybe_arg.value(), broker()));
5459 }
5460
5461 // Patch {node} to use [[BoundTargetFunction]].
5462 node->ReplaceInput(n.TargetIndex(), jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
5463 bound_target_function, broker()));
5464
5465 // Patch {node} to use [[BoundTargetFunction]]
5466 // as new.target if {new_target} equals {target}.
5467 if (target == new_target) {
5468 node->ReplaceInput(
5469 n.NewTargetIndex(),
5470 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(bound_target_function, broker()));
5471 } else {
5472 node->ReplaceInput(
5473 n.NewTargetIndex(),
5474 graph()->NewNode(
5475 common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kTagged),
5476 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), target,
5477 new_target),
5478 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(bound_target_function, broker()),
5479 new_target));
5480 }
5481
5482 // Insert the [[BoundArguments]] for {node}.
5483 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < bound_arguments_length; ++i) {
5484 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), n.ArgumentIndex(i), args[i]);
5485 arity++;
5486 }
5487
5488 // Update the JSConstruct operator on {node}.
5489 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
5490 node, javascript()->Construct(JSConstructNode::ArityForArgc(arity),
5491 p.frequency(), FeedbackSource()));
5492
5493 // Try to further reduce the JSConstruct {node}.
5494 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSConstruct(node));
5495 }
5496
5497 // TODO(bmeurer): Also support optimizing proxies here.
5498 }
5499
5500 // If {target} is the result of a JSCreateBoundFunction operation,
5501 // we can just fold the construction and construct the bound target
5502 // function directly instead.
5503 if (target->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCreateBoundFunction) {
5504 Node* bound_target_function = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(target, 0);
5505 uint32_t const bound_arguments_length =
5506 static_cast<int>(CreateBoundFunctionParametersOf(target->op()).arity());
5507
5508 // Patch the {node} to use [[BoundTargetFunction]].
5509 node->ReplaceInput(n.TargetIndex(), bound_target_function);
5510
5511 // Patch {node} to use [[BoundTargetFunction]]
5512 // as new.target if {new_target} equals {target}.
5513 if (target == new_target) {
5514 node->ReplaceInput(n.NewTargetIndex(), bound_target_function);
5515 } else {
5516 node->ReplaceInput(
5517 n.NewTargetIndex(),
5518 graph()->NewNode(common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kTagged),
5519 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(),
5520 target, new_target),
5521 bound_target_function, new_target));
5522 }
5523
5524 // Insert the [[BoundArguments]] for {node}.
5525 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < bound_arguments_length; ++i) {
5526 Node* value = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(target, 2 + i);
5527 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), n.ArgumentIndex(i), value);
5528 arity++;
5529 }
5530
5531 // Update the JSConstruct operator on {node}.
5532 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
5533 node, javascript()->Construct(JSConstructNode::ArityForArgc(arity),
5534 p.frequency(), FeedbackSource()));
5535
5536 // Try to further reduce the JSConstruct {node}.
5537 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSConstruct(node));
5538 }
5539
5540 return NoChange();
5541}
5542
5543// ES #sec-string.prototype.indexof
5544// ES #sec-string.prototype.includes
5545Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeIndexOfIncludes(
5546 Node* node, StringIndexOfIncludesVariant variant) {
5547 JSCallNode n(node);
5548 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
5549 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
5550 return NoChange();
5551 }
5552
5553 Effect effect = n.effect();
5554 Control control = n.control();
5555 if (n.ArgumentCount() > 0) {
5556 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
5557 Node* new_receiver = effect = graph()->NewNode(
5558 simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()), receiver, effect, control);
5559
5560 Node* search_string = n.Argument(0);
5561 Node* new_search_string = effect =
5562 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()), search_string,
5563 effect, control);
5564
5565 Node* new_position = jsgraph()->ZeroConstant();
5566 if (n.ArgumentCount() > 1) {
5567 Node* position = n.Argument(1);
5568 new_position = effect = graph()->NewNode(
5569 simplified()->CheckSmi(p.feedback()), position, effect, control);
5570
5571 Node* receiver_length =
5572 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringLength(), new_receiver);
5573 new_position = graph()->NewNode(
5574 simplified()->NumberMin(),
5575 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberMax(), new_position,
5576 jsgraph()->ZeroConstant()),
5577 receiver_length);
5578 }
5579
5580 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
5581 RelaxEffectsAndControls(node);
5582 node->ReplaceInput(0, new_receiver);
5583 node->ReplaceInput(1, new_search_string);
5584 node->ReplaceInput(2, new_position);
5585 node->TrimInputCount(3);
5586 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, simplified()->StringIndexOf());
5587
5588 if (variant == StringIndexOfIncludesVariant::kIndexOf) {
5589 return Changed(node);
5590 } else {
5591 DCHECK(variant == StringIndexOfIncludesVariant::kIncludes);
5592 Node* result =
5593 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->BooleanNot(),
5594 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(), node,
5595 jsgraph()->SmiConstant(-1)));
5596 return Replace(result);
5597 }
5598 }
5599 return NoChange();
5600}
5601

5603Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeSubstring(Node* node) {
5604 JSCallNode n(node);
5605 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
5606 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) return NoChange();
5607 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
5608 return NoChange();
5609 }
5610
5611 JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node);
5612 Node* subgraph = a.ReduceStringPrototypeSubstring();
5613 return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
5614}

5621 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
5622 return NoChange();

5629
5630// ES #sec-string.prototype.substr
5631Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeSubstr(Node* node) {
5632 JSCallNode n(node);
5633 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
5634 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) return NoChange();
5635 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
5636 return NoChange();
5637 }
5638
5639 Effect effect = n.effect();
5640 Control control = n.control();
5641 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
5642 Node* start = n.Argument(0);
5643 Node* end = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph());
5644
5645 receiver = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()),
5646 receiver, effect, control);
5647
5648 start = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckSmi(p.feedback()), start,
5649 effect, control);
5650
5651 Node* length = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringLength(), receiver);
5652
5653 // Replace {end} argument with {length} if it is undefined.
5654 {
5655 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), end,
5656 jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
5657 Node* branch =
5658 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse), check, control);
5659
5660 Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
5661 Node* etrue = effect;
5662 Node* vtrue = length;
5663
5664 Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
5665 Node* efalse = effect;
5666 Node* vfalse = efalse = graph()->NewNode(
5667 simplified()->CheckSmi(p.feedback()), end, efalse, if_false);
5668
5669 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
5670 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
5671 end = graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
5672 vtrue, vfalse, control);
5673 }
5674
5675 Node* initStart = graph()->NewNode(
5676 common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, BranchHint::kFalse),
5677 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThan(), start,
5678 jsgraph()->ZeroConstant()),
5679 graph()->NewNode(
5680 simplified()->NumberMax(),
5681 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), length, start),
5682 jsgraph()->ZeroConstant()),
5683 start);
5684 // The select above guarantees that initStart is non-negative, but
5685 // our typer can't figure that out yet.
5686 initStart = effect = graph()->NewNode(
5687 common()->TypeGuard(Type::UnsignedSmall()), initStart, effect, control);
5688
5689 Node* resultLength = graph()->NewNode(
5690 simplified()->NumberMin(),
5691 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberMax(), end,
5692 jsgraph()->ZeroConstant()),
5693 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberSubtract(), length, initStart));
5694
5695 // The the select below uses {resultLength} only if {resultLength > 0},
5696 // but our typer can't figure that out yet.
5697 Node* to = effect = graph()->NewNode(
5698 common()->TypeGuard(Type::UnsignedSmall()),
5699 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), initStart, resultLength),
5700 effect, control);
5701
5702 Node* result_string = nullptr;
5703 // Return empty string if {from} is smaller than {to}.
5704 {
5705 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThan(),
5706 jsgraph()->ZeroConstant(), resultLength);
5707
5708 Node* branch =
5709 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check, control);
5710
5711 Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
5712 Node* etrue = effect;
5713 Node* vtrue = etrue =
5714 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringSubstring(), receiver, initStart,
5715 to, etrue, if_true);
5716
5717 Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
5718 Node* efalse = effect;
5719 Node* vfalse = jsgraph()->EmptyStringConstant();
5720
5721 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
5722 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
5723 result_string =
5724 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
5725 vtrue, vfalse, control);
5726 }
5727
5728 ReplaceWithValue(node, result_string, effect, control);
5729 return Replace(result_string);
5730}

5732Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceJSConstructWithArrayLike(Node* node) {
5733 JSConstructWithArrayLikeNode n(node);
5734 ConstructParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
5735 const int arraylike_index = n.LastArgumentIndex();
5736 DCHECK_EQ(n.ArgumentCount(), 1); // The arraylike object.
5737 return ReduceCallOrConstructWithArrayLikeOrSpread(
5738 node, n.ArgumentCount(), arraylike_index, p.frequency(), p.feedback(),
5739 SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation, CallFeedbackRelation::kTarget,
5740 n.target(), n.effect(), n.control());
5741}
