5743Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceJSConstructWithSpread(Node* node) {
5744 JSConstructWithSpreadNode n(node);
5745 ConstructParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
5746 const int spread_index = n.LastArgumentIndex();
5747 DCHECK_GE(n.ArgumentCount(), 1); // At least the spread.
5748 return ReduceCallOrConstructWithArrayLikeOrSpread(
5749 node, n.ArgumentCount(), spread_index, p.frequency(), p.feedback(),
5750 SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation, CallFeedbackRelation::kTarget,
5751 n.target(), n.effect(), n.control());
5752}
5753
5754Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceJSConstructForwardAllArgs(Node* node) {
5755 JSConstructForwardAllArgsNode n(node);
5756 DCHECK_EQ(n.ArgumentCount(), 0);
5757
5758 // If this frame is not being inlined, JSConstructForwardAllArgs will be
5759 // lowered later in JSGenericLowering to a builtin call.
5760 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
5761 if (frame_state.outer_frame_state()->opcode() != IrOpcode::kFrameState) {
5762 return NoChange();
5763 }
5764
5765 // Hook up the arguments directly when forwarding arguments of inlined frames.
5766 FrameState outer_state{frame_state.outer_frame_state()};
5767 FrameStateInfo outer_info = outer_state.frame_state_info();
5768 if (outer_info.type() == FrameStateType::kInlinedExtraArguments) {
5769 frame_state = outer_state;
5770 }
5771
5772 int argc = 0;
5773 StateValuesAccess parameters_access(frame_state.parameters());
5774 for (auto it = parameters_access.begin_without_receiver(); !it.done(); ++it) {
5775 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(it.node());
5776 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(),
5777 JSCallOrConstructNode::ArgumentIndex(argc++), it.node());
5778 }
5779
5780 ConstructParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
5781 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
5782 node, javascript()->Construct(JSConstructNode::ArityForArgc(argc),
5783 p.frequency(), p.feedback()));
5784 CheckIfConstructor(node);
5785 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSConstruct(node));
5786}
5787
5788Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceReturnReceiver(Node* node) {
5789 JSCallNode n(node);
5790 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
5791 ReplaceWithValue(node, receiver);
5792 return Replace(receiver);
5793}
5794
5795Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceForInsufficientFeedback(
5796 Node* node, DeoptimizeReason reason) {
5797 DCHECK(node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCall ||
5798 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSConstruct);
5799 if (!(flags() & kBailoutOnUninitialized)) return NoChange();
5800
5801 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
5802 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
5803 Node* frame_state =
5804 NodeProperties::FindFrameStateBefore(node, jsgraph()->Dead());
5805 Node* deoptimize =
5806 graph()->NewNode(common()->Deoptimize(reason, FeedbackSource()),
5807 frame_state, effect, control);
5808 MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), deoptimize);
5809 node->TrimInputCount(0);
5810 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, common()->Dead());
5811 return Changed(node);
5812}
5813
5814Node* JSCallReducer::LoadReceiverElementsKind(Node* receiver, Effect* effect,
5815 Control control) {
5816 Node* effect_node = *effect;
5817 Node* receiver_map = effect_node =
5818 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap()),
5819 receiver, effect_node, control);
5820 Node* receiver_bit_field2 = effect_node = graph()->NewNode(
5821 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField2()), receiver_map,
5822 effect_node, control);
5823 Node* receiver_elements_kind = graph()->NewNode(
5824 simplified()->NumberShiftRightLogical(),
5825 graph()->NewNode(
5826 simplified()->NumberBitwiseAnd(), receiver_bit_field2,
5827 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kMask)),
5828 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kShift));
5829 *effect = effect_node;
5830 return receiver_elements_kind;
5831}
5832
5833void JSCallReducer::CheckIfElementsKind(Node* receiver_elements_kind,
5834 ElementsKind kind, Node* control,
5835 Node** if_true, Node** if_false) {
5836 Node* is_packed_kind =
5837 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(), receiver_elements_kind,
5838 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(GetPackedElementsKind(kind)));
5839 Node* packed_branch =
5840 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), is_packed_kind, control);
5841 Node* if_packed = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), packed_branch);
5842
5843 if (IsHoleyElementsKind(kind)) {
5844 Node* if_not_packed = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), packed_branch);
5845 Node* is_holey_kind =
5846 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(), receiver_elements_kind,
5847 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(GetHoleyElementsKind(kind)));
5848 Node* holey_branch =
5849 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), is_holey_kind, if_not_packed);
5850 Node* if_holey = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), holey_branch);
5851
5852 Node* if_not_packed_not_holey =
5853 graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), holey_branch);
5854
5855 *if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_packed, if_holey);
5856 *if_false = if_not_packed_not_holey;
5857 } else {
5858 *if_true = if_packed;
5859 *if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), packed_branch);
5860 }
5861}
5862
5863// ES6 section 23.1.3.1 Array.prototype.at ( )
5864Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayPrototypeAt(Node* node) {
5865 if (!v8_flags.turbo_inline_array_builtins) return NoChange();
5866
5867 JSCallNode n(node);
5868 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
5869 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
5870 return NoChange();
5871 }
5872
5873 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
5874 Effect effect = n.effect();
5875 Control control = n.control();
5876
5877 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
5878 if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
5879
5880 // Collecting maps, and checking if a fallback builtin call will be required
5881 // (it is required if at least one map doesn't support fast array iteration).
5882 ZoneVector<MapRef> maps(broker()->zone());
5883 bool needs_fallback_builtin_call = false;
5884 for (MapRef map : inference.GetMaps()) {
5885 if (map.supports_fast_array_iteration(broker())) {
5886 maps.push_back(map);
5887 } else {
5888 needs_fallback_builtin_call = true;
5889 }
5890 }
5891
5892 inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
5893 control, p.feedback());
5894
5895 if (maps.empty()) {
5896 // No map in the feedback supports fast iteration. Keeping the builtin call.
5897 return NoChange();
5898 }
5899
5900 if (!dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
5901 return NoChange();
5902 }
5903
5904 IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler a(this, node);
5905 a.InitializeEffectControl(effect, control);
5906
5907 TNode<Object> subgraph =
5908 a.ReduceArrayPrototypeAt(maps, needs_fallback_builtin_call);
5909 return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
5910}
5911
5912// ES6 section 22.1.3.18 Array.prototype.push ( )
5913Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayPrototypePush(Node* node) {
5914 JSCallNode n(node);
5915 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
5916 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
5917 return NoChange();
5918 }
5919
5920 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
5921 Effect effect = n.effect();
5922 Control control = n.control();
5923
5924 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
5925 if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
5926 ZoneRefSet<Map> const& receiver_maps = inference.GetMaps();
5927
5928 std::vector<ElementsKind> kinds;
5929 if (!CanInlineArrayResizingBuiltin(broker(), receiver_maps, &kinds, true)) {
5930 return inference.NoChange();
5931 }
5932 if (!dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
5933 return inference.NoChange();
5934 }
5935
5936 inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
5937 control, p.feedback());
5938
5939 IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler a(this, node);
5940 a.InitializeEffectControl(effect, control);
5941
5942 TNode<Object> subgraph = a.ReduceArrayPrototypePush(&inference);
5943 return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
5944}
5945
5946// ES6 section 22.1.3.17 Array.prototype.pop ( )
5947Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayPrototypePop(Node* node) {
5948 JSCallNode n(node);
5949 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
5950 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
5951 return NoChange();
5952 }
5953
5954 Effect effect = n.effect();
5955 Control control = n.control();
5956 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
5957
5958 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
5959 if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
5960 ZoneRefSet<Map> const& receiver_maps = inference.GetMaps();
5961
5962 std::vector<ElementsKind> kinds;
5963 if (!CanInlineArrayResizingBuiltin(broker(), receiver_maps, &kinds)) {
5964 return inference.NoChange();
5965 }
5966 if (!dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
5967 return inference.NoChange();
5968 }
5969 inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
5970 control, p.feedback());
5971
5972 std::vector<Node*> controls_to_merge;
5973 std::vector<Node*> effects_to_merge;
5974 std::vector<Node*> values_to_merge;
5975 Node* value = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
5976
5977 Node* receiver_elements_kind =
5978 LoadReceiverElementsKind(receiver, &effect, control);
5979 Node* next_control = control;
5980 Node* next_effect = effect;
5981 for (size_t i = 0; i < kinds.size(); i++) {
5982 ElementsKind kind = kinds[i];
5983 control = next_control;
5984 effect = next_effect;
5985 // We do not need branch for the last elements kind.
5986 if (i != kinds.size() - 1) {
5987 Node* control_node = control;
5988 CheckIfElementsKind(receiver_elements_kind, kind, control_node,
5989 &control_node, &next_control);
5990 control = control_node;
5991 }
5992
5993 // Load the "length" property of the {receiver}.
5994 Node* length = effect = graph()->NewNode(
5995 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(kind)),
5996 receiver, effect, control);
5997
5998 // Check if the {receiver} has any elements.
5999 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(), length,
6000 jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
6001 Node* branch =
6002 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse), check, control);
6003
6004 Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
6005 Node* etrue = effect;
6006 Node* vtrue = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
6007
6008 Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
6009 Node* efalse = effect;
6010 Node* vfalse;
6011 {
6012 // TODO(turbofan): We should trim the backing store if the capacity is too
6013 // big, as implemented in elements.cc:ElementsAccessorBase::SetLengthImpl.
6014
6015 // Load the elements backing store from the {receiver}.
6016 Node* elements = efalse = graph()->NewNode(
6017 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements()),
6018 receiver, efalse, if_false);
6019
6020 // Ensure that we aren't popping from a copy-on-write backing store.
6021 if (IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(kind)) {
6022 elements = efalse =
6023 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->EnsureWritableFastElements(),
6024 receiver, elements, efalse, if_false);
6025 }
6026
6027 // Compute the new {length}.
6028 Node* new_length = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberSubtract(),
6029 length, jsgraph()->OneConstant());
6030
6031 if (v8_flags.turbo_typer_hardening) {
6032 new_length = efalse = graph()->NewNode(
6033 simplified()->CheckBounds(p.feedback(),
6034 CheckBoundsFlag::kAbortOnOutOfBounds),
6035 new_length, length, efalse, if_false);
6036 }
6037
6038 // Store the new {length} to the {receiver}.
6039 efalse = graph()->NewNode(
6040 simplified()->StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(kind)),
6041 receiver, new_length, efalse, if_false);
6042
6043 // Load the last entry from the {elements}.
6044 vfalse = efalse = graph()->NewNode(
6045 simplified()->LoadElement(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(kind)),
6046 elements, new_length, efalse, if_false);
6047
6048 // Store a hole to the element we just removed from the {receiver}.
6049 efalse = graph()->NewNode(
6050 simplified()->StoreElement(
6051 AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(GetHoleyElementsKind(kind))),
6052 elements, new_length, jsgraph()->TheHoleConstant(), efalse, if_false);
6053 }
6054
6055 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
6056 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
6057 value = graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
6058 vtrue, vfalse, control);
6059
6060 // Convert the hole to undefined. Do this last, so that we can optimize
6061 // conversion operator via some smart strength reduction in many cases.
6062 if (IsHoleyElementsKind(kind)) {
6063 value =
6064 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ConvertTaggedHoleToUndefined(), value);
6065 }
6066
6067 controls_to_merge.push_back(control);
6068 effects_to_merge.push_back(effect);
6069 values_to_merge.push_back(value);
6070 }
6071
6072 if (controls_to_merge.size() > 1) {
6073 int const count = static_cast<int>(controls_to_merge.size());
6074
6075 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(count), count,
6076 &controls_to_merge.front());
6077 effects_to_merge.push_back(control);
6078 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(count), count + 1,
6079 &effects_to_merge.front());
6080 values_to_merge.push_back(control);
6081 value =
6082 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, count),
6083 count + 1, &values_to_merge.front());
6084 }
6085
6086 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
6087 return Replace(value);
6088}
6089
6090// ES6 section 22.1.3.22 Array.prototype.shift ( )
6091// Currently disabled. See https://crbug.com/v8/14409
6092Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayPrototypeShift(Node* node) {
6093 JSCallNode n(node);
6094 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6095 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
6096 return NoChange();
6097 }
6098
6099 Node* target = n.target();
6100 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
6101 Node* context = n.context();
6102 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
6103 Effect effect = n.effect();
6104 Control control = n.control();
6105
6106 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
6107 if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
6108 ZoneRefSet<Map> const& receiver_maps = inference.GetMaps();
6109
6110 std::vector<ElementsKind> kinds;
6111 if (!CanInlineArrayResizingBuiltin(broker(), receiver_maps, &kinds)) {
6112 return inference.NoChange();
6113 }
6114 if (!dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
6115 return inference.NoChange();
6116 }
6117 inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
6118 control, p.feedback());
6119
6120 std::vector<Node*> controls_to_merge;
6121 std::vector<Node*> effects_to_merge;
6122 std::vector<Node*> values_to_merge;
6123 Node* value = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
6124
6125 Node* receiver_elements_kind =
6126 LoadReceiverElementsKind(receiver, &effect, control);
6127 Node* next_control = control;
6128 Node* next_effect = effect;
6129 for (size_t i = 0; i < kinds.size(); i++) {
6130 ElementsKind kind = kinds[i];
6131 control = next_control;
6132 effect = next_effect;
6133 // We do not need branch for the last elements kind.
6134 if (i != kinds.size() - 1) {
6135 Node* control_node = control;
6136 CheckIfElementsKind(receiver_elements_kind, kind, control_node,
6137 &control_node, &next_control);
6138 control = control_node;
6139 }
6140
6141 // Load length of the {receiver}.
6142 Node* length = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6143 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(kind)),
6144 receiver, effect, control);
6145
6146 // Return undefined if {receiver} has no elements.
6147 Node* check0 = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(), length,
6148 jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
6149 Node* branch0 =
6150 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse), check0, control);
6151
6152 Node* if_true0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch0);
6153 Node* etrue0 = effect;
6154 Node* vtrue0 = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
6155
6156 Node* if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch0);
6157 Node* efalse0 = effect;
6158 Node* vfalse0;
6159 {
6160 // Check if we should take the fast-path.
6161 Node* check1 = graph()->NewNode(
6162 simplified()->NumberLessThanOrEqual(), length,
6163 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(JSArray::kMaxCopyElements));
6164 Node* branch1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue),
6165 check1, if_false0);
6166
6167 Node* if_true1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch1);
6168 Node* etrue1 = efalse0;
6169 Node* vtrue1;
6170 {
6171 Node* elements = etrue1 = graph()->NewNode(
6172 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements()),
6173 receiver, etrue1, if_true1);
6174
6175 // Load the first element here, which we return below.
6176 vtrue1 = etrue1 = graph()->NewNode(
6177 simplified()->LoadElement(
6178 AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(kind)),
6179 elements, jsgraph()->ZeroConstant(), etrue1, if_true1);
6180
6181 // Ensure that we aren't shifting a copy-on-write backing store.
6182 if (IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(kind)) {
6183 elements = etrue1 =
6184 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->EnsureWritableFastElements(),
6185 receiver, elements, etrue1, if_true1);
6186 }
6187
6188 // Shift the remaining {elements} by one towards the start.
6189 Node* loop = graph()->NewNode(common()->Loop(2), if_true1, if_true1);
6190 Node* eloop =
6191 graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue1, etrue1, loop);
6192 Node* terminate = graph()->NewNode(common()->Terminate(), eloop, loop);
6193 MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), terminate);
6194
6195 Node* index = graph()->NewNode(
6196 common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
6197 jsgraph()->OneConstant(),
6198 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(JSArray::kMaxCopyElements - 1), loop);
6199
6200 {
6201 Node* check2 =
6202 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThan(), index, length);
6203 Node* branch2 = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), check2, loop);
6204
6205 if_true1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch2);
6206 etrue1 = eloop;
6207
6208 Node* control2 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch2);
6209 Node* effect2 = etrue1;
6210
6211 ElementAccess const access =
6212 AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(kind);
6213
6214 // When disable v8_flags.turbo_loop_variable, typer cannot infer index
6215 // is in [1, kMaxCopyElements-1], and will break in representing
6216 // kRepFloat64 (Range(1, inf)) to kRepWord64 when converting
6217 // input for kLoadElement. So we need to add type guard here.
6218 // And we need to use index when using NumberLessThan to check
6219 // terminate and updating index, otherwise which will break inducing
6220 // variables in LoopVariableOptimizer.
6221 static_assert(JSArray::kMaxCopyElements < kSmiMaxValue);
6222 Node* index_retyped = effect2 =
6223 graph()->NewNode(common()->TypeGuard(Type::UnsignedSmall()),
6224 index, effect2, control2);
6225
6226 Node* value2 = effect2 =
6227 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadElement(access), elements,
6228 index_retyped, effect2, control2);
6229 effect2 = graph()->NewNode(
6230 simplified()->StoreElement(access), elements,
6231 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberSubtract(), index_retyped,
6232 jsgraph()->OneConstant()),
6233 value2, effect2, control2);
6234
6235 loop->ReplaceInput(1, control2);
6236 eloop->ReplaceInput(1, effect2);
6237 index->ReplaceInput(1,
6238 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), index,
6239 jsgraph()->OneConstant()));
6240 }
6241
6242 // Compute the new {length}.
6243 Node* new_length = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberSubtract(),
6244 length, jsgraph()->OneConstant());
6245
6246 if (v8_flags.turbo_typer_hardening) {
6247 new_length = etrue1 = graph()->NewNode(
6248 simplified()->CheckBounds(p.feedback(),
6249 CheckBoundsFlag::kAbortOnOutOfBounds),
6250 new_length, length, etrue1, if_true1);
6251 }
6252
6253 // Store the new {length} to the {receiver}.
6254 etrue1 = graph()->NewNode(
6255 simplified()->StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(kind)),
6256 receiver, new_length, etrue1, if_true1);
6257
6258 // Store a hole to the element we just removed from the {receiver}.
6259 etrue1 = graph()->NewNode(
6260 simplified()->StoreElement(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(
6261 GetHoleyElementsKind(kind))),
6262 elements, new_length, jsgraph()->TheHoleConstant(), etrue1,
6263 if_true1);
6264 }
6265
6266 Node* if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch1);
6267 Node* efalse1 = efalse0;
6268 Node* vfalse1;
6269 {
6270 // Call the generic C++ implementation.
6271 const Builtin builtin = Builtin::kArrayShift;
6272 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetCEntryStubCallDescriptor(
6273 graph()->zone(), 1, BuiltinArguments::kNumExtraArgsWithReceiver,
6274 Builtins::name(builtin), node->op()->properties(),
6275 CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState);
6276 const bool has_builtin_exit_frame = true;
6277 Node* stub_code = jsgraph()->CEntryStubConstant(1, ArgvMode::kStack,
6278 has_builtin_exit_frame);
6279 Address builtin_entry = Builtins::CppEntryOf(builtin);
6280 Node* entry = jsgraph()->ExternalConstant(
6281 ExternalReference::Create(builtin_entry));
6282 Node* argc = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
6283 BuiltinArguments::kNumExtraArgsWithReceiver);
6284 static_assert(BuiltinArguments::kNewTargetIndex == 0);
6285 static_assert(BuiltinArguments::kTargetIndex == 1);
6286 static_assert(BuiltinArguments::kArgcIndex == 2);
6287 static_assert(BuiltinArguments::kPaddingIndex == 3);
6288 if_false1 = efalse1 = vfalse1 =
6289 graph()->NewNode(common()->Call(call_descriptor), stub_code,
6290 receiver, jsgraph()->PaddingConstant(), argc,
6291 target, jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant(), entry,
6292 argc, context, frame_state, efalse1, if_false1);
6293 }
6294
6295 if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true1, if_false1);
6296 efalse0 =
6297 graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue1, efalse1, if_false0);
6298 vfalse0 =
6299 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
6300 vtrue1, vfalse1, if_false0);
6301 }
6302
6303 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true0, if_false0);
6304 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue0, efalse0, control);
6305 value = graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
6306 vtrue0, vfalse0, control);
6307
6308 // Convert the hole to undefined. Do this last, so that we can optimize
6309 // conversion operator via some smart strength reduction in many cases.
6310 if (IsHoleyElementsKind(kind)) {
6311 value =
6312 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ConvertTaggedHoleToUndefined(), value);
6313 }
6314
6315 controls_to_merge.push_back(control);
6316 effects_to_merge.push_back(effect);
6317 values_to_merge.push_back(value);
6318 }
6319
6320 if (controls_to_merge.size() > 1) {
6321 int const count = static_cast<int>(controls_to_merge.size());
6322
6323 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(count), count,
6324 &controls_to_merge.front());
6325 effects_to_merge.push_back(control);
6326 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(count), count + 1,
6327 &effects_to_merge.front());
6328 values_to_merge.push_back(control);
6329 value =
6330 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, count),
6331 count + 1, &values_to_merge.front());
6332 }
6333
6334 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
6335 return Replace(value);
6336}
6337
6338// ES6 section 22.1.3.23 Array.prototype.slice ( )
6339Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayPrototypeSlice(Node* node) {
6340 if (!v8_flags.turbo_inline_array_builtins) return NoChange();
6341 JSCallNode n(node);
6342 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6343 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
6344 return NoChange();
6345 }
6346
6347 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
6348 Node* start = n.ArgumentOr(0, jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
6349 Node* end = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph());
6350 Node* context = n.context();
6351 Effect effect = n.effect();
6352 Control control = n.control();
6353
6354 // Optimize for the case where we simply clone the {receiver}, i.e. when the
6355 // {start} is zero and the {end} is undefined (meaning it will be set to
6356 // {receiver}s "length" property). This logic should be in sync with
6357 // ReduceArrayPrototypeSlice (to a reasonable degree). This is because
6358 // CloneFastJSArray produces arrays which are potentially COW. If there's a
6359 // discrepancy, TF generates code which produces a COW array and then expects
6360 // it to be non-COW (or the other way around) -> immediate deopt.
6361 if (!NumberMatcher(start).Is(0) ||
6362 !HeapObjectMatcher(end).Is(factory()->undefined_value())) {
6363 return NoChange();
6364 }
6365
6366 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
6367 if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
6368 ZoneRefSet<Map> const& receiver_maps = inference.GetMaps();
6369
6370 // Check that the maps are of JSArray (and more).
6371 // TODO(turbofan): Consider adding special case for the common pattern
6372 // `slice.call(arguments)`, for example jQuery makes heavy use of that.
6373 bool can_be_holey = false;
6374 for (MapRef receiver_map : receiver_maps) {
6375 if (!receiver_map.supports_fast_array_iteration(broker())) {
6376 return inference.NoChange();
6377 }
6378 if (IsHoleyElementsKind(receiver_map.elements_kind())) {
6379 can_be_holey = true;
6380 }
6381 }
6382
6383 if (!dependencies()->DependOnArraySpeciesProtector()) {
6384 return inference.NoChange();
6385 }
6386 if (can_be_holey && !dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
6387 return inference.NoChange();
6388 }
6389 inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
6390 control, p.feedback());
6391
6392 // TODO(turbofan): We can do even better here, either adding a CloneArray
6393 // simplified operator, whose output type indicates that it's an Array,
6394 // saving subsequent checks, or yet better, by introducing new operators
6395 // CopySmiOrObjectElements / CopyDoubleElements and inlining the JSArray
6396 // allocation in here. That way we'd even get escape analysis and scalar
6397 // replacement to help in some cases.
6398 Callable callable =
6399 Builtins::CallableFor(isolate(), Builtin::kCloneFastJSArray);
6400 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
6401 graph()->zone(), callable.descriptor(),
6402 callable.descriptor().GetStackParameterCount(), CallDescriptor::kNoFlags,
6403 Operator::kNoThrow | Operator::kNoDeopt);
6404
6405 // Calls to Builtin::kCloneFastJSArray produce COW arrays
6406 // if the original array is COW
6407 Node* clone = effect =
6408 graph()->NewNode(common()->Call(call_descriptor),
6409 jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(callable.code()), receiver,
6410 context, effect, control);
6411
6412 ReplaceWithValue(node, clone, effect, control);
6413 return Replace(clone);
6414}
6415
6416// ES6 section 22.1.2.2 Array.isArray ( arg )
6417Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayIsArray(Node* node) {
6418 // We certainly know that undefined is not an array.
6419 JSCallNode n(node);
6420 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
6421 Node* value = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
6422 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
6423 return Replace(value);
6424 }
6425
6426 Effect effect = n.effect();
6427 Control control = n.control();
6428 Node* context = n.context();
6429 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
6430 Node* object = n.Argument(0);
6431 node->ReplaceInput(0, object);
6432 node->ReplaceInput(1, context);
6433 node->ReplaceInput(2, frame_state);
6434 node->ReplaceInput(3, effect);
6435 node->ReplaceInput(4, control);
6436 node->TrimInputCount(5);
6437 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->ObjectIsArray());
6438 return Changed(node);
6439}
6440
6441Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayIterator(Node* node,
6442 ArrayIteratorKind array_kind,
6443 IterationKind iteration_kind) {
6444 JSCallNode n(node);
6445 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
6446 Node* context = n.context();
6447 Effect effect = n.effect();
6448 Control control = n.control();
6449
6450 // Check if we know that {receiver} is a valid JSReceiver.
6451 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
6452 if (!inference.HaveMaps() || !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAreJSReceiver()) {
6453 return NoChange();
6454 }
6455
6456 // TypedArray iteration is stricter: it throws if the receiver is not a typed
6457 // array. So don't bother optimizing in that case.
6458 if (array_kind == ArrayIteratorKind::kTypedArray &&
6459 !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(InstanceType::JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE)) {
6460 return NoChange();
6461 }
6462
6463 if (array_kind == ArrayIteratorKind::kTypedArray) {
6464 // Make sure we deopt when the JSArrayBuffer is detached.
6465 if (!dependencies()->DependOnArrayBufferDetachingProtector()) {
6466 CallParameters const& p = CallParametersOf(node->op());
6467 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
6468 return NoChange();
6469 }
6470
6471 std::set<ElementsKind> elements_kinds;
6472 for (MapRef map : inference.GetMaps()) {
6473 elements_kinds.insert(map.elements_kind());
6474 }
6475
6476 // The following detach check is built with the given {elements_kinds} in
6477 // mind, so we have to install dependency on those.
6478 inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(
6479 dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect, control,
6480 CallParametersOf(node->op()).feedback());
6481
6482 JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node);
6483 a.CheckIfTypedArrayWasDetached(
6484 TNode<JSTypedArray>::UncheckedCast(receiver),
6485 std::move(elements_kinds), p.feedback());
6486 std::tie(effect, control) = ReleaseEffectAndControlFromAssembler(&a);
6487 }
6488 }
6489
6490 // JSCreateArrayIterator doesn't have control output, so we bypass the old
6491 // JSCall node on the control chain.
6492 ReplaceWithValue(node, node, node, control);
6493
6494 // Morph the {node} into a JSCreateArrayIterator with the given {kind}.
6495 node->ReplaceInput(0, receiver);
6496 node->ReplaceInput(1, context);
6497 node->ReplaceInput(2, effect);
6498 node->ReplaceInput(3, control);
6499 node->TrimInputCount(4);
6500 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node,
6501 javascript()->CreateArrayIterator(iteration_kind));
6502 return Changed(node);
6503}
6504
6505// ES #sec-%arrayiteratorprototype%.next
6506Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayIteratorPrototypeNext(Node* node) {
6507 JSCallNode n(node);
6508 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6509 Node* iterator = n.receiver();
6510 Node* context = n.context();
6511 Effect effect = n.effect();
6512 Control control = n.control();
6513
6514 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
6515 return NoChange();
6516 }
6517
6518 if (iterator->opcode() != IrOpcode::kJSCreateArrayIterator) return NoChange();
6519
6520 IterationKind const iteration_kind =
6521 CreateArrayIteratorParametersOf(iterator->op()).kind();
6522 Node* iterated_object = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(iterator, 0);
6523 Effect iterator_effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(iterator)};
6524
6525 MapInference inference(broker(), iterated_object, iterator_effect);
6526 if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
6527 ZoneRefSet<Map> const& iterated_object_maps = inference.GetMaps();
6528
6529 // Check that various {iterated_object_maps} have compatible elements kinds.
6530 ElementsKind elements_kind = iterated_object_maps[0].elements_kind();
6531 if (IsTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
6532 // TurboFan doesn't support loading from BigInt typed arrays yet.
6533 if (elements_kind == BIGUINT64_ELEMENTS ||
6534 elements_kind == BIGINT64_ELEMENTS) {
6535 return inference.NoChange();
6536 }
6537 for (MapRef iterated_object_map : iterated_object_maps) {
6538 if (iterated_object_map.elements_kind() != elements_kind) {
6539 return inference.NoChange();
6540 }
6541 }
6542 } else {
6543 if (!CanInlineArrayIteratingBuiltin(broker(), iterated_object_maps,
6544 &elements_kind)) {
6545 return inference.NoChange();
6546 }
6547 }
6548
6549 if (IsHoleyElementsKind(elements_kind) &&
6550 !dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
6551 return inference.NoChange();
6552 }
6553
6554 if (IsFloat16TypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
6555 // TODO(v8:14212): Allow optimizing Float16 typed arrays here, once they are
6556 // supported in the rest of the compiler.
6557 return inference.NoChange();
6558 }
6559
6560 // Since the map inference was done relative to {iterator_effect} rather than
6561 // {effect}, we need to guard the use of the map(s) even when the inference
6562 // was reliable.
6563 inference.InsertMapChecks(jsgraph(), &effect, control, p.feedback());
6564
6565 if (IsTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
6566 // See if we can skip the detaching check.
6567 if (!dependencies()->DependOnArrayBufferDetachingProtector()) {
6568 // Bail out if the {iterated_object}s JSArrayBuffer was detached.
6569 Node* buffer = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6570 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewBuffer()),
6571 iterated_object, effect, control);
6572 Node* buffer_bit_field = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6573 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferBitField()),
6574 buffer, effect, control);
6575 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(
6576 simplified()->NumberEqual(),
6577 graph()->NewNode(
6578 simplified()->NumberBitwiseAnd(), buffer_bit_field,
6579 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(JSArrayBuffer::WasDetachedBit::kMask)),
6580 jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
6581 effect = graph()->NewNode(
6582 simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kArrayBufferWasDetached,
6583 p.feedback()),
6584 check, effect, control);
6585 }
6586 }
6587
6588 // Load the [[NextIndex]] from the {iterator} and leverage the fact
6589 // that we definitely know that it's in Unsigned32 range since the
6590 // {iterated_object} is either a JSArray or a JSTypedArray. For the
6591 // latter case we even know that it's a Smi in UnsignedSmall range.
6592 FieldAccess index_access = AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayIteratorNextIndex();
6593 if (IsTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
6594 index_access.type = TypeCache::Get()->kJSTypedArrayLengthType;
6595 } else {
6596 index_access.type = TypeCache::Get()->kJSArrayLengthType;
6597 }
6598 Node* index = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(index_access),
6599 iterator, effect, control);
6600
6601 // Load the elements of the {iterated_object}. While it feels
6602 // counter-intuitive to place the elements pointer load before
6603 // the condition below, as it might not be needed (if the {index}
6604 // is out of bounds for the {iterated_object}), it's better this
6605 // way as it allows the LoadElimination to eliminate redundant
6606 // reloads of the elements pointer.
6607 Node* elements = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6608 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements()),
6609 iterated_object, effect, control);
6610
6611 // Load the length of the {iterated_object}. Due to the map checks we
6612 // already know something about the length here, which we can leverage
6613 // to generate Word32 operations below without additional checking.
6614 FieldAccess length_access =
6615 IsTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)
6616 ? AccessBuilder::ForJSTypedArrayLength()
6617 : AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(elements_kind);
6618 Node* length = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6619 simplified()->LoadField(length_access), iterated_object, effect, control);
6620
6621 // Check whether {index} is within the valid range for the {iterated_object}.
6622 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThan(), index, length);
6623 Node* branch =
6624 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kNone), check, control);
6625
6626 Node* done_true;
6627 Node* value_true;
6628 Node* etrue = effect;
6629 Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
6630 {
6631 // This extra check exists to refine the type of {index} but also to break
6632 // an exploitation technique that abuses typer mismatches.
6633 if (v8_flags.turbo_typer_hardening) {
6634 index = etrue = graph()->NewNode(
6635 simplified()->CheckBounds(p.feedback(),
6636 CheckBoundsFlag::kAbortOnOutOfBounds),
6637 index, length, etrue, if_true);
6638 }
6639
6640 done_true = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
6641 if (iteration_kind == IterationKind::kKeys) {
6642 // Just return the {index}.
6643 value_true = index;
6644 } else {
6645 DCHECK(iteration_kind == IterationKind::kEntries ||
6646 iteration_kind == IterationKind::kValues);
6647
6648 if (IsTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
6649 Node* base_ptr = etrue =
6650 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(
6651 AccessBuilder::ForJSTypedArrayBasePointer()),
6652 iterated_object, etrue, if_true);
6653 Node* external_ptr = etrue = graph()->NewNode(
6654 simplified()->LoadField(
6655 AccessBuilder::ForJSTypedArrayExternalPointer()),
6656 iterated_object, etrue, if_true);
6657
6658 ExternalArrayType array_type = kExternalInt8Array;
6659 switch (elements_kind) {
6660#define TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) \
6661 case TYPE##_ELEMENTS: \
6662 array_type = kExternal##Type##Array; \
6663 break;
6664 TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
6665 default:
6666 UNREACHABLE();
6667#undef TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
6668 }
6669
6670 Node* buffer = etrue =
6671 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(
6672 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewBuffer()),
6673 iterated_object, etrue, if_true);
6674
6675 value_true = etrue =
6676 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadTypedElement(array_type), buffer,
6677 base_ptr, external_ptr, index, etrue, if_true);
6678 } else {
6679 value_true = etrue = graph()->NewNode(
6680 simplified()->LoadElement(
6681 AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(elements_kind)),
6682 elements, index, etrue, if_true);
6683
6684 // Convert hole to undefined if needed.
6685 if (IsHoleyElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
6686 value_true = ConvertHoleToUndefined(value_true, elements_kind);
6687 }
6688 }
6689
6690 if (iteration_kind == IterationKind::kEntries) {
6691 // Allocate elements for key/value pair
6692 value_true = etrue =
6693 graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateKeyValueArray(), index,
6694 value_true, context, etrue);
6695 } else {
6696 DCHECK_EQ(IterationKind::kValues, iteration_kind);
6697 }
6698 }
6699
6700 // Increment the [[NextIndex]] field in the {iterator}. The TypeGuards
6701 // above guarantee that the {next_index} is in the UnsignedSmall range.
6702 Node* next_index = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), index,
6703 jsgraph()->OneConstant());
6704 etrue = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StoreField(index_access), iterator,
6705 next_index, etrue, if_true);
6706 }
6707
6708 Node* done_false;
6709 Node* value_false;
6710 Node* efalse = effect;
6711 Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
6712 {
6713 // iterator.[[NextIndex]] >= array.length, stop iterating.
6714 done_false = jsgraph()->TrueConstant();
6715 value_false = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
6716
6717 if (!IsTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
6718 // Mark the {iterator} as exhausted by setting the [[NextIndex]] to a
6719 // value that will never pass the length check again (aka the maximum
6720 // value possible for the specific iterated object). Note that this is
6721 // different from what the specification says, which is changing the
6722 // [[IteratedObject]] field to undefined, but that makes it difficult
6723 // to eliminate the map checks and "length" accesses in for..of loops.
6724 //
6725 // This is not necessary for JSTypedArray's, since the length of those
6726 // cannot change later and so if we were ever out of bounds for them
6727 // we will stay out-of-bounds forever.
6728 Node* end_index = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(index_access.type.Max());
6729 efalse = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StoreField(index_access),
6730 iterator, end_index, efalse, if_false);
6731 }
6732 }
6733
6734 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
6735 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
6736 Node* value =
6737 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
6738 value_true, value_false, control);
6739 Node* done =
6740 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
6741 done_true, done_false, control);
6742
6743 // Create IteratorResult object.
6744 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateIterResultObject(),
6745 value, done, context, effect);
6746 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
6747 return Replace(value);
6748}
6749
6750// ES6 section 21.1.3.2 String.prototype.charCodeAt ( pos )
6751// ES6 section 21.1.3.3 String.prototype.codePointAt ( pos )
6752Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeStringAt(
6753 const Operator* string_access_operator, Node* node) {
6754 DCHECK(string_access_operator->opcode() == IrOpcode::kStringCharCodeAt ||
6755 string_access_operator->opcode() == IrOpcode::kStringCodePointAt);
6756 JSCallNode n(node);
6757 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6758 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
6759 return NoChange();
6760 }
6761
6762 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
6763 Node* index = n.ArgumentOr(0, jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
6764 Effect effect = n.effect();
6765 Control control = n.control();
6766
6767 // Ensure that the {receiver} is actually a String.
6768 receiver = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()),
6769 receiver, effect, control);
6770
6771 // Determine the {receiver} length.
6772 Node* receiver_length =
6773 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringLength(), receiver);
6774
6775 // Check that the {index} is within range.
6776 index = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckBounds(p.feedback()),
6777 index, receiver_length, effect, control);
6778
6779 // Return the character from the {receiver} as single character string.
6780 Node* value = effect = graph()->NewNode(string_access_operator, receiver,
6781 index, effect, control);
6782
6783 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
6784 return Replace(value);
6785}
6786
6787// ES section 21.1.3.20
6788// String.prototype.startsWith ( searchString [ , position ] )
6789Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeStartsWith(Node* node) {
6790 JSCallNode n(node);
6791 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6792 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
6793 return NoChange();
6794 }
6795
6796 TNode<Object> search_element = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
6797
6798 // Here are three conditions:
6799 // First, If search_element is definitely not a string, we make no change.
6800 // Second, If search_element is definitely a string and its length is less
6801 // or equal than max inline matching sequence threshold, we could inline
6802 // the entire matching sequence.
6803 // Third, we try to inline, and have a runtime deopt if search_element is
6804 // not a string.
6805 HeapObjectMatcher search_element_matcher(search_element);
6806 if (search_element_matcher.HasResolvedValue()) {
6807 ObjectRef target_ref = search_element_matcher.Ref(broker());
6808 if (!target_ref.IsString()) return NoChange();
6809 StringRef search_element_string = target_ref.AsString();
6810 if (!search_element_string.IsContentAccessible()) return NoChange();
6811 int length = search_element_string.length();
6812 // If search_element's length is less or equal than
6813 // kMaxInlineMatchSequence, we inline the entire
6814 // matching sequence.
6815 if (length <= kMaxInlineMatchSequence) {
6816 JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node);
6817 Node* subgraph = a.ReduceStringPrototypeStartsWith(search_element_string);
6818 return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
6819 }
6820 }
6821
6822 JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node);
6823 Node* subgraph = a.ReduceStringPrototypeStartsWith();
6824 return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
6825}
6826
6827// ES section 21.1.3.7
6828// String.prototype.endsWith(searchString [, endPosition])
6829Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeEndsWith(Node* node) {
6830 JSCallNode n(node);
6831 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6832 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
6833 return NoChange();
6834 }
6835
6836 TNode<Object> search_element = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
6837
6838 // Here are three conditions:
6839 // First, If search_element is definitely not a string, we make no change.
6840 // Second, If search_element is definitely a string and its length is less
6841 // or equal than max inline matching sequence threshold, we could inline
6842 // the entire matching sequence.
6843 // Third, we try to inline, and have a runtime deopt if search_element is
6844 // not a string.
6845 HeapObjectMatcher search_element_matcher(search_element);
6846 if (search_element_matcher.HasResolvedValue()) {
6847 ObjectRef target_ref = search_element_matcher.Ref(broker());
6848 if (!target_ref.IsString()) return NoChange();
6849 StringRef search_element_string = target_ref.AsString();
6850 if (!search_element_string.IsContentAccessible()) return NoChange();
6851 int length = search_element_string.length();
6852 // If search_element's length is less or equal than
6853 // kMaxInlineMatchSequence, we inline the entire
6854 // matching sequence.
6855 if (length <= kMaxInlineMatchSequence) {
6856 JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node);
6857 Node* subgraph = a.ReduceStringPrototypeEndsWith(search_element_string);
6858 return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
6859 }
6860 }
6861
6862 JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node);
6863 Node* subgraph = a.ReduceStringPrototypeEndsWith();
6864 return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
6865}

6867// ES section 21.1.3.1 String.prototype.charAt ( pos )
6868Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeCharAt(Node* node) {
6869 JSCallNode n(node);
6870 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6871 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
6872 return NoChange();
6873 }
6874
6875 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
6876 Node* index = n.ArgumentOr(0, jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
6877
6878 // Attempt to constant fold the operation when we know
6879 // that receiver is a string and index is a number.
6880 HeapObjectMatcher receiver_matcher(receiver);
6881 NumberMatcher index_matcher(index);
6882 if (receiver_matcher.HasResolvedValue()) {
6883 HeapObjectRef receiver_ref = receiver_matcher.Ref(broker());
6884 if (!receiver_ref.IsString()) return NoChange();
6885 StringRef receiver_string = receiver_ref.AsString();
6886 bool is_content_accessible = receiver_string.IsContentAccessible();
6887 bool is_integer_in_max_range =
6888 index_matcher.IsInteger() &&
6889 index_matcher.IsInRange(
6890 0.0, static_cast<double>(JSObject::kMaxElementIndex));
6891 if (is_content_accessible && is_integer_in_max_range) {
6892 JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node);
6893 Node* subgraph = a.ReduceStringPrototypeCharAt(
6894 receiver_string,
6895 static_cast<uint32_t>(index_matcher.ResolvedValue()));
6896 return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
6897 }
6898 }
6899
6900 JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node);
6901 Node* subgraph = a.ReduceStringPrototypeCharAt();
6902 return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
6903}

6915
6916 Node* receiver = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6917 simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()), n.receiver(), effect, control);
6918
6919 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
6920 RelaxEffectsAndControls(node);
6921 node->ReplaceInput(0, receiver);
6922 node->TrimInputCount(1);
6923 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, simplified()->StringToLowerCaseIntl());
6924 NodeProperties::SetType(node, Type::String());
6925 return Changed(node);

6951// ES #sec-string.fromcharcode
6952Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringFromCharCode(Node* node) {
6953 JSCallNode n(node);
6954 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6955 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
6956 return NoChange();
6957 }
6958 if (n.ArgumentCount() == 1) {
6959 Effect effect = n.effect();
6960 Control control = n.control();
6961 Node* input = n.Argument(0);
6962
6963 input = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6964 simplified()->SpeculativeToNumber(NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball,
6965 p.feedback()),
6966 input, effect, control);
6967
6968 Node* value =
6969 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringFromSingleCharCode(), input);
6970 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect);
6971 return Replace(value);
6972 }
6973 return NoChange();
6974}

6976// ES #sec-string.fromcodepoint
6977Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringFromCodePoint(Node* node) {
6978 JSCallNode n(node);
6979 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6980 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
6981 return NoChange();
6982 }
6983 if (n.ArgumentCount() != 1) return NoChange();
6984
6985 Effect effect = n.effect();
6986 Control control = n.control();
6987 Node* input = n.Argument(0);
6988
6989 input = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6990 simplified()->CheckBounds(p.feedback(),
6991 CheckBoundsFlag::kConvertStringAndMinusZero),
6992 input, jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(0x10FFFF + 1), effect, control);
6993
6994 Node* value =
6995 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringFromSingleCodePoint(), input);
6996 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect);
6997 return Replace(value);

7000Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeIterator(Node* node) {
7001 JSCallNode n(node);
7002 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
7003 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
7004 return NoChange();
7005 }
7006 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
7007 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
7008 Node* receiver = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7009 simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()), n.receiver(), effect, control);
7010 Node* iterator = effect =
7011 graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateStringIterator(), receiver,
7012 jsgraph()->NoContextConstant(), effect);
7013 ReplaceWithValue(node, iterator, effect, control);
7014 return Replace(iterator);
7015}

7017#ifdef V8_INTL_SUPPORT
7018
7019Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeLocaleCompareIntl(Node* node) {
7020 JSCallNode n(node);
7021 // Signature: receiver.localeCompare(compareString, locales, options)
7022 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1 || n.ArgumentCount() > 3) {
7023 return NoChange();
7024 }
7025
7026 {
7027 DirectHandle<Object> locales;
7028 {
7029 HeapObjectMatcher m(n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph()));
7030 if (!m.HasResolvedValue()) return NoChange();
7031 if (m.Is(factory()->undefined_value())) {
7032 locales = factory()->undefined_value();
7033 } else {
7034 ObjectRef ref = m.Ref(broker());
7035 if (!ref.IsString()) return NoChange();
7036 StringRef sref = ref.AsString();
7037 if (std::optional<Handle<String>> maybe_locales =
7038 sref.ObjectIfContentAccessible(broker())) {
7039 locales = *maybe_locales;
7040 } else {
7041 return NoChange();
7042 }
7043 }
7044 }
7045
7046 TNode<Object> options = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(2, jsgraph());
7047 {
7048 HeapObjectMatcher m(options);
7049 if (!m.Is(factory()->undefined_value())) {
7050 return NoChange();
7051 }
7052 }
7053
7054 if (Intl::CompareStringsOptionsFor(broker()->local_isolate_or_isolate(),
7055 locales, factory()->undefined_value()) !=
7056 Intl::CompareStringsOptions::kTryFastPath) {
7057 return NoChange();
7058 }
7059 }
7060
7061 Callable callable =
7062 Builtins::CallableFor(isolate(), Builtin::kStringFastLocaleCompare);
7063 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
7064 graph()->zone(), callable.descriptor(),
7065 callable.descriptor().GetStackParameterCount(),
7066 CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState);
7067 node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
7068 if (n.ArgumentCount() == 3) {
7069 node->RemoveInput(n.ArgumentIndex(2));
7070 } else if (n.ArgumentCount() == 1) {
7071 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), n.LastArgumentIndex() + 1,
7072 jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
7073 } else {
7074 DCHECK_EQ(2, n.ArgumentCount());
7075 }
7076 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 0,
7077 jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(callable.code()));
7078 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, common()->Call(call_descriptor));
7079 return Changed(node);
7080}
7081#endif // V8_INTL_SUPPORT
7082
7083Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringIteratorPrototypeNext(Node* node) {
7084 JSCallNode n(node);
7085 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
7086 Effect effect = n.effect();
7087 Control control = n.control();
7088 Node* context = n.context();
7089
7090 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
7091 if (!inference.HaveMaps() ||
7092 !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(JS_STRING_ITERATOR_TYPE)) {
7093 return NoChange();
7094 }
7095
7096 Node* string = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7097 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSStringIteratorString()),
7098 receiver, effect, control);
7099 Node* index = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7100 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSStringIteratorIndex()),
7101 receiver, effect, control);
7102 Node* length = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringLength(), string);
7103
7104 // branch0: if (index < length)
7105 Node* check0 =
7106 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThan(), index, length);
7107 Node* branch0 =
7108 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kNone), check0, control);
7109
7110 Node* etrue0 = effect;
7111 Node* if_true0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch0);
7112 Node* done_true;
7113 Node* vtrue0;
7114 {
7115 done_true = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
7116 vtrue0 = etrue0 = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringFromCodePointAt(),
7117 string, index, etrue0, if_true0);
7118
7119 // Update iterator.[[NextIndex]]
7120 Node* char_length = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringLength(), vtrue0);
7121 index = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), index, char_length);
7122 etrue0 = graph()->NewNode(
7123 simplified()->StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForJSStringIteratorIndex()),
7124 receiver, index, etrue0, if_true0);
7125 }
7126
7127 Node* if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch0);
7128 Node* done_false;
7129 Node* vfalse0;
7130 {
7131 vfalse0 = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
7132 done_false = jsgraph()->TrueConstant();
7133 }
7134
7135 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true0, if_false0);
7136 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue0, effect, control);
7137 Node* value =
7138 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2), vtrue0,
7139 vfalse0, control);
7140 Node* done =
7141 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
7142 done_true, done_false, control);
7143
7144 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateIterResultObject(),
7145 value, done, context, effect);
7146
7147 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
7148 return Replace(value);
7149}
7150
7151// ES #sec-string.prototype.concat
7152Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeConcat(Node* node) {
7153 JSCallNode n(node);
7154 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
7155 const int parameter_count = n.ArgumentCount();
7156 if (parameter_count > 1) return NoChange();
7157 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
7158 return NoChange();
7159 }
7160
7161 Effect effect = n.effect();
7162 Control control = n.control();
7163 Node* receiver = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7164 simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()), n.receiver(), effect, control);
7165
7166 if (parameter_count == 0) {
7167 ReplaceWithValue(node, receiver, effect, control);
7168 return Replace(receiver);
7169 }
7170
7171 Node* argument = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7172 simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()), n.Argument(0), effect, control);
7173 Node* receiver_length =
7174 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringLength(), receiver);
7175 Node* argument_length =
7176 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringLength(), argument);
7177 Node* length = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), receiver_length,
7178 argument_length);
7179 length = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7180 simplified()->CheckBounds(p.feedback()), length,
7181 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(String::kMaxLength + 1), effect, control);
7182
7183 Node* value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringConcat(), length, receiver,
7184 argument);
7185
7186 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
7187 return Replace(value);
7188}
