7190namespace {
7191
7192FrameState CreateStringCreateLazyDeoptContinuationFrameState(
7193 JSGraph* graph, SharedFunctionInfoRef shared, Node* target, Node* context,
7194 Node* outer_frame_state) {
7195 Node* const receiver = graph->TheHoleConstant();
7196 Node* stack_parameters[]{receiver};
7197 const int stack_parameter_count = arraysize(stack_parameters);
7198 return CreateJavaScriptBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
7199 graph, shared, Builtin::kStringCreateLazyDeoptContinuation, target,
7200 context, stack_parameters, stack_parameter_count, outer_frame_state,
7201 ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY);
7202}
7203
7204} // namespace
7205
7206Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringConstructor(Node* node,
7207 JSFunctionRef constructor) {
7208 JSConstructNode n(node);
7209 if (n.target() != n.new_target()) return NoChange();
7210
7211 DCHECK_EQ(constructor, native_context().string_function(broker_));
7212 DCHECK(constructor.initial_map(broker_).IsJSPrimitiveWrapperMap());
7213
7214 Node* context = n.context();
7215 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
7216 Effect effect = n.effect();
7217 Control control = n.control();
7218
7219 Node* primitive_value;
7220 if (n.ArgumentCount() == 0) {
7221 primitive_value = jsgraph()->EmptyStringConstant();
7222 } else {
7223 // Insert a construct stub frame into the chain of frame states. This will
7224 // reconstruct the proper frame when deoptimizing within the constructor.
7225 frame_state = CreateConstructInvokeStubFrameState(
7226 node, frame_state, constructor.shared(broker_), context, common(),
7227 graph());
7228
7229 // This continuation takes the newly created primitive string, and wraps it
7230 // in a string wrapper, matching CreateStringWrapper.
7231 Node* continuation_frame_state =
7232 CreateStringCreateLazyDeoptContinuationFrameState(
7233 jsgraph(), constructor.shared(broker_), n.target(), context,
7234 frame_state);
7235
7236 primitive_value = effect = control =
7237 graph()->NewNode(javascript()->ToString(), n.Argument(0), context,
7238 continuation_frame_state, effect, control);
7239
7240 // Rewire potential exception edges.
7241 Node* on_exception = nullptr;
7242 if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &on_exception)) {
7243 // Create appropriate {IfException} and {IfSuccess} nodes.
7244 Node* if_exception =
7245 graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), effect, control);
7246 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), control);
7247
7248 // Join the exception edges.
7249 Node* merge =
7250 graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_exception, on_exception);
7251 Node* ephi = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), if_exception,
7252 on_exception, merge);
7253 Node* phi =
7254 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
7255 if_exception, on_exception, merge);
7256 ReplaceWithValue(on_exception, phi, ephi, merge);
7257 merge->ReplaceInput(1, on_exception);
7258 ephi->ReplaceInput(1, on_exception);
7259 phi->ReplaceInput(1, on_exception);
7260 }
7261 }
7262
7263 RelaxControls(node, control);
7264 node->ReplaceInput(0, primitive_value);
7265 node->ReplaceInput(1, context);
7266 node->ReplaceInput(2, effect);
7267 node->TrimInputCount(3);
7268 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->CreateStringWrapper());
7269 return Changed(node);
7270}
7271
7272Reduction JSCallReducer::ReducePromiseConstructor(Node* node) {
7273 PromiseBuiltinReducerAssembler a(this, node);
7274
7275 // We only inline when we have the executor.
7276 if (a.ConstructArity() < 1) return NoChange();
7277 // Only handle builtins Promises, not subclasses.
7278 if (a.TargetInput() != a.NewTargetInput()) return NoChange();
7279 if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseHookProtector()) return NoChange();
7280
7281 TNode<Object> subgraph = a.ReducePromiseConstructor(native_context());
7282 return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
7283}
7284
7285bool JSCallReducer::DoPromiseChecks(MapInference* inference) {
7286 if (!inference->HaveMaps()) return false;
7287 ZoneRefSet<Map> const& receiver_maps = inference->GetMaps();
7288
7289 // Check whether all {receiver_maps} are JSPromise maps and
7290 // have the initial Promise.prototype as their [[Prototype]].
7291 for (MapRef receiver_map : receiver_maps) {
7292 if (!receiver_map.IsJSPromiseMap()) return false;
7293 HeapObjectRef prototype = receiver_map.prototype(broker());
7294 if (!prototype.equals(native_context().promise_prototype(broker()))) {
7295 return false;
7296 }
7297 }
7298
7299 return true;
7300}
7301
7302// ES section #sec-promise.prototype.catch
7303Reduction JSCallReducer::ReducePromisePrototypeCatch(Node* node) {
7304 JSCallNode n(node);
7305 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
7306 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
7307 return NoChange();
7308 }
7309 int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
7310 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
7311 Effect effect = n.effect();
7312 Control control = n.control();
7313
7314 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
7315 if (!DoPromiseChecks(&inference)) return inference.NoChange();
7316
7317 if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseThenProtector()) {
7318 return inference.NoChange();
7319 }
7320 inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
7321 control, p.feedback());
7322
7323 // Massage the {node} to call "then" instead by first removing all inputs
7324 // following the onRejected parameter, and then filling up the parameters
7325 // to two inputs from the left with undefined.
7326 Node* target = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
7327 native_context().promise_then(broker()), broker());
7328 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, target, 0);
7329 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
7330 for (; arity > 1; --arity) node->RemoveInput(3);
7331 for (; arity < 2; ++arity) {
7332 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 2, jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
7333 }
7334 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
7335 node, javascript()->Call(
7336 JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(arity), p.frequency(), p.feedback(),
7337 ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined, p.speculation_mode(),
7338 CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated));
7339 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReducePromisePrototypeThen(node));
7340}
7341
7342Node* JSCallReducer::CreateClosureFromBuiltinSharedFunctionInfo(
7343 SharedFunctionInfoRef shared, Node* context, Node* effect, Node* control) {
7344 DCHECK(shared.HasBuiltinId());
7345 Handle<FeedbackCell> feedback_cell =
7346 isolate()->factory()->many_closures_cell();
7347 Callable const callable =
7348 Builtins::CallableFor(isolate(), shared.builtin_id());
7349 CodeRef code = MakeRef(broker(), *callable.code());
7350 return graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateClosure(shared, code),
7351 jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(feedback_cell), context,
7352 effect, control);
7353}
7354
7355// ES section #sec-promise.prototype.finally
7356Reduction JSCallReducer::ReducePromisePrototypeFinally(Node* node) {
7357 JSCallNode n(node);
7358 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
7359 int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
7360 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
7361 Node* on_finally = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
7362 Effect effect = n.effect();
7363 Control control = n.control();
7364 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
7365 return NoChange();
7366 }
7367
7368 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
7369 if (!DoPromiseChecks(&inference)) return inference.NoChange();
7370 ZoneRefSet<Map> const& receiver_maps = inference.GetMaps();
7371
7372 if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseHookProtector()) {
7373 return inference.NoChange();
7374 }
7375 if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseThenProtector()) {
7376 return inference.NoChange();
7377 }
7378 if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseSpeciesProtector()) {
7379 return inference.NoChange();
7380 }
7381 inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
7382 control, p.feedback());
7383
7384 // Check if {on_finally} is callable, and if so wrap it into appropriate
7385 // closures that perform the finalization.
7386 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsCallable(), on_finally);
7387 Node* branch =
7388 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check, control);
7389
7390 Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
7391 Node* etrue = effect;
7392 Node* catch_true;
7393 Node* then_true;
7394 {
7395 Node* context = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(native_context(), broker());
7396 Node* constructor = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
7397 native_context().promise_function(broker()), broker());
7398
7399 // Allocate shared context for the closures below.
7400 context = etrue = graph()->NewNode(
7401 javascript()->CreateFunctionContext(
7402 native_context().scope_info(broker()),
7403 int{PromiseBuiltins::kPromiseFinallyContextLength} -
7404 Context::MIN_CONTEXT_SLOTS,
7405 FUNCTION_SCOPE),
7406 context, etrue, if_true);
7407 etrue = graph()->NewNode(
7408 simplified()->StoreField(
7409 AccessBuilder::ForContextSlot(PromiseBuiltins::kOnFinallySlot)),
7410 context, on_finally, etrue, if_true);
7411 etrue = graph()->NewNode(
7412 simplified()->StoreField(
7413 AccessBuilder::ForContextSlot(PromiseBuiltins::kConstructorSlot)),
7414 context, constructor, etrue, if_true);
7415
7416 // Allocate the closure for the reject case.
7417 SharedFunctionInfoRef promise_catch_finally =
7418 MakeRef(broker(), factory()->promise_catch_finally_shared_fun());
7419 catch_true = etrue = CreateClosureFromBuiltinSharedFunctionInfo(
7420 promise_catch_finally, context, etrue, if_true);
7421
7422 // Allocate the closure for the fulfill case.
7423 SharedFunctionInfoRef promise_then_finally =
7424 MakeRef(broker(), factory()->promise_then_finally_shared_fun());
7425 then_true = etrue = CreateClosureFromBuiltinSharedFunctionInfo(
7426 promise_then_finally, context, etrue, if_true);
7427 }
7428
7429 Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
7430 Node* efalse = effect;
7431 Node* catch_false = on_finally;
7432 Node* then_false = on_finally;
7433
7434 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
7435 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
7436 Node* catch_finally =
7437 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
7438 catch_true, catch_false, control);
7439 Node* then_finally =
7440 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
7441 then_true, then_false, control);
7442
7443 // At this point we definitely know that {receiver} has one of the
7444 // {receiver_maps}, so insert a MapGuard as a hint for the lowering
7445 // of the call to "then" below.
7446 {
7447 effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->MapGuard(receiver_maps), receiver,
7448 effect, control);
7449 }
7450
7451 // Massage the {node} to call "then" instead by first removing all inputs
7452 // following the onFinally parameter, and then replacing the only parameter
7453 // input with the {on_finally} value.
7454 Node* target = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
7455 native_context().promise_then(broker()), broker());
7456 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, target, n.TargetIndex());
7457 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
7458 NodeProperties::ReplaceControlInput(node, control);
7459 for (; arity > 2; --arity) node->RemoveInput(2);
7460 for (; arity < 2; ++arity) {
7461 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 2, then_finally);
7462 }
7463 node->ReplaceInput(2, then_finally);
7464 node->ReplaceInput(3, catch_finally);
7465 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
7466 node, javascript()->Call(
7467 JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(arity), p.frequency(), p.feedback(),
7468 ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined, p.speculation_mode(),
7469 CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated));
7470 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReducePromisePrototypeThen(node));
7471}
7472
7473Reduction JSCallReducer::ReducePromisePrototypeThen(Node* node) {
7474 JSCallNode n(node);
7475 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
7476 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
7477 return NoChange();
7478 }
7479
7480 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
7481 Node* on_fulfilled = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
7482 Node* on_rejected = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph());
7483 Node* context = n.context();
7484 Effect effect = n.effect();
7485 Control control = n.control();
7486 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
7487
7488 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
7489 if (!DoPromiseChecks(&inference)) return inference.NoChange();
7490
7491 if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseHookProtector()) {
7492 return inference.NoChange();
7493 }
7494 if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseSpeciesProtector()) {
7495 return inference.NoChange();
7496 }
7497 inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
7498 control, p.feedback());
7499
7500 // Check that {on_fulfilled} is callable.
7501 on_fulfilled = graph()->NewNode(
7502 common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, BranchHint::kTrue),
7503 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsCallable(), on_fulfilled),
7504 on_fulfilled, jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
7505
7506 // Check that {on_rejected} is callable.
7507 on_rejected = graph()->NewNode(
7508 common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, BranchHint::kTrue),
7509 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsCallable(), on_rejected),
7510 on_rejected, jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
7511
7512 // Create the resulting JSPromise.
7513 Node* promise = effect =
7514 graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreatePromise(), context, effect);
7515
7516 // Chain {result} onto {receiver}.
7517 promise = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7518 javascript()->PerformPromiseThen(), receiver, on_fulfilled, on_rejected,
7519 promise, context, frame_state, effect, control);
7520
7521 // At this point we know that {promise} is going to have the
7522 // initial Promise map, since even if {PerformPromiseThen}
7523 // above called into the host rejection tracker, the {promise}
7524 // doesn't escape to user JavaScript. So bake this information
7525 // into the graph such that subsequent passes can use the
7526 // information for further optimizations.
7527 MapRef promise_map =
7528 native_context().promise_function(broker()).initial_map(broker());
7529 effect =
7530 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->MapGuard(ZoneRefSet<Map>(promise_map)),
7531 promise, effect, control);
7532
7533 ReplaceWithValue(node, promise, effect, control);
7534 return Replace(promise);
7535}
7536
7537// ES section #sec-promise.resolve
7538Reduction JSCallReducer::ReducePromiseResolveTrampoline(Node* node) {
7539 JSCallNode n(node);
7540 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
7541 Node* value = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
7542 Node* context = n.context();
7543 Effect effect = n.effect();
7544 Control control = n.control();
7545 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
7546
7547 // Only reduce when the receiver is guaranteed to be a JSReceiver.
7548 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
7549 if (!inference.HaveMaps() || !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAreJSReceiver()) {
7550 return NoChange();
7551 }
7552
7553 // Morph the {node} into a JSPromiseResolve operation.
7554 node->ReplaceInput(0, receiver);
7555 node->ReplaceInput(1, value);
7556 node->ReplaceInput(2, context);
7557 node->ReplaceInput(3, frame_state);
7558 node->ReplaceInput(4, effect);
7559 node->ReplaceInput(5, control);
7560 node->TrimInputCount(6);
7561 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->PromiseResolve());
7562 return Changed(node);
7563}
7564
7565// ES #sec-typedarray-constructors
7566Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceTypedArrayConstructor(
7567 Node* node, SharedFunctionInfoRef shared) {
7568 JSConstructNode n(node);
7569 Node* target = n.target();
7570 Node* arg0 = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
7571 Node* arg1 = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph());
7572 Node* arg2 = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(2, jsgraph());
7573 Node* new_target = n.new_target();
7574 Node* context = n.context();
7575 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
7576 Effect effect = n.effect();
7577 Control control = n.control();
7578
7579 // Insert a construct stub frame into the chain of frame states. This will
7580 // reconstruct the proper frame when deoptimizing within the constructor.
7581 frame_state = CreateConstructInvokeStubFrameState(node, frame_state, shared,
7582 context, common(), graph());
7583
7584 // This continuation just returns the newly created JSTypedArray. We
7585 // pass the_hole as the receiver, just like the builtin construct stub
7586 // does in this case.
7587 Node* const receiver = jsgraph()->TheHoleConstant();
7588 Node* continuation_frame_state = CreateGenericLazyDeoptContinuationFrameState(
7589 jsgraph(), shared, target, context, receiver, frame_state);
7590
7591 Node* result = graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateTypedArray(), target,
7592 new_target, arg0, arg1, arg2, context,
7593 continuation_frame_state, effect, control);
7594 return Replace(result);
7595}
7596
7597// ES #sec-get-%typedarray%.prototype-@@tostringtag
7598Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceTypedArrayPrototypeToStringTag(Node* node) {
7599 Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
7600 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
7601 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
7602
7603 NodeVector values(graph()->zone());
7604 NodeVector effects(graph()->zone());
7605 NodeVector controls(graph()->zone());
7606
7607 Node* smi_check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsSmi(), receiver);
7608 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse), smi_check,
7609 control);
7610
7611 values.push_back(jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
7612 effects.push_back(effect);
7613 controls.push_back(graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), control));
7614
7615 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), control);
7616 Node* receiver_map = effect =
7617 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap()),
7618 receiver, effect, control);
7619 Node* receiver_bit_field2 = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7620 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField2()), receiver_map,
7621 effect, control);
7622 Node* receiver_elements_kind = graph()->NewNode(
7623 simplified()->NumberShiftRightLogical(),
7624 graph()->NewNode(
7625 simplified()->NumberBitwiseAnd(), receiver_bit_field2,
7626 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kMask)),
7627 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kShift));
7628
7629 // Offset the elements kind by FIRST_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND,
7630 // so that the branch cascade below is turned into a simple table
7631 // switch by the ControlFlowOptimizer later.
7632 receiver_elements_kind = graph()->NewNode(
7633 simplified()->NumberSubtract(), receiver_elements_kind,
7634 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(FIRST_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND));
7635
7636 // To be converted into a switch by the ControlFlowOptimizer, the below
7637 // code requires that TYPED_ARRAYS and RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAYS are consecutive.
7638 static_assert(LAST_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND + 1 ==
7639 FIRST_RAB_GSAB_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND);
7640#define TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) \
7641 do { \
7642 Node* check = graph()->NewNode( \
7643 simplified()->NumberEqual(), receiver_elements_kind, \
7644 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(TYPE##_ELEMENTS - \
7645 FIRST_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND)); \
7646 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), check, control); \
7647 values.push_back(jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole( \
7648 broker()->GetTypedArrayStringTag(TYPE##_ELEMENTS), broker())); \
7649 effects.push_back(effect); \
7650 controls.push_back(graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), control)); \
7651 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), control); \
7652 } while (false);
7653 TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
7654 RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
7655#undef TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
7656
7657 values.push_back(jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
7658 effects.push_back(effect);
7659 controls.push_back(control);
7660
7661 int const count = static_cast<int>(controls.size());
7662 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(count), count, &controls.front());
7663 effects.push_back(control);
7664 effect =
7665 graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(count), count + 1, &effects.front());
7666 values.push_back(control);
7667 Node* value =
7668 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, count),
7669 count + 1, &values.front());
7670 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
7671 return Replace(value);
7672}
7673
7674Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayBufferViewByteLengthAccessor(
7675 Node* node, InstanceType instance_type, Builtin builtin) {
7676 // TODO(v8:11111): Optimize for JS_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE too.
7677 DCHECK(instance_type == JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE ||
7678 instance_type == JS_DATA_VIEW_TYPE);
7679 Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
7680 Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
7681 Control control{NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node)};
7682
7683 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
7684 if (!inference.HaveMaps() ||
7685 !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(instance_type)) {
7686 return inference.NoChange();
7687 }
7688
7689 std::set<ElementsKind> elements_kinds;
7690 bool maybe_rab_gsab = false;
7691 if (instance_type == JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE) {
7692 for (MapRef map : inference.GetMaps()) {
7693 ElementsKind kind = map.elements_kind();
7694 elements_kinds.insert(kind);
7695 if (IsRabGsabTypedArrayElementsKind(kind)) maybe_rab_gsab = true;
7696 }
7697 }
7698
7699 if (!maybe_rab_gsab) {
7700 // We do not perform any change depending on this inference.
7701 Reduction unused_reduction = inference.NoChange();
7702 USE(unused_reduction);
7703 // Call default implementation for non-rab/gsab TAs.
7704 return ReduceArrayBufferViewAccessor(
7705 node, instance_type, AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewByteLength(),
7706 builtin);
7707 }
7708
7709 const CallParameters& p = CallParametersOf(node->op());
7710 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
7711 return inference.NoChange();
7712 }
7713 DCHECK(p.feedback().IsValid());
7714
7715 inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
7716 control, p.feedback());
7717
7718 const bool depended_on_detaching_protector =
7719 dependencies()->DependOnArrayBufferDetachingProtector();
7720 if (!depended_on_detaching_protector && instance_type == JS_DATA_VIEW_TYPE) {
7721 // DataView prototype accessors throw on detached ArrayBuffers instead of
7722 // return 0, so skip the optimization.
7723 //
7724 // TODO(turbofan): Ideally we would bail out if the buffer is actually
7725 // detached.
7726 return inference.NoChange();
7727 }
7728
7729 JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node);
7730 TNode<JSTypedArray> typed_array =
7731 TNode<JSTypedArray>::UncheckedCast(receiver);
7732 TNode<Number> length = a.ArrayBufferViewByteLength(
7733 typed_array, instance_type, std::move(elements_kinds), a.ContextInput());
7734
7735 return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, length);
7736}
7737
7738Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayBufferViewByteOffsetAccessor(
7739 Node* node, InstanceType instance_type, Builtin builtin) {
7740 // TODO(v8:11111): Optimize for JS_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE too.
7741 DCHECK(instance_type == JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE ||
7742 instance_type == JS_DATA_VIEW_TYPE);
7743 Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
7744 Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
7745 Control control{NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node)};
7746
7747 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
7748 if (!inference.HaveMaps() ||
7749 !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(instance_type)) {
7750 return inference.NoChange();
7751 }
7752
7753 std::set<ElementsKind> elements_kinds;
7754 bool maybe_rab_gsab = false;
7755 if (instance_type == JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE) {
7756 for (MapRef map : inference.GetMaps()) {
7757 ElementsKind kind = map.elements_kind();
7758 elements_kinds.insert(kind);
7759 if (IsRabGsabTypedArrayElementsKind(kind)) maybe_rab_gsab = true;
7760 }
7761 }
7762
7763 if (!maybe_rab_gsab) {
7764 // We do not perform any change depending on this inference.
7765 Reduction unused_reduction = inference.NoChange();
7766 USE(unused_reduction);
7767 // Call default implementation for non-rab/gsab TAs.
7768 return ReduceArrayBufferViewAccessor(
7769 node, instance_type, AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewByteOffset(),
7770 builtin);
7771 }
7772
7773 // TODO(v8:11111): Optimize for RAG/GSAB TypedArray/DataView.
7774 return inference.NoChange();
7775}
7776
7777Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceTypedArrayPrototypeLength(Node* node) {
7778 Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
7779 Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
7780 Control control{NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node)};
7781
7782 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
7783 if (!inference.HaveMaps() ||
7784 !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE)) {
7785 return inference.NoChange();
7786 }
7787
7788 std::set<ElementsKind> elements_kinds;
7789 bool maybe_rab_gsab = false;
7790 for (MapRef map : inference.GetMaps()) {
7791 ElementsKind kind = map.elements_kind();
7792 elements_kinds.insert(kind);
7793 if (IsRabGsabTypedArrayElementsKind(kind)) maybe_rab_gsab = true;
7794 }
7795
7796 if (!maybe_rab_gsab) {
7797 // We do not perform any change depending on this inference.
7798 Reduction unused_reduction = inference.NoChange();
7799 USE(unused_reduction);
7800 // Call default implementation for non-rab/gsab TAs.
7801 return ReduceArrayBufferViewAccessor(node, JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE,
7802 AccessBuilder::ForJSTypedArrayLength(),
7803 Builtin::kTypedArrayPrototypeLength);
7804 }
7805
7806 if (!inference.RelyOnMapsViaStability(dependencies())) {
7807 return inference.NoChange();
7808 }
7809
7810 JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node);
7811 TNode<JSTypedArray> typed_array =
7812 TNode<JSTypedArray>::UncheckedCast(receiver);
7813 TNode<Number> length = a.TypedArrayLength(
7814 typed_array, std::move(elements_kinds), a.ContextInput());
7815
7816 return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, length);
7817}

7827 Node* input = n.Argument(0);
7828 Node* value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsFiniteNumber(), input);
7829 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
7830 return Replace(value);
7831}

7874
7875Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceMapPrototypeGet(Node* node) {
7876 // We only optimize if we have target, receiver and key parameters.
7877 JSCallNode n(node);
7878 if (n.ArgumentCount() != 1) return NoChange();
7879 Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
7880 Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
7881 Control control{NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node)};
7882 Node* key = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 2);
7883
7884 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
7885 if (!inference.HaveMaps() || !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(JS_MAP_TYPE)) {
7886 return NoChange();
7887 }
7888
7889 Node* table = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7890 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionTable()), receiver,
7891 effect, control);
7892
7893 Node* entry = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7894 simplified()->FindOrderedCollectionEntry(CollectionKind::kMap), table,
7895 key, effect, control);
7896
7897 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(), entry,
7898 jsgraph()->MinusOneConstant());
7899
7900 Node* branch = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), check, control);
7901
7902 // Key not found.
7903 Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
7904 Node* etrue = effect;
7905 Node* vtrue = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
7906
7907 // Key found.
7908 Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
7909 Node* efalse = effect;
7910 Node* vfalse = efalse = graph()->NewNode(
7911 simplified()->LoadElement(AccessBuilder::ForOrderedHashMapEntryValue()),
7912 table, entry, efalse, if_false);
7913
7914 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
7915 Node* value = graph()->NewNode(
7916 common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2), vtrue, vfalse, control);
7917 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
7918
7919 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
7920 return Replace(value);
7921}
7922
7923namespace {
7924
7925InstanceType InstanceTypeForCollectionKind(CollectionKind kind) {
7926 switch (kind) {
7927 case CollectionKind::kMap:
7928 return JS_MAP_TYPE;
7929 case CollectionKind::kSet:
7930 return JS_SET_TYPE;
7931 }
7932 UNREACHABLE();
7933}
7934
7935} // namespace

7937Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceCollectionPrototypeHas(
7938 Node* node, CollectionKind collection_kind) {
7939 // We only optimize if we have target, receiver and key parameters.
7940 JSCallNode n(node);
7941 if (n.ArgumentCount() != 1) return NoChange();
7942 Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
7943 Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
7944 Control control{NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node)};
7945 Node* key = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 2);
7946 InstanceType instance_type = InstanceTypeForCollectionKind(collection_kind);
7947
7948 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
7949 if (!inference.HaveMaps() ||
7950 !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(instance_type)) {
7951 return NoChange();
7952 }
7953
7954 Node* table = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7955 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionTable()), receiver,
7956 effect, control);
7957
7958 Node* index = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7959 simplified()->FindOrderedCollectionEntry(collection_kind), table, key,
7960 effect, control);
7961
7962 Node* value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(), index,
7963 jsgraph()->MinusOneConstant());
7964 value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->BooleanNot(), value);
7965
7966 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
7967 return Replace(value);
7968}
7969
7970Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceMapPrototypeHas(Node* node) {
7971 return ReduceCollectionPrototypeHas(node, CollectionKind::kMap);
7972}
7973
7974Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceSetPrototypeHas(Node* node) {
7975 return ReduceCollectionPrototypeHas(node, CollectionKind::kSet);
7976}
7977
7978Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceCollectionIteration(
7979 Node* node, CollectionKind collection_kind, IterationKind iteration_kind) {
7980 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSCall, node->opcode());
7981 Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
7982 Node* context = NodeProperties::GetContextInput(node);
7983 Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
7984 Control control{NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node)};
7985
7986 InstanceType type = InstanceTypeForCollectionKind(collection_kind);
7987 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
7988 if (!inference.HaveMaps() || !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(type)) {
7989 return NoChange();
7990 }
7991
7992 Node* js_create_iterator = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7993 javascript()->CreateCollectionIterator(collection_kind, iteration_kind),
7994 receiver, context, effect, control);
7995 ReplaceWithValue(node, js_create_iterator, effect);
7996 return Replace(js_create_iterator);
7997}

7999Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceCollectionPrototypeSize(
8000 Node* node, CollectionKind collection_kind) {
8001 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSCall, node->opcode());
8002 Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
8003 Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
8004 Control control{NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node)};
8005
8006 InstanceType type = InstanceTypeForCollectionKind(collection_kind);
8007 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
8008 if (!inference.HaveMaps() || !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(type)) {
8009 return NoChange();
8010 }
8011
8012 Node* table = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8013 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionTable()), receiver,
8014 effect, control);
8015 Node* value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8016 simplified()->LoadField(
8017 AccessBuilder::ForOrderedHashMapOrSetNumberOfElements()),
8018 table, effect, control);
8019 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
8020 return Replace(value);
8021}
8022
8023Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceCollectionIteratorPrototypeNext(
8024 Node* node, int entry_size, Handle<HeapObject> empty_collection,
8025 InstanceType collection_iterator_instance_type_first,
8026 InstanceType collection_iterator_instance_type_last) {
8027 JSCallNode n(node);
8028 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
8029 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
8030 return NoChange();
8031 }
8032
8033 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
8034 Node* context = n.context();
8035 Effect effect = n.effect();
8036 Control control = n.control();
8037
8038 // A word of warning to begin with: This whole method might look a bit
8039 // strange at times, but that's mostly because it was carefully handcrafted
8040 // to allow for full escape analysis and scalar replacement of both the
8041 // collection iterator object and the iterator results, including the
8042 // key-value arrays in case of Set/Map entry iteration.
8043 //
8044 // TODO(turbofan): Currently the escape analysis (and the store-load
8045 // forwarding) is unable to eliminate the allocations for the key-value
8046 // arrays in case of Set/Map entry iteration, and we should investigate
8047 // how to update the escape analysis / arrange the graph in a way that
8048 // this becomes possible.
8049
8050 InstanceType receiver_instance_type;
8051 {
8052 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
8053 if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
8054 ZoneRefSet<Map> const& receiver_maps = inference.GetMaps();
8055 receiver_instance_type = receiver_maps[0].instance_type();
8056 for (size_t i = 1; i < receiver_maps.size(); ++i) {
8057 if (receiver_maps[i].instance_type() != receiver_instance_type) {
8058 return inference.NoChange();
8059 }
8060 }
8061 if (receiver_instance_type < collection_iterator_instance_type_first ||
8062 receiver_instance_type > collection_iterator_instance_type_last) {
8063 return inference.NoChange();
8064 }
8065 inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
8066 control, p.feedback());
8067 }
8068
8069 // Transition the JSCollectionIterator {receiver} if necessary
8070 // (i.e. there were certain mutations while we're iterating).
8071 {
8072 Node* done_loop;
8073 Node* done_eloop;
8074 Node* loop = control =
8075 graph()->NewNode(common()->Loop(2), control, control);
8076 Node* eloop = effect =
8077 graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), effect, effect, loop);
8078 Node* terminate = graph()->NewNode(common()->Terminate(), eloop, loop);
8079 MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), terminate);
8080
8081 // Check if reached the final table of the {receiver}.
8082 Node* table = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8083 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionIteratorTable()),
8084 receiver, effect, control);
8085 Node* next_table = effect =
8086 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(
8087 AccessBuilder::ForOrderedHashMapOrSetNextTable()),
8088 table, effect, control);
8089 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsSmi(), next_table);
8090 control =
8091 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check, control);
8092
8093 // Abort the {loop} when we reach the final table.
8094 done_loop = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), control);
8095 done_eloop = effect;
8096
8097 // Migrate to the {next_table} otherwise.
8098 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), control);
8099
8100 // Self-heal the {receiver}s index.
8101 Node* index = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8102 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionIteratorIndex()),
8103 receiver, effect, control);
8104 Callable const callable =
8105 Builtins::CallableFor(isolate(), Builtin::kOrderedHashTableHealIndex);
8106 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
8107 graph()->zone(), callable.descriptor(),
8108 callable.descriptor().GetStackParameterCount(),
8109 CallDescriptor::kNoFlags, Operator::kEliminatable);
8110 index = effect =
8111 graph()->NewNode(common()->Call(call_descriptor),
8112 jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(callable.code()), table,
8113 index, jsgraph()->NoContextConstant(), effect);
8114
8115 index = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8116 common()->TypeGuard(TypeCache::Get()->kFixedArrayLengthType), index,
8117 effect, control);
8118
8119 // Update the {index} and {table} on the {receiver}.
8120 effect = graph()->NewNode(
8121 simplified()->StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionIteratorIndex()),
8122 receiver, index, effect, control);
8123 effect = graph()->NewNode(
8124 simplified()->StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionIteratorTable()),
8125 receiver, next_table, effect, control);
8126
8127 // Tie the knot.
8128 loop->ReplaceInput(1, control);
8129 eloop->ReplaceInput(1, effect);
8130
8131 control = done_loop;
8132 effect = done_eloop;
8133 }
8134
8135 // Get current index and table from the JSCollectionIterator {receiver}.
8136 Node* index = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8137 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionIteratorIndex()),
8138 receiver, effect, control);
8139 Node* table = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8140 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionIteratorTable()),
8141 receiver, effect, control);
8142
8143 // Create the {JSIteratorResult} first to ensure that we always have
8144 // a dominating Allocate node for the allocation folding phase.
8145 Node* iterator_result = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8146 javascript()->CreateIterResultObject(), jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant(),
8147 jsgraph()->TrueConstant(), context, effect);
8148
8149 // Look for the next non-holey key, starting from {index} in the {table}.
8150 Node* controls[2];
8151 Node* effects[3];
8152 {
8153 // Compute the currently used capacity.
8154 Node* number_of_buckets = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8155 simplified()->LoadField(
8156 AccessBuilder::ForOrderedHashMapOrSetNumberOfBuckets()),
8157 table, effect, control);
8158 Node* number_of_elements = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8159 simplified()->LoadField(
8160 AccessBuilder::ForOrderedHashMapOrSetNumberOfElements()),
8161 table, effect, control);
8162 Node* number_of_deleted_elements = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8163 simplified()->LoadField(
8164 AccessBuilder::ForOrderedHashMapOrSetNumberOfDeletedElements()),
8165 table, effect, control);
8166 Node* used_capacity =
8167 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), number_of_elements,
8168 number_of_deleted_elements);
8169
8170 // Skip holes and update the {index}.
8171 Node* loop = graph()->NewNode(common()->Loop(2), control, control);
8172 Node* eloop =
8173 graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), effect, effect, loop);
8174 Node* terminate = graph()->NewNode(common()->Terminate(), eloop, loop);
8175 MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), terminate);
8176 Node* iloop = graph()->NewNode(
8177 common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2), index, index, loop);
8178
8179 index = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8180 common()->TypeGuard(TypeCache::Get()->kFixedArrayLengthType), iloop,
8181 eloop, control);
8182 {
8183 Node* check0 = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThan(), index,
8184 used_capacity);
8185 Node* branch0 =
8186 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check0, loop);
8187
8188 Node* if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch0);
8189 Node* efalse0 = effect;
8190 {
8191 // Mark the {receiver} as exhausted.
8192 efalse0 = graph()->NewNode(
8193 simplified()->StoreField(
8194 AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionIteratorTable()),
8195 receiver, jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(empty_collection), efalse0,
8196 if_false0);
8197
8198 controls[0] = if_false0;
8199 effects[0] = efalse0;
8200 }
8201
8202 Node* if_true0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch0);
8203 Node* etrue0 = effect;
8204 {
8205 // Load the key of the entry.
8206 static_assert(OrderedHashMap::HashTableStartIndex() ==
8207 OrderedHashSet::HashTableStartIndex());
8208 Node* entry_start_position = graph()->NewNode(
8209 simplified()->NumberAdd(),
8210 graph()->NewNode(
8211 simplified()->NumberAdd(),
8212 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberMultiply(), index,
8213 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(entry_size)),
8214 number_of_buckets),
8215 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(OrderedHashMap::HashTableStartIndex()));
8216 Node* entry_key = etrue0 = graph()->NewNode(
8217 simplified()->LoadElement(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement()),
8218 table, entry_start_position, etrue0, if_true0);
8219
8220 // Advance the index.
8221 index = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), index,
8222 jsgraph()->OneConstant());
8223
8224 Node* check1 =
8225 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), entry_key,
8226 jsgraph()->HashTableHoleConstant());
8227 Node* branch1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse),
8228 check1, if_true0);
8229
8230 {
8231 // Abort loop with resulting value.
8232 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch1);
8233 effect = etrue0;
8234 Node* value = effect =
8235 graph()->NewNode(common()->TypeGuard(Type::NonInternal()),
8236 entry_key, effect, control);
8237 Node* done = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
8238
8239 // Advance the index on the {receiver}.
8240 effect = graph()->NewNode(
8241 simplified()->StoreField(
8242 AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionIteratorIndex()),
8243 receiver, index, effect, control);
8244
8245 // The actual {value} depends on the {receiver} iteration type.
8246 switch (receiver_instance_type) {
8247 case JS_MAP_KEY_ITERATOR_TYPE:
8248 case JS_SET_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
8249 break;
8250
8251 case JS_SET_KEY_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
8252 value = effect =
8253 graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateKeyValueArray(), value,
8254 value, context, effect);
8255 break;
8256
8257 case JS_MAP_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
8258 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8259 simplified()->LoadElement(
8260 AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement()),
8261 table,
8262 graph()->NewNode(
8263 simplified()->NumberAdd(), entry_start_position,
8264 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(OrderedHashMap::kValueOffset)),
8265 effect, control);
8266 break;
8267
8268 case JS_MAP_KEY_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
8269 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8270 simplified()->LoadElement(
8271 AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement()),
8272 table,
8273 graph()->NewNode(
8274 simplified()->NumberAdd(), entry_start_position,
8275 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(OrderedHashMap::kValueOffset)),
8276 effect, control);
8277 value = effect =
8278 graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateKeyValueArray(),
8279 entry_key, value, context, effect);
8280 break;
8281
8282 default:
8283 UNREACHABLE();
8284 }
8285
8286 // Store final {value} and {done} into the {iterator_result}.
8287 effect =
8288 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StoreField(
8289 AccessBuilder::ForJSIteratorResultValue()),
8290 iterator_result, value, effect, control);
8291 effect =
8292 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StoreField(
8293 AccessBuilder::ForJSIteratorResultDone()),
8294 iterator_result, done, effect, control);
8295
8296 controls[1] = control;
8297 effects[1] = effect;
8298 }
8299
8300 // Continue with next loop index.
8301 loop->ReplaceInput(1, graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch1));
8302 eloop->ReplaceInput(1, etrue0);
8303 iloop->ReplaceInput(1, index);
8304 }
8305 }
8306
8307 control = effects[2] = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), 2, controls);
8308 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), 3, effects);
8309 }
8310
8311 // Yield the final {iterator_result}.
8312 ReplaceWithValue(node, iterator_result, effect, control);
8313 return Replace(iterator_result);
8314}
8315
8316Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayBufferIsView(Node* node) {
8317 JSCallNode n(node);
8318 Node* value = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
8319 RelaxEffectsAndControls(node);
8320 node->ReplaceInput(0, value);
8321 node->TrimInputCount(1);
8322 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, simplified()->ObjectIsArrayBufferView());
8323 return Changed(node);
8324}
8325
8326Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayBufferViewAccessor(
8327 Node* node, InstanceType instance_type, FieldAccess const& access,
8328 Builtin builtin) {
8329 // TODO(v8:11111): Optimize for JS_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE too.
8330 TNode<JSArrayBufferView> receiver = TNode<JSArrayBufferView>::UncheckedCast(
8331 NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1));
8332 Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
8333
8334 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
8335 if (!inference.HaveMaps() ||
8336 !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(instance_type)) {
8337 return inference.NoChange();
8338 }
8339
8340 DCHECK_IMPLIES((builtin == Builtin::kTypedArrayPrototypeLength ||
8341 builtin == Builtin::kTypedArrayPrototypeByteLength),
8342 base::none_of(inference.GetMaps(), [](MapRef map) {
8343 return IsRabGsabTypedArrayElementsKind(map.elements_kind());
8344 }));
8345
8346 if (!inference.RelyOnMapsViaStability(dependencies())) {
8347 return inference.NoChange();
8348 }
8349
8350 const bool depended_on_detaching_protector =
8351 dependencies()->DependOnArrayBufferDetachingProtector();
8352 if (!depended_on_detaching_protector && instance_type == JS_DATA_VIEW_TYPE) {
8353 // DataView prototype accessors throw on detached ArrayBuffers instead of
8354 // return 0, so skip the optimization.
8355 //
8356 // TODO(turbofan): Ideally we would bail out if the buffer is actually
8357 // detached.
8358 return inference.NoChange();
8359 }
8360
8361 JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node, effect);
8362
8363 // Load the {receiver}s field.
8364 DCHECK_EQ(access.machine_type.representation(),
8365 MachineType::PointerRepresentation());
8366 TNode<UintPtrT> value = a.EnterMachineGraph<UintPtrT>(
8367 a.LoadField<UintPtrT>(access, receiver), UseInfo::Word());
8368
8369 // See if we can skip the detaching check.
8370 if (!depended_on_detaching_protector) {
8371 // Check whether {receiver}s JSArrayBuffer was detached.
8372 TNode<HeapObject> buffer = a.LoadField<HeapObject>(
8373 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewBuffer(), receiver);
8374 TNode<Word32T> bitfield = a.EnterMachineGraph<Word32T>(
8375 a.LoadField<Word32T>(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferBitField(), buffer),
8376 UseInfo::TruncatingWord32());
8377 TNode<Word32T> detached_bit = a.Word32And(
8378 bitfield, a.Uint32Constant(JSArrayBuffer::WasDetachedBit::kMask));
8379
8380 // TODO(turbofan): Ideally we would bail out here if the {receiver}s
8381 // JSArrayBuffer was detached, but there's no way to guard against
8382 // deoptimization loops right now, since the JSCall {node} is usually
8383 // created from a LOAD_IC inlining, and so there's no CALL_IC slot
8384 // from which we could use the speculation bit.
8385 value = a.MachineSelect<UintPtrT>(detached_bit, a.UintPtrConstant(0), value,
8386 BranchHint::kFalse);
8387 }
8388
8389 TNode<Number> result =
8390 a.ExitMachineGraph<Number>(value, MachineType::PointerRepresentation(),
8391 TypeCache::Get()->kJSTypedArrayLengthType);
8392 return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, result);
8393}
8394
8395Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceDataViewAccess(Node* node, DataViewAccess access,
8396 ExternalArrayType element_type) {
8397 // TODO(v8:11111): Optimize for JS_RAB_GSAB_DATA_VIEW_TYPE too.
8398 JSCallNode n(node);
8399 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
8400 size_t const element_size = ExternalArrayElementSize(element_type);
8401 Effect effect = n.effect();
8402 Control control = n.control();
8403 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
8404 Node* offset = n.ArgumentOr(0, jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
8405 Node* value = nullptr;
8406
8407 if (!Is64() && (element_type == kExternalBigInt64Array ||
8408 element_type == kExternalBigUint64Array)) {
8409 return NoChange();
8410 }
8411
8412 if (access == DataViewAccess::kSet) {
8413 value = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph());
8414 }
8415 const int endian_index = (access == DataViewAccess::kGet ? 1 : 2);
8416 Node* is_little_endian =
8417 n.ArgumentOr(endian_index, jsgraph()->FalseConstant());
8418
8419 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
8420 return NoChange();
8421 }
8422
8423 // Only do stuff if the {receiver} is really a DataView.
8424 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
8425 if (!inference.HaveMaps() ||
8426 !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(JS_DATA_VIEW_TYPE)) {
8427 return NoChange();
8428 }
8429
8430 // Check that the {offset} is within range for the {receiver}.
8431 HeapObjectMatcher m(receiver);
8432 if (m.HasResolvedValue() && m.Ref(broker()).IsJSDataView()) {
8433 // We only deal with DataViews here whose [[ByteLength]] is at least
8434 // {element_size}, as for all other DataViews it'll be out-of-bounds.
8435 JSDataViewRef dataview = m.Ref(broker()).AsJSDataView();
8436
8437 size_t length = dataview.byte_length();
8438 if (length < element_size) return NoChange();
8439
8440 // Check that the {offset} is within range of the {length}.
8441 Node* byte_length = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(length - (element_size - 1));
8442 offset = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckBounds(p.feedback()),
8443 offset, byte_length, effect, control);
8444 } else {
8445 // We only deal with DataViews here that have Smi [[ByteLength]]s.
8446 Node* byte_length = effect =
8447 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(
8448 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewByteLength()),
8449 receiver, effect, control);
8450 if (element_size > 1) {
8451 // For non-byte accesses we also need to check that the {offset}
8452 // plus the {element_size}-1 fits within the given {byte_length}.
8453 // So to keep this as a single check on the {offset}, we subtract
8454 // the {element_size}-1 from the {byte_length} here (clamped to
8455 // positive safe integer range), and perform a check against that
8456 // with the {offset} below.
8457 byte_length = graph()->NewNode(
8458 simplified()->NumberMax(), jsgraph()->ZeroConstant(),
8459 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberSubtract(), byte_length,
8460 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(element_size - 1)));
8461 }
8462
8463 // Check that the {offset} is within range of the {byte_length}.
8464 offset = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckBounds(p.feedback()),
8465 offset, byte_length, effect, control);
8466 }
8467
8468 // Coerce {is_little_endian} to boolean.
8469 is_little_endian =
8470 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ToBoolean(), is_little_endian);
8471
8472 // Coerce {value} to Number.
8473 if (access == DataViewAccess::kSet) {
8474 if (element_type == kExternalBigInt64Array ||
8475 element_type == kExternalBigUint64Array) {
8476 value = effect =
8477 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->SpeculativeToBigInt(
8478 BigIntOperationHint::kBigInt, p.feedback()),
8479 value, effect, control);
8480 } else {
8481 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8482 simplified()->SpeculativeToNumber(
8483 NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball, p.feedback()),
8484 value, effect, control);
8485 }
8486 }
8487
8488 // We need to retain either the {receiver} itself or its backing
8489 // JSArrayBuffer to make sure that the GC doesn't collect the raw
8490 // memory. We default to {receiver} here, and only use the buffer
8491 // if we anyways have to load it (to reduce register pressure).
8492 Node* buffer_or_receiver = receiver;
8493
8494 if (!dependencies()->DependOnArrayBufferDetachingProtector()) {
8495 // Get the underlying buffer and check that it has not been detached.
8496 Node* buffer = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8497 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewBuffer()),
8498 receiver, effect, control);
8499
8500 // Bail out if the {buffer} was detached.
8501 Node* buffer_bit_field = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8502 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferBitField()),
8503 buffer, effect, control);
8504 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(
8505 simplified()->NumberEqual(),
8506 graph()->NewNode(
8507 simplified()->NumberBitwiseAnd(), buffer_bit_field,
8508 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(JSArrayBuffer::WasDetachedBit::kMask)),
8509 jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
8510 effect = graph()->NewNode(
8511 simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kArrayBufferWasDetached,
8512 p.feedback()),
8513 check, effect, control);
8514
8515 // We can reduce register pressure by holding on to the {buffer}
8516 // now to retain the backing store memory.
8517 buffer_or_receiver = buffer;
8518 }
8519
8520 // Load the {receiver}s data pointer.
8521 Node* data_pointer = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8522 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSDataViewDataPointer()),
8523 receiver, effect, control);
8524
8525 switch (access) {
8526 case DataViewAccess::kGet:
8527 // Perform the load.
8528 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8529 simplified()->LoadDataViewElement(element_type), buffer_or_receiver,
8530 data_pointer, offset, is_little_endian, effect, control);
8531 break;
8532 case DataViewAccess::kSet:
8533 // Perform the store.
8534 effect = graph()->NewNode(
8535 simplified()->StoreDataViewElement(element_type), buffer_or_receiver,
8536 data_pointer, offset, value, is_little_endian, effect, control);
8537 value = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
8538 break;
8539 }
8540
8541 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
8542 return Changed(value);
8543}
8544
8545// ES6 section 18.2.2 isFinite ( number )
8546Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceGlobalIsFinite(Node* node) {
8547 JSCallNode n(node);
8548 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
8549 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
8550 return NoChange();
8551 }
8552 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
8553 Node* value = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
8554 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
8555 return Replace(value);
8556 }
8557
8558 Effect effect = n.effect();
8559 Control control = n.control();
8560 Node* input = n.Argument(0);
8561
8562 input = effect =
8563 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->SpeculativeToNumber(
8564 NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball, p.feedback()),
8565 input, effect, control);
8566 Node* value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberIsFinite(), input);
8567 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect);
8568 return Replace(value);
8569}

8575 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
8576 return NoChange();
8577 }
8578 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
8579 Node* value = jsgraph()->TrueConstant();
8580 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
8581 return Replace(value);
8582 }
8583

8585 Control control = n.control();
8586 Node* input = n.Argument(0);
8587

8589 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->SpeculativeToNumber(
8590 NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball, p.feedback()),
8591 input, effect, control);
8592 Node* value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberIsNaN(), input);
8593 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect);
8594 return Replace(value);
8595}

8599 Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
8600 Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
8601 Control control{NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node)};
8602

8604 if (!inference.HaveMaps() || !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(JS_DATE_TYPE)) {
8605 return NoChange();
8606 }
8607
8608 Node* value = effect =
8609 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSDateValue()),
8610 receiver, effect, control);
8611 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
8612 return Replace(value);
8613}

8624
8625// ES6 section 20.1.2.13 Number.parseInt ( string, radix )
8626Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceNumberParseInt(Node* node) {
8627 JSCallNode n(node);
8628 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
8629 Node* value = jsgraph()->NaNConstant();
8630 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
8631 return Replace(value);
8632 }
8633
8634 Effect effect = n.effect();
8635 Control control = n.control();
8636 Node* context = n.context();
8637 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
8638 Node* object = n.Argument(0);
8639 Node* radix = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph());
8640
8641 // Try constant-folding when input is a string constant.
8642 HeapObjectMatcher object_matcher(object);
8643 HeapObjectMatcher radix_object_matcher(radix);
8644 NumberMatcher radix_number_matcher(radix);
8645 if (object_matcher.HasResolvedValue() &&
8646 object_matcher.Ref(broker()).IsString() &&
8647 (radix_object_matcher.Is(factory()->undefined_value()) ||
8648 radix_number_matcher.HasResolvedValue())) {
8649 StringRef input_value = object_matcher.Ref(broker()).AsString();
8650 // {undefined} is treated same as 0.
8651 int radix_value = radix_object_matcher.Is(factory()->undefined_value())
8652 ? 0
8653 : DoubleToInt32(radix_number_matcher.ResolvedValue());
8654 if (radix_value != 0 && (radix_value < 2 || radix_value > 36)) {
8655 Node* value = jsgraph()->NaNConstant();
8656 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
8657 return Replace(value);
8658 }
8659
8660 std::optional<double> number = input_value.ToInt(broker(), radix_value);
8661 if (number.has_value()) {
8662 Node* result = graph()->NewNode(common()->NumberConstant(number.value()));
8663 ReplaceWithValue(node, result);
8664 return Replace(result);
8665 }
8666 }
8667
8668 node->ReplaceInput(0, object);
8669 node->ReplaceInput(1, radix);
8670 node->ReplaceInput(2, context);
8671 node->ReplaceInput(3, frame_state);
8672 node->ReplaceInput(4, effect);
8673 node->ReplaceInput(5, control);
8674 node->TrimInputCount(6);
8675 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->ParseInt());
8676 return Changed(node);
8677}
8678
8679Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceRegExpPrototypeTest(Node* node) {
8680 JSCallNode n(node);
8681 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
8682 if (v8_flags.force_slow_path) return NoChange();
8683 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) return NoChange();
8684
8685 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
8686 return NoChange();
8687 }
8688
8689 Effect effect = n.effect();
8690 Control control = n.control();
8691 Node* regexp = n.receiver();
8692
8693 // Only the initial JSRegExp map is valid here, since the following lastIndex
8694 // check as well as the lowered builtin call rely on a known location of the
8695 // lastIndex field.
8696 MapRef regexp_initial_map =
8697 native_context().regexp_function(broker()).initial_map(broker());
8698
8699 MapInference inference(broker(), regexp, effect);
8700 if (!inference.Is(regexp_initial_map)) return inference.NoChange();
8701 ZoneRefSet<Map> const& regexp_maps = inference.GetMaps();
8702
8703 ZoneVector<PropertyAccessInfo> access_infos(graph()->zone());
8704 AccessInfoFactory access_info_factory(broker(), graph()->zone());
8705
8706 for (MapRef map : regexp_maps) {
8707 access_infos.push_back(broker()->GetPropertyAccessInfo(
8708 map, broker()->exec_string(), AccessMode::kLoad));
8709 }
8710
8711 PropertyAccessInfo ai_exec =
8712 access_info_factory.FinalizePropertyAccessInfosAsOne(access_infos,
8713 AccessMode::kLoad);
8714 if (ai_exec.IsInvalid()) return inference.NoChange();
8715 if (!ai_exec.IsFastDataConstant()) return inference.NoChange();
8716
8717 // Do not reduce if the exec method is not on the prototype chain.
8718 OptionalJSObjectRef holder = ai_exec.holder();
8719 if (!holder.has_value()) return inference.NoChange();
8720
8721 // Bail out if the exec method is not the original one.
8722 if (ai_exec.field_representation().IsDouble()) return inference.NoChange();
8723 OptionalObjectRef constant = holder->GetOwnFastConstantDataProperty(
8724 broker(), ai_exec.field_representation(), ai_exec.field_index(),
8725 dependencies());
8726 if (!constant.has_value() ||
8727 !constant->equals(native_context().regexp_exec_function(broker()))) {
8728 return inference.NoChange();
8729 }
8730
8731 // Add proper dependencies on the {regexp}s [[Prototype]]s.
8732 dependencies()->DependOnStablePrototypeChains(
8733 ai_exec.lookup_start_object_maps(), kStartAtPrototype, holder.value());
8734
8735 inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
8736 control, p.feedback());
8737
8738 Node* context = n.context();
8739 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
8740 Node* search = n.Argument(0);
8741 Node* search_string = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8742 simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()), search, effect, control);
8743
8744 Node* lastIndex = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8745 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSRegExpLastIndex()), regexp,
8746 effect, control);
8747
8748 Node* lastIndexSmi = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8749 simplified()->CheckSmi(p.feedback()), lastIndex, effect, control);
8750
8751 Node* is_positive = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThanOrEqual(),
8752 jsgraph()->ZeroConstant(), lastIndexSmi);
8753
8754 effect = graph()->NewNode(
8755 simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kNotASmi, p.feedback()),
8756 is_positive, effect, control);
8757
8758 node->ReplaceInput(0, regexp);
8759 node->ReplaceInput(1, search_string);
8760 node->ReplaceInput(2, context);
8761 node->ReplaceInput(3, frame_state);
8762 node->ReplaceInput(4, effect);
8763 node->ReplaceInput(5, control);
8764 node->TrimInputCount(6);
8765 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->RegExpTest());
8766 return Changed(node);
8767}
8768
8769// ES section #sec-number-constructor
8770Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceNumberConstructor(Node* node) {
8771 JSCallNode n(node);
8772 Node* target = n.target();
8773 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
8774 Node* value = n.ArgumentOr(0, jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
8775 Node* context = n.context();
8776 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
8777
8778 // Create the artificial frame state in the middle of the Number constructor.
8779 SharedFunctionInfoRef shared_info =
8780 native_context().number_function(broker()).shared(broker());
8781 Node* continuation_frame_state = CreateGenericLazyDeoptContinuationFrameState(
8782 jsgraph(), shared_info, target, context, receiver, frame_state);
8783
8784 // Convert the {value} to a Number.
8785 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInputs(node, value);
8786 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->ToNumberConvertBigInt());
8787 NodeProperties::ReplaceFrameStateInput(node, continuation_frame_state);
8788 return Changed(node);
8789}
8790
8791// ES section #sec-bigint-constructor
8792Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceBigIntConstructor(Node* node) {
8793 if (!jsgraph()->machine()->Is64()) return NoChange();
8794
8795 JSCallNode n(node);
8796 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
8797 return NoChange();
8798 }
8799
8800 Node* target = n.target();
8801 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
8802 Node* value = n.Argument(0);
8803 Node* context = n.context();
8804 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
8805
8806 // Create the artificial frame state in the middle of the BigInt constructor.
8807 SharedFunctionInfoRef shared_info =
8808 native_context().bigint_function(broker()).shared(broker());
8809 Node* continuation_frame_state = CreateGenericLazyDeoptContinuationFrameState(
8810 jsgraph(), shared_info, target, context, receiver, frame_state);
8811
8812 // Convert the {value} to a BigInt.
8813 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInputs(node, value);
8814 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->ToBigIntConvertNumber());
8815 NodeProperties::ReplaceFrameStateInput(node, continuation_frame_state);
8816 return Changed(node);
8817}
8818
8819Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceBigIntAsN(Node* node, Builtin builtin) {
8820 DCHECK(builtin == Builtin::kBigIntAsIntN ||
8821 builtin == Builtin::kBigIntAsUintN);
8822
8823 if (!jsgraph()->machine()->Is64()) return NoChange();
8824
8825 JSCallNode n(node);
8826 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
8827 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
8828 return NoChange();
8829 }
8830 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 2) {
8831 return NoChange();
8832 }
8833
8834 Effect effect = n.effect();
8835 Control control = n.control();
8836 Node* bits = n.Argument(0);
8837 Node* value = n.Argument(1);
8838
8839 NumberMatcher matcher(bits);
8840 if (matcher.IsInteger() && matcher.IsInRange(0, 64)) {
8841 const int bits_value = static_cast<int>(matcher.ResolvedValue());
8842 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8843 (builtin == Builtin::kBigIntAsIntN
8844 ? simplified()->SpeculativeBigIntAsIntN(bits_value, p.feedback())
8845 : simplified()->SpeculativeBigIntAsUintN(bits_value,
8846 p.feedback())),
8847 value, effect, control);
8848 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect);
8849 return Replace(value);
8850 }
8851
8852 return NoChange();
8853}
8854
8855std::optional<Reduction> JSCallReducer::TryReduceJSCallMathMinMaxWithArrayLike(
8856 Node* node) {
8857 if (!v8_flags.turbo_optimize_math_minmax) return std::nullopt;
8858
8859 JSCallWithArrayLikeNode n(node);
8860 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
8861 Node* target = n.target();
8862 Effect effect = n.effect();
8863 Control control = n.control();
8864
8865 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
8866 return std::nullopt;
8867 }
8868
8869 if (n.ArgumentCount() != 1) {
8870 return std::nullopt;
8871 }
8872
8873 if (!dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
8874 return std::nullopt;
8875 }
8876
8877 // These ops are handled by ReduceCallOrConstructWithArrayLikeOrSpread.
8878 // IrOpcode::kJSCreateEmptyLiteralArray is not included, since arguments_list
8879 // for Math.min/min is not likely to keep empty.
8880 Node* arguments_list = n.Argument(0);
8881 if (arguments_list->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCreateLiteralArray ||
8882 arguments_list->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCreateArguments) {
8883 return std::nullopt;
8884 }
8885
8886 HeapObjectMatcher m(target);
8887 if (m.HasResolvedValue()) {
8888 ObjectRef target_ref = m.Ref(broker());
8889 if (target_ref.IsJSFunction()) {
8890 JSFunctionRef function = target_ref.AsJSFunction();
8891
8892 // Don't inline cross native context.
8893 if (!function.native_context(broker()).equals(native_context())) {
8894 return std::nullopt;
8895 }
8896
8897 SharedFunctionInfoRef shared = function.shared(broker());
8898 Builtin builtin =
8899 shared.HasBuiltinId() ? shared.builtin_id() : Builtin::kNoBuiltinId;
8900 if (builtin == Builtin::kMathMax || builtin == Builtin::kMathMin) {
8901 return ReduceJSCallMathMinMaxWithArrayLike(node, builtin);
8902 } else {
8903 return std::nullopt;
8904 }
8905 }
8906 }
8907
8908 // Try specialize the JSCallWithArrayLike node with feedback target.
8909 if (ShouldUseCallICFeedback(target) &&
8910 p.feedback_relation() == CallFeedbackRelation::kTarget &&
8911 p.feedback().IsValid()) {
8912 ProcessedFeedback const& feedback =
8913 broker()->GetFeedbackForCall(p.feedback());
8914 if (feedback.IsInsufficient()) {
8915 return std::nullopt;
8916 }
8917 OptionalHeapObjectRef feedback_target = feedback.AsCall().target();
8918 if (feedback_target.has_value() &&
8919 feedback_target->map(broker()).is_callable()) {
8920 Node* target_function =
8921 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(*feedback_target, broker());
8922 ObjectRef target_ref = feedback_target.value();
8923 if (!target_ref.IsJSFunction()) {
8924 return std::nullopt;
8925 }
8926 JSFunctionRef function = target_ref.AsJSFunction();
8927 SharedFunctionInfoRef shared = function.shared(broker());
8928 Builtin builtin =
8929 shared.HasBuiltinId() ? shared.builtin_id() : Builtin::kNoBuiltinId;
8930 if (builtin == Builtin::kMathMax || builtin == Builtin::kMathMin) {
8931 // Check that the {target} is still the {target_function}.
8932 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), target,
8933 target_function);
8934 effect = graph()->NewNode(
8935 simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongCallTarget), check,
8936 effect, control);
8937
8938 // Specialize the JSCallWithArrayLike node to the {target_function}.
8939 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, target_function,
8940 n.TargetIndex());
8941 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
8942 // Try to further reduce the Call MathMin/Max with double array.
8943 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(
8944 ReduceJSCallMathMinMaxWithArrayLike(node, builtin));
8945 }
8946 }
8947 }
8948
8949 return std::nullopt;
8950}
8951
8952Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceJSCallMathMinMaxWithArrayLike(Node* node,
8953 Builtin builtin) {
8954 JSCallWithArrayLikeNode n(node);
8955 DCHECK_NE(n.Parameters().speculation_mode(),
8956 SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation);
8957 DCHECK_EQ(n.ArgumentCount(), 1);
8958
8959 JSCallReducerAssembler a(this, node);
8960 Node* subgraph = a.ReduceJSCallMathMinMaxWithArrayLike(builtin);
8961 return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
8962}
8963
8964#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CONTINUATION_PRESERVED_EMBEDDER_DATA
8965Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceGetContinuationPreservedEmbedderData(
8966 Node* node) {
8967 JSCallNode n(node);
8968 Effect effect = n.effect();
8969 Control control = n.control();
8970
8971 Node* value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
8972 simplified()->GetContinuationPreservedEmbedderData(), effect);
8973
8974 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
8975 return Replace(node);
8976}
8977
8978Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceSetContinuationPreservedEmbedderData(
8979 Node* node) {
8980 JSCallNode n(node);
8981 Effect effect = n.effect();
8982 Control control = n.control();
8983
8984 if (n.ArgumentCount() == 0) return NoChange();
8985
8986 effect =
8987 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->SetContinuationPreservedEmbedderData(),
8988 n.Argument(0), effect);
8989
8990 Node* value = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
8991
8992 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
8993 return Replace(node);
8994}
8995#endif // V8_ENABLE_CONTINUATION_PRESERVED_EMBEDDER_DATA
